Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.74,1:58:12.14,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}總盈利 26.9億
Dialogue: 0,2:01:55.08,2:01:57.88,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}等金融動盪塵埃落定
Dialogue: 0,2:01:57.90,2:02:00.68,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}總共有5萬億美元消失不見 包括養老金 房地產…
Dialogue: 0,2:02:00.78,2:02:04.18,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}401K退休福利 存款和證券
Dialogue: 0,2:02:04.28,2:02:07.48,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}8百萬人失業 6百萬人無家可歸
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.58,2:02:11.48,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}這還只是美國的情況
Dialogue: 0,2:02:14.68,2:02:17.68,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}馬克·鮑姆的妻子 辛西婭說
Dialogue: 0,2:02:17.78,2:02:21.28,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}馬克在金融危機之後變得謙和了
Dialogue: 0,2:02:21.38,2:02:24.18,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}再也不對人說"我早就告訴過你"了
Dialogue: 0,2:02:24.28,2:02:27.58,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}他的手下丹尼 文尼和伯特…
Dialogue: 0,2:02:27.68,2:02:30.58,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}還在曼哈頓經營一家基金
Dialogue: 0,2:02:30.68,2:02:32.88,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}公司旁邊就有松久壽司店
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.50,2:02:38.90,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}查理和傑米試圖去…
Dialogue: 0,2:02:39.00,2:02:41.20,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}起訴信用評級機構
Dialogue: 0,2:02:41.30,2:02:43.40,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}所有的律所都嘲笑他們太天真
Dialogue: 0,2:02:43.50,2:02:45.60,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}傑米還在經營棕地基金
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.70,2:02:47.60,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}但是查理離開了紐約
Dialogue: 0,2:02:47.70,2:02:49.80,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}在北卡羅來納州的夏洛特安家立業
Dialogue: 0,2:02:49.90,2:02:52.70,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}本現在和妻子有一個大果園自給自足
Dialogue: 0,2:02:52.80,2:02:55.10,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}他們保存了很多種子
Dialogue: 0,2:02:59.50,2:03:01.60,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}邁克爾·巴里 幾次去聯繫政府
Dialogue: 0,2:03:01.70,2:03:03.80,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}看看是否有人願意採訪他
Dialogue: 0,2:03:03.90,2:03:05.80,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}去瞭解他對金融系統的看法
Dialogue: 0,2:03:05.90,2:03:07.40,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}為什麼只有他提前預測到了金融危機
Dialogue: 0,2:03:07.50,2:03:09.00,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}但從沒有人回過他電話
Dialogue: 0,2:03:09.10,2:03:11.20,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}可是他本人被審訊過4次
Dialogue: 0,2:03:11.30,2:03:14.00,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}被聯邦調查局查帳
Dialogue: 0,2:03:16.50,2:03:18.60,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}他現在唯一在做的小型投資
Dialogue: 0,2:03:18.70,2:03:21.00,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}只關注一種商品：
Dialogue: 0,2:03:21.10,2:03:23.90,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}淡水
Dialogue: 0,2:03:28.50,2:03:31.60,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}2015年開始 很多的大銀行發售十億規模的
Dialogue: 0,2:03:31.70,2:03:34.80,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}"定制分級機會投資"
Dialogue: 0,2:03:34.90,2:03:37.20,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}據彭博新聞的分析
Dialogue: 0,2:03:37.30,2:03:39.90,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}這就是CDO改了個名字
Dialogue: 0,2:03:57.50,2:03:59.50,單行字幕,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fn黑體\fs11\fscy110}根據邁克爾·路易斯同名書籍改編
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.95,0:01:23.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiya, Frank. How are the wife and kids?\N{\rCHT}嘿 弗蘭克 老婆孩子還好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.37,0:01:24.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, for you, I'm considering\N{\rCHT}你考慮過
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.66,0:01:28.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,treasury bonds and utility stocks. Smoke?\N{\rCHT}買國庫券或事業公司股票嗎 抽煙嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.46,0:01:30.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In the late '70s, banking wasn't a job\N{\rCHT}在70年代後期 銀行業並不是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.63,0:01:33.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,you went into to make large sums of money.\N{\rCHT}賺大錢的行業
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.05,0:01:35.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a fucking snooze.\N{\rCHT}絕對廢柴行業
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.72,0:01:40.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Filled with losers. Like selling insurance or\N{\rCHT}到處是窮鬼 都是來賣保險
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.47,0:01:41.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,accounfing.\N{\rCHT}做帳的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.89,0:01:43.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And if banking was boring,\N{\rCHT}如果銀行業廢柴的話
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.14,0:01:45.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,then the bond department at the bank was straight-up comatose.\N{\rCHT}證券部門就是植物人呆的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.64,0:01:48.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We all know about bonds.\N{\rCHT}大夥都知道證券是怎麼回事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.10,0:01:50.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You give them to your snot-nosed kid when he turns 15.\N{\rCHT}把證券當禮物送給你的15歲小屁孩
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.27,0:01:52.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe when he's 30 he makes a hundred bucks.\N{\rCHT}到他30了 能拿到一百來塊錢
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.36,0:01:53.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Boring.\N{\rCHT}無聊之極
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.73,0:01:56.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That is, until Lewis Ranieri came on the scene at Salomon Brothers.\N{\rCHT}千呼萬喚 所羅門兄弟公司的路易斯·拉涅裡駕臨
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.62,0:02:04.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You might not know who he is, but he changed your life\N{\rCHT}這名不經傳的人物 對你的影響…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.91,0:02:08.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,more than Michael Jordan, the iPod and YouTube put together.\N{\rCHT}比起邁克爾·喬丹 iPod YouTube視頻網站加起來還要大
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.54,0:02:12.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, gentlemen! Let's get some money in here!\N{\rCHT}好了 先生們 咱們一起發財吧 怎麼樣？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.38,0:02:15.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make some money! What do you say?\N{\rCHT}一起發財吧 怎麼樣？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.97,0:02:17.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, Lewis didn't know it yet,\N{\rCHT}可能當時路易斯還不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.88,0:02:19.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but he had already changed banking forever\N{\rCHT}但其實他已經改變了歷史
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.89,0:02:21.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,with one simple idea.\N{\rCHT}就用最簡單的這個點子
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.89,0:02:26.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The mortgage-backed security. Or private-label MBS.\N{\rCHT}房貸證券 或者私營房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.39,0:02:29.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got your average person's mortgage.\N{\rCHT}你們都背著普通的房貸
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.31,0:02:30.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fixed rate, 30 years.\N{\rCHT}固定利率 30年還清
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:34.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Boring, safe, small payoff, right? But,\N{\rCHT}簡單 安全 小筆錢償還 對吧？但是…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.44,0:02:38.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,when you have thousands of them all bundled together,\N{\rCHT}如果你把上千個房貸打包起來
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.24,0:02:41.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,suddenly the yield goes up but the risk is still small because,\N{\rCHT}忽然回報率上升了 但風險還很小 因為
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.87,0:02:42.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,well, they're mortgages!\N{\rCHT}它們是房貸
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.91,0:02:44.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And who the hell doesn't pay their mortgage?\N{\rCHT}哪個神經病不還房貸呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.41,0:02:46.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly is the credit rating on this bond?\N{\rCHT}這種證券評級怎麼樣？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.87,0:02:49.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This bond, gentlemen, is AAA-rated.\N{\rCHT}證券評級… 是AAA級別
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:52.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is exactly what the Michigan state pension fund has been looking for.\N{\rCHT}這就是我們密西根州養老基金一直找的啊
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:54.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll buy $20 million.\N{\rCHT}我買兩千萬
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:57.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, come on, live a little. - $25 million.\N{\rCHT}- 別掃興啊 放開點 - 兩千五百萬
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.01,0:03:00.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The money came raining down,\N{\rCHT}錢就像下雨一樣來了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.05,0:03:02.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and for the first time,\N{\rCHT}起初
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.64,0:03:05.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the banker went from the country club to the strip club.\N{\rCHT}銀行家破例從鄉村具樂部跑到了脫衣舞夜總會
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.06,0:03:11.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty soon, stocks and savings were almost inconsequential.\N{\rCHT}很快 股票和存款都沒人考慮了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.44,0:03:13.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They were doing $50, $100, $200 billion\N{\rCHT}每年大夥都買賣5百億 1千億 2千億的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.69,0:03:17.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in mortgage bonds and dozens of other securities a year.\N{\rCHT}房貸證券 還有幾十種其他證券
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.95,0:03:28.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And America barely noticed as its number one industry\N{\rCHT}美國人都沒注意到金融行業已經
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.33,0:03:30.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,became boring old banking.\N{\rCHT}成為領頭羊
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.08,0:03:37.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then one day, almost 30 years later, in 2008,\N{\rCHT}然後三十年後 08年的一天
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.80,0:03:40.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,it all came crashing down.\N{\rCHT}一切轟然倒塌
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:46.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,March. Bear Stearns was in a death spiral\N{\rCHT}三月 貝爾斯登公司陷入泥潭
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.51,0:03:47.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Fed brokered its sale.\N{\rCHT}美聯儲幫忙救急
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.02,0:03:51.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been called the worst financial crisis in modern times.\N{\rCHT}現代歷史上最嚴重的經濟危機
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.39,0:03:55.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly the largest financial disaster in decades in this country,\N{\rCHT}幾十年以來最大的金融海嘯
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.73,0:03:58.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and perhaps the end of an era in American business.\N{\rCHT}很可能是整個時代最糟的情況了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.86,0:04:01.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, Lewis Ranieri's mortgage-backed security\N{\rCHT}到最後 路易斯·拉涅裡的房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.20,0:04:04.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,mutated into a monstrosity that collapsed the whole world economy.\N{\rCHT}異變成了摧毀全球經濟的怪物
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.20,0:04:07.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And none of the experts or leaders or talking heads\N{\rCHT}專家 領導人或者電視上的權威
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.37,0:04:08.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,had a clue it was coming.\N{\rCHT}都沒能預料到
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.16,0:04:13.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing most of you still don't really know what happened.\N{\rCHT}我估計你們也沒弄明白發生了什麼事情
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.62,0:04:16.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you got a soundbite you repeat so you don't sound dumb, but come on.\N{\rCHT}是啊 大家也就是人云亦云一下…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.50,0:04:19.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Our financial institutions are strong.\N{\rCHT}我們的金融機構是強有力的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.17,0:04:22.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But there were some who saw it coming.\N{\rCHT}不過確實有人預料到這事兒發生
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.68,0:04:24.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,While the whole world was having a big old party,\N{\rCHT}整個世界都在虛假狂歡
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.84,0:04:28.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,a few outsiders and weirdos saw what no one else could.\N{\rCHT}少數的局外人和怪才卻獨具慧眼
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.18,0:04:31.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Not me. I'm not a weirdo. I'm pretty fucking cool.\N{\rCHT}不是我 我才不怪呢 我的酷事兒
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.85,0:04:33.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But we'll meet again later.\N{\rCHT}等會再跟你說
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.35,0:04:37.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,These outsiders saw the giant lie at the heart of the economy.\N{\rCHT}這些人發現了經濟中心的彌天大謊
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.19,0:04:38.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And they saw it by doing something\N{\rCHT}方法不難
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.69,0:04:41.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the rest of the suckers never thought to do.\N{\rCHT}只是隨大流的人永遠不會去做：
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:43.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They looked.\N{\rCHT}親自去瞭解
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.54,0:04:58.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,During the 1930s,\N{\rCHT}貫穿整個20世紀30年代…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.50,0:05:05.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the housing market collapsed nationwide\N{\rCHT}房產市場… 全國性的崩潰
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.55,0:05:08.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,by roughly 80%.\N{\rCHT}大概80%都完了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.76,0:05:13.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, half of all mortgage debt was in default.\N{\rCHT}其中有一半的房貸都違約了
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.98,0:05:16.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And, I mean, there were very\N{\rCHT}而且 我是說 那時候有…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.77,0:05:21.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,specific identifiers, extremely recognizable.\N{\rCHT}明確的鑒別指標 相當好認
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.19,0:05:25.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, for instance,\N{\rCHT}稍等 比方說
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:28.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,one of the hallmarks of mania\N{\rCHT}狂熱的標誌之一
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.91,0:05:32.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,is the rapid rise in complexity and the rates of fraud.\N{\rCHT}是快速上升的複雜性和欺詐性的利率
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.49,0:05:35.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And did you know that they're going up?\N{\rCHT}居然在上升
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.43,0:05:59.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been more comfortable alone.\N{\rCHT}我這人習慣自己呆著
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:11.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe maybe it's because of my glass eye.\N{\rCHT}可能是我玻璃假眼的原因吧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:16.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost the eye in a childhood illness.\N{\rCHT}小時候得過病 眼睛壞了一邊
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.92,0:06:23.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It separates me from people.\N{\rCHT}我就不再合群了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:29.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And did you know that they are going\N{\rCHT}利率居然在
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.76,0:06:30.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Up?\N{\rCHT}上升
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.97,0:06:34.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The highest fraud rates since the 1930s.\N{\rCHT}欺詐性的利率達到了30年代最高點
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.56,0:06:36.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, it's okay. It's okay.\N{\rCHT}嘿 嘿 沒事的 沒事的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:38.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't know that.\N{\rCHT}我還真不瞭解
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.15,0:06:47.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In 1933, the fourth year of the Great Depression.\N{\rCHT}我是說1933年大蕭條的第四年
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.49,0:06:49.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's wash it off and put it back in.\N{\rCHT}把傷口洗乾淨 然後回到賽場
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.24,0:06:51.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You were playing so great, son.\N{\rCHT}你表現的一直很好 孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.32,0:06:53.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I even heard the coach say it.\N{\rCHT}教練都表揚你了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.49,0:06:56.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we just go home?\N{\rCHT}我想回家
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.83,0:07:01.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Most social interactions are awkward for me and for the person.\N{\rCHT}所有社交活動 都會讓我和對方不舒服
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:04.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when I try to compliment someone,\N{\rCHT}哪怕我想誇誇別人
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.67,0:07:06.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,it comes out wrong.\N{\rCHT}也詞不達意
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.96,0:07:10.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a very nice haircut. Did you do it yourself?\N{\rCHT}你頭型不錯啊 你自己理的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.47,0:07:12.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\N{\rCHT}你說啥？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:15.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No, I...\N{\rCHT}不是我… 嗯…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:25.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I'm just...\N{\rCHT}抱歉 別往心裡去
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.41,0:07:32.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going on and on.\N{\rCHT}我老是這樣
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.70,0:07:34.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife told me I need to share more.\N{\rCHT}我老婆讓我多和別人交流
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.37,0:07:38.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That seems healthy. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 聽起來挺好的建議 - 對
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.01,0:07:52.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So do I get the job?\N{\rCHT}那我就在這兒幹了？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.51,0:07:54.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I really think I could help your fund.\N{\rCHT}我覺得我能幫你籌款
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.22,0:07:57.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}好啊
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.68,0:07:59.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure. Go on.\N{\rCHT}那太好了 去吧
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:05.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're... - David. Great.\N{\rCHT}- 你叫？ - 大衛 太棒了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:07.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll go find a desk.\N{\rCHT}那我去找個位子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:09.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything you want me to work on for start...\N{\rCHT}有什麼我能上手幫到你的工作嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.91,0:08:14.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}有
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.36,0:08:16.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You could let me know later. I could come back.\N{\rCHT}你回頭找我也行
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.79,0:08:23.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think it was strange when\N{\rCHT}你覺得當時奇怪嗎…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:25.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the tech bubble burst in 2001\N{\rCHT}2001年互聯網泡沫破裂的時候…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.00,0:08:28.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the housing market in San Jose,\N{\rCHT}矽谷的房價…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.88,0:08:31.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the tech capital of the world,\N{\rCHT}世界科技中心的房價…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.59,0:08:34.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Went up?\N{\rCHT}卻逆勢上漲…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.43,0:08:36.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Wasn't that strange? - No.\N{\rCHT}- 難道不奇怪 - 不
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.55,0:08:39.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's housing. Housing is always stable.\N{\rCHT}這是房產… 房產一直很穩定
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.26,0:08:40.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Low risk. It's solid.\N{\rCHT}風險也低 很穩定
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.39,0:08:42.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the idea, yeah.\N{\rCHT}我說的就是這點很奇怪
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.43,0:08:44.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to get me\N{\rCHT}我要你幫我找到…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.27,0:08:47.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the top 20 selling mortgage bonds.\N{\rCHT}賣的最火的20個房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.56,0:08:50.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So you want to know what the top 20 selling mortgage bonds are?\N{\rCHT}你想要知道最火的20家是哪些？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.48,0:08:54.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, I want to know what mortgages are in each one.\N{\rCHT}不 不 不 我要知道每一家的所有房貸資料
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.24,0:08:59.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, aren't those mortgages made up of...\N{\rCHT}好吧 這些房貸不是…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:00.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, aren't those bonds made up\N{\rCHT}稍等 這些房貸證券不是
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.83,0:09:02.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,of thousands and thousands of mortgages?\N{\rCHT}成千上萬個房貸組成的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:04.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}是啊
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:09.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Right away, Dr. Burry.\N{\rCHT}我這就去辦 巴里博士
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.02,0:09:33.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a nice guy all day long.\N{\rCHT}我人不錯 整天樂呵呵的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.44,0:09:36.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask anyone, I'm a pleasure to work with.\N{\rCHT}你去問別人 大夥都願意和我相處
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.03,0:09:42.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But the second my son screws up, I am...\N{\rCHT}可是我兒子只要辦砸了事兒 我…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.04,0:09:45.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...yelling at him just like my dad did to me.\N{\rCHT}我就對他吼 就像我爸對我一樣…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:51.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear the words that are coming out of my mouth and...\N{\rCHT}感覺自己控制不住自己的嘴…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:54.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late! No cabs.\N{\rCHT}抱歉我遲到了 沒計程車
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.63,0:09:58.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, get this.\N{\rCHT}你們評評理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.97,0:10:01.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I met with this retail banker yesterday.\N{\rCHT}昨天我和私人銀行的一個人聊
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.72,0:10:04.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm supposed to be getting him to invest in a fund,\N{\rCHT}本來是讓他投資我的基金
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.22,0:10:05.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but instead\N{\rCHT}結果
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.64,0:10:08.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I start grilling him about overdraft penalties\N{\rCHT}我開始和他較真有關透支的問題
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.60,0:10:11.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and how his bank will let a customer write 10-12 checks\N{\rCHT}他的銀行讓客戶寫了十幾個支票
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.69,0:10:12.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,before they tell them they're overdrawn.\N{\rCHT}還不告訴客戶已經透支了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.03,0:10:16.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And this creep is making billions off screwing over people this way.\N{\rCHT}這個小人用這種卑鄙的方式賺了十億多
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.03,0:10:18.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm getting madder and madder.\N{\rCHT}我越來越壓不住火
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:22.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I ask him, I look him in the face and I say,\N{\rCHT}我問他 瞪著他 質問他
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.37,0:10:24.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"How can you sleep at night\N{\rCHT}你晚上睡得著覺嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.70,0:10:28.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"knowing that you are ripping off working people?"\N{\rCHT}不怕鬼叫門嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.25,0:10:29.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And you know what he did? He left.\N{\rCHT}你猜怎麼著… 他扭頭走了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.04,0:10:32.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He just walks out of the lunch, doesn't say a word.\N{\rCHT}也不理我 直接走人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.84,0:10:33.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What the fuck is that?\N{\rCHT}這他媽是什麼玩意？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.92,0:10:36.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's fucked up in that scenario? Am I?\N{\rCHT}好像我惹著他了 錯在我？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.34,0:10:38.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Or is this douchebag, who leaves me hanging?\N{\rCHT}還是這個人渣？把我晾在那兒
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.88,0:10:40.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he the fucked up one?\N{\rCHT}誰更操蛋？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.22,0:10:43.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We have talked about this numerous times.\N{\rCHT}咱們以前說過幾次了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.10,0:10:46.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't come in late and hijack the entire session.\N{\rCHT}你不能遲到了就搶別人的話
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.31,0:10:47.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? I didn't hijack the meeting.\N{\rCHT}你說什麼啊 我沒搶啊
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.85,0:10:50.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Did I hijack the session? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 我搶話了嗎？- 搶了
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.65,0:10:53.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- What do you do? - I'm in commodities.\N{\rCHT}- 你幹啥的？- 我做商品期貨的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:54.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck with that.\N{\rCHT}我等著看你的好戲
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.57,0:10:58.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, I know you suffered a terrible loss.\N{\rCHT}馬克… 我知道你剛失去了親人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.24,0:10:59.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you want to talk about that.\N{\rCHT}你想要聊聊嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.74,0:11:00.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't talk about that.\N{\rCHT}這事兒我不會開口
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.86,0:11:02.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.\N{\rCHT}稍等
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.37,0:11:03.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on...\N{\rCHT}稍等…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:06.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit, I have to take this. Sorry. Sorry.\N{\rCHT}我得接電話了 抱歉 對不起了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.54,0:11:09.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No... I don't care, Porter.\N{\rCHT}伯特 你怎麼做我不管
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.75,0:11:11.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy's whole business is built on ripping people off.\N{\rCHT}這傢伙賺的錢是刮人骨頭來的
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.42,0:11:12.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How long can that last?\N{\rCHT}能撐多久
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.46,0:11:15.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, everybody!\N{\rCHT}大夥再見
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.71,0:11:18.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,95...\N{\rCHT}95…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.63,0:11:20.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's 30 days late... Sixty days late...\N{\rCHT}這個逾期30天 這個60天沒交了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.22,0:11:25.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They pay on time...\N{\rCHT}按時還貸
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.60,0:11:30.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,These FICO scores...\N{\rCHT}這些FICO信用評分…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.94,0:11:38.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Late. And they caught up on their payments...\N{\rCHT}你們這下現原形了…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.03,0:11:40.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Another 30 days late...\N{\rCHT}30天逾期
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:43.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,LTV, 95... LTV, 90... They caught up on their payments...\N{\rCHT}貸款價值比 大概是95 可能是90
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:45.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixty days late? Jesus!\N{\rCHT}60天逾期 天哪
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.58,0:11:47.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,LTV, 110? I've never heard of that!\N{\rCHT}貸款價值比 110 聞所未聞
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:49.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty days late, rate adjusts...\N{\rCHT}30天逾期 利率調整
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:51.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In '07 rate adjusts...\N{\rCHT}07年利率調整
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.46,0:11:52.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In '06 rate adjusts...\N{\rCHT}06年利率調整
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.75,0:11:55.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,95.. 90... Jesus!\N{\rCHT}95 90 天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.75,0:11:58.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't moved all day.\N{\rCHT}他一天都沒動窩了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.46,0:12:00.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He does this every few days.\N{\rCHT}他每隔幾天都這樣一次
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.88,0:12:02.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't spoken to me since he hired me.\N{\rCHT}他雇了我以後就沒再理過我
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.63,0:12:04.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the LTV's at... High-risk,\N{\rCHT}貸款價值比 處於高風險
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:06.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,interest-only... I never heard of that mortgage history,\N{\rCHT}只還利息 我從來沒有聽說過房貸歷史有過
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.47,0:12:09.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I never heard of that... How?\N{\rCHT}我從未聽說過 怎麼啦
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.31,0:12:10.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael, how are you, guy?\N{\rCHT}邁克爾 你還好嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:13.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence, I found something really interesting.\N{\rCHT}勞倫斯 我找到了有意思的東西
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.81,0:12:15.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, Michael. Whenever you find something interesting,\N{\rCHT}邁克爾你幹的好 你每次找到有意思的東西
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:17.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,we all tend to make money.\N{\rCHT}我們就能躺著賺錢了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:19.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- What stock are you valuing? - No, no, no, no. No stocks.\N{\rCHT}- 看上哪個股票了 - 不 不 不… 不是股票
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:22.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to short the housing market.\N{\rCHT}我要做空房地產市場
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.49,0:12:26.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? But the housing market is rock solid.\N{\rCHT}是嗎？房地產市場可是堅如磐石
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.66,0:12:28.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Greenspan just said\N{\rCHT}格林斯潘說過
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.16,0:12:30.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,bubbles are regional, defaults are rare.\N{\rCHT}泡沫是局部現象 斷供的很少
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.83,0:12:32.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them I'll be there in a minute.\N{\rCHT}告訴他們我一會就到
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.04,0:12:34.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Say again? - Look, look...\N{\rCHT}- 你再說一遍 - 聽好了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.92,0:12:36.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Greenspan's wrong.\N{\rCHT}格林斯潘說錯了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.84,0:12:40.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you mean to do this, but sometimes you sound very\N{\rCHT}我知道你不是故意的 可你有時候說話
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.34,0:12:42.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,dismissive and superior.\N{\rCHT}太瞧不起人
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.72,0:12:43.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fact. Greenspan's wrong.\N{\rCHT}事情本來就是這樣 格林斯潘錯了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.97,0:12:46.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how else you want me to say...\N{\rCHT}你讓我怎麼說…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:47.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Michael.\N{\rCHT}聽著 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:49.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Metro Capital backed you four years ago\N{\rCHT}四年前你還是個博士
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.56,0:12:51.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,when you were a doctor with a\N{\rCHT}只有個破網站和一點繼承來的錢
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.43,0:12:53.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,dinky webpage and some inheritance money.\N{\rCHT}我們全球國際資本就力挺你了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.85,0:12:54.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We've all done very well.\N{\rCHT}一直以來業績也不錯…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.94,0:12:56.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you just stick with stocks?\N{\rCHT}你繼續做股票…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.15,0:12:58.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. You know me. I, I, I...\N{\rCHT}你瞭解我這個人 我 我
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.36,0:13:02.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I look for value wherever it can be found.\N{\rCHT}我的風格就是找能賺錢的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.19,0:13:03.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fact is\N{\rCHT}情況就是
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.36,0:13:06.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that these mortgage-backed securities are filled\N{\rCHT}這些房貸證券…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:10.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,with extremely risky subprime adjustable-rate loans.\N{\rCHT}裡面有相當高風險的可調利率房貸
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.20,0:13:12.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And when the majority of the adjustable rates\N{\rCHT}等這部分到07年左右
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.79,0:13:15.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,kick in, in '07,\N{\rCHT}開始發作
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.21,0:13:16.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,they will begin to fail.\N{\rCHT}市場就會衰退
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:19.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And if they fail above 15%, the whole bond is worthless.\N{\rCHT}如果最終能占到15%以上 整個房貸證券市場就毫無價值
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.88,0:13:22.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael, just take a beat.\N{\rCHT}邁克爾 停下來再想想
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.13,0:13:23.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll talk about this later, okay?\N{\rCHT}回頭我再找你聊 好嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.42,0:13:26.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence, please, don't patronize me. Listen...\N{\rCHT}勞倫斯 別給我來這套 如果
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.55,0:13:28.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mortgage-backed securities.\N{\rCHT}房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.09,0:13:30.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- It, it, it... - Subprime loans. Tranches.\N{\rCHT}- 這 這 - 次級貸 份額…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:33.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty confusing, right?\N{\rCHT}名詞讓人頭疼是吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.14,0:13:35.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it make you feel bored? Or stupid?\N{\rCHT}是不是讓你覺得智商特別低
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.85,0:13:38.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's supposed to.\N{\rCHT}這就是它的本意
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.23,0:13:39.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wall Street loves to use confusing terms\N{\rCHT}華爾街特別愛用玄乎的詞兒
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.90,0:13:42.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,to make you think only they can do what they do.\N{\rCHT}讓你覺得只有他們才能做的來
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.90,0:13:44.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, even better,\N{\rCHT}或者你撒手不管
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.19,0:13:46.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,for you to just leave them the fuck alone.\N{\rCHT}他們就更高興了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.66,0:13:49.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So here's Margot Robbie in a bubble bath to explain.\N{\rCHT}我們讓演員瑪格在泡泡浴裡解釋給你聽
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:52.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, Lewis Ranieri's mortgage bonds\N{\rCHT}大概意思就是 路易斯的房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.95,0:13:55.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,were amazingly profitable for the big banks.\N{\rCHT}讓大銀行瘋狂賺錢
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.33,0:13:59.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They made billions and billions on their 2% fee\N{\rCHT}他們從2%的買賣提成中
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.38,0:14:01.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,they got for selling each of these bonds.\N{\rCHT}賺了幾十億
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:05.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But then they started running out of mortgages to put in them.\N{\rCHT}但慢慢房貸不夠用來組成證券了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.17,0:14:07.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, there are only so many homes\N{\rCHT}畢竟 房子和能買房的人
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.93,0:14:11.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and so many people with good enough jobs to buy them, right?\N{\rCHT}都是有數兒的 對吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.76,0:14:16.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So the banks started filling these bonds with riskier and riskier mortgages.\N{\rCHT}銀行就開始把風險越來越高的房貸做成證券
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.18,0:14:17.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Benter.\N{\rCHT}謝了 本特
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:21.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That way they can keep that profit machine churning, right?\N{\rCHT}這樣的話 機器就能一直轉著了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.07,0:14:26.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, these risky mortgages are called subprime.\N{\rCHT}對了 這些高風險的房貸 就叫:次級貸
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.53,0:14:28.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So whenever you hear "subprime", think\N{\rCHT}下回 聽到次級貸這個詞 你就想：
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.99,0:14:30.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"shit".\N{\rCHT}狗屎貸
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.53,0:14:34.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Our friend Michael Burry found out that these mortgage bonds\N{\rCHT}邁克爾老兄發現… 這些房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.16,0:14:37.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that were supposedly 65% AAA\N{\rCHT}本來應該至少有65%的3A評級
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.46,0:14:40.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,were actually just mostly full of shit.\N{\rCHT}但其實裡面就是一坨屎
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.79,0:14:43.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So now he's going to "short" the bonds.\N{\rCHT}所以他要做空房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.63,0:14:45.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means to "bet against".\N{\rCHT}也就是 賭房產市場跌
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.46,0:14:47.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?\N{\rCHT}懂了吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.22,0:14:49.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.\N{\rCHT}太好了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.55,0:14:53.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now fuck off.\N{\rCHT}別看姐洗澡了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.93,0:14:56.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a matter of time before someone else sees this investment.\N{\rCHT}很快人們就會發現這個機會的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.35,0:14:58.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to act now!\N{\rCHT}咱們得快點幹
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.14,0:15:00.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know the bonds are worthless?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼就知道這些證券不值錢？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:02.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't they filled with fucking thousands\N{\rCHT}這裡面不是他媽的有上千頁
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.77,0:15:03.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,of pages of mortgages?\N{\rCHT}房貸嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.98,0:15:06.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I read them.\N{\rCHT}我都看了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.32,0:15:08.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You read them? - I read... Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 你都看了？- 我都看了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:11.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No one reads them. Only the lawyers who put them together read them.\N{\rCHT}沒人這麼去讀的 打包房貸的證券律師才不得不看
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.62,0:15:16.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I don't think that they even know what they've made.\N{\rCHT}聽著 我覺得他們也不懂紙裡包的是什麼
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.45,0:15:19.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The housing market is propped up on these\N{\rCHT}有這些垃圾貸款 房地產註定
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.00,0:15:22.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,bad loans, and I'm...\N{\rCHT}火不起來 我…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.75,0:15:24.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a time bomb, and I want to short it.\N{\rCHT}定時炸彈在 我要做空房產市場
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.88,0:15:27.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Through what instrument, Michael?\N{\rCHT}憑藉什麼做空 邁克爾？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.26,0:15:30.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no insurance contracts or options for mortgage bonds.\N{\rCHT}現在還沒有做房貸證券的保險或期權
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:33.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- The bonds are too stable. - Lawrence...\N{\rCHT}- 這證券太穩定沒人做 - 勞倫斯…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.35,0:15:40.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I'm gonna do. I am gonna get a bank\N{\rCHT}我打算這麼幹 我要讓銀行
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:42.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,to make me one.\N{\rCHT}專門為我做一個
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:44.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then\N{\rCHT}然後…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.69,0:15:47.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna buy it.\N{\rCHT}我再買下來
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.03,0:15:50.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want that kind of business.\N{\rCHT}我不做這種買賣
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.65,0:15:53.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Money is not money. That's bad money.\N{\rCHT}這錢不乾淨 是黑心錢
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.99,0:15:56.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Excuse me!\N{\rCHT}嘿 看著點
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.58,0:16:00.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me ask you this. What company treats its customers\N{\rCHT}我問你 什麼公司這麼玩弄客戶
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.58,0:16:03.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that shittily and succeeds?\N{\rCHT}還能做大？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.04,0:16:05.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. Okay, Goldman. You're right.\N{\rCHT}好吧 高盛銀行 隨便你
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.96,0:16:07.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark Baum had built his career\N{\rCHT}馬克之所以成功
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:09.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,on never assuming anyone or any company\N{\rCHT}是因為他從不為任何
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.51,0:16:11.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,was legit without proving it.\N{\rCHT}不合法的生意做擔保
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.26,0:16:12.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,When he was a kid he excelled at studying\N{\rCHT}他小的時候在
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.84,0:16:14.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the Talmud in Yeshiva. Whatever.\N{\rCHT}猶太學院學法典時 不管怎樣
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:16.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But one day his rabbi told his mom why.\N{\rCHT}有天他老師對他媽說
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:21.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Paul is a fine boy, and Mark is an excellent student\N{\rCHT}保羅不錯 馬克學習法典
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.18,0:16:23.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,of the Torah and the Talmud.\N{\rCHT}也成績優異
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:25.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's the problem, rabbi?\N{\rCHT}那還有什麼問題 老師？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.90,0:16:29.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the reason Mark is studying so hard.\N{\rCHT}是因為馬克努力學習的理由
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:33.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He's looking for inconsistencies in the word of God!\N{\rCHT}他是想要找到上帝福音中的矛盾之處
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.82,0:16:37.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So has he found any?\N{\rCHT}那他找到了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.08,0:16:42.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Later, Baum started his own fund on Wall Street.\N{\rCHT}以後 馬克就在華爾街成立了自己的基金
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.41,0:16:43.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He had an amazing nose for bullshit.\N{\rCHT}他對屁話可是有狗一樣嗅覺
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.92,0:16:45.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And he wasn't afraid to let anyone know when and where\N{\rCHT}哪裡有蠢蛋在胡說 他都會給大夥指出來何時何地
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.00,0:16:48.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the bull had gone number two.\N{\rCHT}牛市變了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.71,0:16:50.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But then a tragedy happened to Mark,\N{\rCHT}後來馬克經歷了不幸
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.42,0:16:51.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and it turned his world view dark\N{\rCHT}整個世界觀都陰暗了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.97,0:16:54.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and ready to believe the whole system was a lie.\N{\rCHT}開始覺得整個金融系統都是騙局
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.38,0:16:55.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.\N{\rCHT}稍等
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.01,0:16:58.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Cynthia. I'll be in the office in 20 minutes.\N{\rCHT}辛西婭找我 我20分鐘到辦公室
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.76,0:17:00.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, honey.\N{\rCHT}親愛的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.43,0:17:06.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The therapist called. You did it again.\N{\rCHT}諮詢師打電話給我 你怎麼又這樣了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.52,0:17:09.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no cabs. What was I supposed to do?\N{\rCHT}沒計程車有什麼辦法
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.36,0:17:11.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I worry about you, Mark.\N{\rCHT}我很擔心你的狀態
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:12.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,At least I went.\N{\rCHT}我至少去報到了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.74,0:17:17.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're running around like you have to right every wrong in the world. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 你這樣 像是想把全世界都理順了 - 好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.74,0:17:18.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so angry.\N{\rCHT}一直氣鼓鼓的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.99,0:17:20.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. You know what?\N{\rCHT}你說的對
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.49,0:17:23.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a mean guy and I'm pissed off.\N{\rCHT}我就是心眼小 現在還生氣了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.50,0:17:25.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But it is a shit storm out here, sweetie.\N{\rCHT}可我這個圈子
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.50,0:17:28.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no idea the kind of crap people are pulling.\N{\rCHT}留下爛攤子 擦屁股走人的太多
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.88,0:17:31.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And everyone's walking around like they're in a goddamn Enya video.\N{\rCHT}大夥還臉上自帶拍恩雅MTV的表情
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.26,0:17:34.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all getting screwed, you know.\N{\rCHT}以後他們全被玩完
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.80,0:17:37.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what they care about? They care about the ballgame.\N{\rCHT}他們關心什麼？關心球賽
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:40.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Or they care about what actress just went into rehab.\N{\rCHT}關心哪個女演員去戒毒了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.43,0:17:42.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you should try medication.\N{\rCHT}你得讓醫生給你開點藥了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:45.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. We agreed. If it interfered with work.\N{\rCHT}不行 咱倆商量過 影響工作的藥不能吃
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.81,0:17:47.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You hate Wall Street. Maybe it's time to quit.\N{\rCHT}你這麼恨華爾街 消消氣就別幹了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.15,0:17:50.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I love my job. - You hate your job.\N{\rCHT}- 我愛這一行 - 你恨這一行
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.19,0:17:52.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I love my job. - You're miserable.\N{\rCHT}- 我愛這一行 - 你都這麼鬱悶了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.32,0:17:54.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I love my job. I love my job, honey.\N{\rCHT}我愛我的工作 真的 親愛的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.28,0:17:56.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark...\N{\rCHT}馬克
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.78,0:18:00.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I am sad every day about what happened.\N{\rCHT}想起發生的事情 我每天也心裡不舒服
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.95,0:18:04.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you must feel the same, but you never show it.\N{\rCHT}你肯定也不好受 可你從來不表現出來
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.54,0:18:13.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how close you were to your brother.\N{\rCHT}我知道你們兄弟倆關係很好
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.42,0:18:17.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Paul.\N{\rCHT}保羅
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:20.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd you go, Paul?\N{\rCHT}你去哪兒了 保羅？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.43,0:18:26.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Paul!\N{\rCHT}保羅
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.36,0:18:35.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Every day I think you're gonna talk about it, but you never do.\N{\rCHT}每天我都覺得你想開口聊聊 可你總是忍著
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.99,0:18:42.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you at least think about the idea of making a change?\N{\rCHT}你能試著做一點改變嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.83,0:18:45.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. Fine. Honey, you know what? I will consider it.\N{\rCHT}好吧 親愛的 我會認真考慮的…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.75,0:18:49.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But, honestly, Cynthia. I'm okay. I really am.\N{\rCHT}不過我真的沒事兒 辛西婭 放心
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.21,0:18:51.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, hey! No, no.\N{\rCHT}嘿 嘿 嘿 不 不
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.25,0:18:54.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My cab. That's my cab. That's my cab. That is my cab.\N{\rCHT}這是我搶來的出租 我的出租 我的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.71,0:18:56.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Schmuck. Fuck you. - Fuck you.\N{\rCHT}- 蠢貨 滾蛋 - 滾蛋
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.38,0:18:58.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fuck you. - Fuck you.\N{\rCHT}- 你滾蛋 - 去死
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.05,0:19:00.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call you later.\N{\rCHT}我等會再打給你
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.93,0:19:12.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to buy swaps on mortgage bonds.\N{\rCHT}我要買… 房貸證券的互換
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.11,0:19:14.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A credit default swap that will pay off\N{\rCHT}這種信用違約互換 來擔保
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.48,0:19:17.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,if the underlying bond fails.\N{\rCHT}房貸證券不能兌換的情況
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:20.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to bet against the housing market?\N{\rCHT}- 你想要賭房價跌？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.41,0:19:22.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes. - Why?\N{\rCHT}- 是的 - 為什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.45,0:19:23.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Those bonds only fail\N{\rCHT}除非
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.70,0:19:26.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,if millions of Americans don't pay their mortgages.\N{\rCHT}有上百萬的美國人房貸斷供才有可能
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.24,0:19:28.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's never happened in history.\N{\rCHT}歷史上從來沒有過這種事
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.75,0:19:31.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll excuse me, Dr. Burry, it seems like a foolish investment.\N{\rCHT}恕我直言 巴里博士 我覺得您投資不太明智
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.75,0:19:36.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, based on prevailing sentiment of the market and banks in popular culture,\N{\rCHT}按照市場和銀行的主流預期和大眾看法
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.71,0:19:39.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,yes, it's a foolish investment. But...\N{\rCHT}我這麼做是不明智 但是
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.09,0:19:41.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's wrong.\N{\rCHT}所有人都錯了…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.18,0:19:44.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good one.\N{\rCHT}不錯的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.02,0:19:48.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Wall Street, Dr. Burry.\N{\rCHT}巴里博士 華爾街是賺錢的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.77,0:19:50.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If you offer us free money, we are going to take it.\N{\rCHT}有免費的錢 我們自然來者不拒
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.81,0:19:55.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My one concern is that when the bonds fail,\N{\rCHT}我唯一的顧慮是 萬一房貸市場垮了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.57,0:20:00.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be certain of payment\N{\rCHT}我要確保你們賠付…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.20,0:20:02.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in case of solvency issues with your bank.\N{\rCHT}你們萬一償還能力不夠 我的錢怎麼辦
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.95,0:20:06.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, are you for real?\N{\rCHT}您不是在說笑吧
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.41,0:20:08.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna bet against the housing market\N{\rCHT}你想要賭房地產崩潰
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.12,0:20:09.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're worried we won't pay you?\N{\rCHT}還擔心我們不能賠付你？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.54,0:20:11.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's correct.\N{\rCHT}是的 就是這意思
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.47,0:20:24.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...unless the market crashes.\N{\rCHT}我覺得我們能做成這筆買賣
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:26.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The market on housing's never gonna crash\N{\rCHT}房貸證券不可能出事的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.76,0:20:29.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,because it's so solid right now.\N{\rCHT}現在市場還非常穩固
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.64,0:20:32.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, who doesn't pay their mortgages?\N{\rCHT}那我們繼續和他談
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.61,0:20:40.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Burry,\N{\rCHT}巴里博士
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.74,0:20:43.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,we could work out a pay-as-we-go structure\N{\rCHT}我們會制定一個
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.15,0:20:45.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that would pay out if the bonds fail.\N{\rCHT}現收現付的賠付辦法
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.24,0:20:46.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But it would also apply to your payments\N{\rCHT}這也意味著 您的付款方面
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:48.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,if the value of the mortgage bond goes up.\N{\rCHT}如果證券勢頭上漲
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.87,0:20:51.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd have to pay us monthly premiums.\N{\rCHT}你要每個月付給我們保險費用
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.66,0:20:54.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that acceptable, Dr. Burry?\N{\rCHT}您能同意這樣的條款嗎 巴里博士？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.83,0:20:58.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Yes.\N{\rCHT}很好 沒問題
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.17,0:21:04.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I have prospectuses on six mortgage-backed securities I want to short.\N{\rCHT}我這裡有招股說明書想給你看6個房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.01,0:21:10.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Majority of the mortgages...\N{\rCHT}這些多數是審批過的房貸
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.07,0:21:24.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see us losing any money on these at all.\N{\rCHT}這交易絕對不會虧錢
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.08,0:21:40.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Burry, these should be fine.\N{\rCHT}巴里博士 這些應該沒問題
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.84,0:21:42.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We're prepared to sell you $5 million\N{\rCHT}好 我們能賣給你5百萬的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.84,0:21:44.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in credit default swaps on these mortgage bonds.\N{\rCHT}房貸證券的信用違約互換
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.93,0:21:47.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we make it $100 million?\N{\rCHT}能不能賣給我一億？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.22,0:21:52.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely, we can make it $100 million.\N{\rCHT}那也沒問題 我們能準備好一億
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.18,0:21:57.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be in touch, send some paperwork over.\N{\rCHT}我們會聯繫你 把文書發給你
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.90,0:22:03.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I like these cups. Can I take one for my son?\N{\rCHT}我挺喜歡這杯子的 想給我兒子帶一個
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.57,0:22:05.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Have... Yes. Yes.\N{\rCHT}拿走吧 好的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.40,0:22:06.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.99,0:22:08.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Have two.\N{\rCHT}拿走兩個也行
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.34,0:22:31.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any way to do $200 million?\N{\rCHT}有可能賣給我2億嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.81,0:22:35.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, we can. But are you sure?\N{\rCHT}我們是可以… 但你得想清楚了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.35,0:22:39.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely. Absolutely, we can do that.\N{\rCHT}當然… 我們當然可以
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.24,0:22:56.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We do different projects. We do gardening.\N{\rCHT}我們有各種服務 比如園藝等…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:22:58.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The bonds I'd like to bet against.\N{\rCHT}有關證券 我想…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.17,0:23:01.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not bad seeing yourself on the big screen.\N{\rCHT}別人說你走極端也沒什麼不好的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.75,0:23:02.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's very cool.\N{\rCHT}這樣活著才酷
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.80,0:23:07.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I ordered the 24-ounce T-bone, which was choice.\N{\rCHT}好比我本來想買24盎司的T骨牛排 結果
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.55,0:23:09.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I went for volume... - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 卻拿到了8盎司的碎肉 - 嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.09,0:23:10.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...rather than prime.\N{\rCHT}我想買頂級的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.80,0:23:13.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I went for subprime, and the gist was...\N{\rCHT}卻買了次級的 主要是
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.37,0:23:37.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Randall! What's with the Dom?\N{\rCHT}蘭達爾 你現在就這麼逍遙？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.16,0:23:39.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bonuses aren't for three months.\N{\rCHT}三個月後才發獎金呢
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.12,0:23:43.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We just sold $200 million in credit swaps for mortgage bonds.\N{\rCHT}我們剛賣了2億的房貸證券的信用違約互換
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.17,0:23:45.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Some fund manager from California.\N{\rCHT}一些加利福尼亞冒出來基金經理
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.46,0:23:46.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fucking crazy, right?\N{\rCHT}真是瘋子 對吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.88,0:23:47.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A whole new way to make money, Doug.\N{\rCHT}老夥計 咱們就得賺傻子的錢
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.05,0:23:50.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait. I didn't know there were swaps on mortgages.\N{\rCHT}有這種違約互換？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.38,0:23:52.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There are now. We made it for him.\N{\rCHT}現在就有了 陪他玩兒麼
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:54.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He must have gone off his Zoloft or something.\N{\rCHT}他腦袋估計塞屁股裡去了吧
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.80,0:23:56.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.\N{\rCHT}我不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.22,0:23:58.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Want to join? No? - Just a second.\N{\rCHT}- 來一杯嗎 - 稍等
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.23,0:24:00.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Jared.\N{\rCHT}嘿 傑瑞德
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.73,0:24:02.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear about the deal that Randall just did\N{\rCHT}你聽說了蘭達爾和一個基金經理
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.27,0:24:03.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,with some fund manager?\N{\rCHT}做的買賣嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.56,0:24:05.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Randall? Bullshit.\N{\rCHT}蘭達爾？扯蛋吧
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.82,0:24:07.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a foot soldier. I'm sure it's a shit deal.\N{\rCHT}他沒腦子 肯定不是賺錢買賣
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.73,0:24:08.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's for real.\N{\rCHT}是真的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.19,0:24:11.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you we'd meet later.\N{\rCHT}跟你說過咱們會再見面的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.70,0:24:14.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, it's in a place like this which I would never be.\N{\rCHT}不巧是這種鬼地方 我平常不會來的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.20,0:24:16.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I never hung out with these idiots after work, ever.\N{\rCHT}我不和這些傻子下班後散心
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.95,0:24:18.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I had fashion friends.\N{\rCHT}我的朋友比他們有品味
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.16,0:24:22.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, this guy wanted $200 mil in credit default swaps.\N{\rCHT}看起來 確實有人要買2億的信用違約互換
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.58,0:24:24.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Randall made the sale. Can you believe it?\N{\rCHT}蘭達爾也做成了買賣 你敢信？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.42,0:24:26.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody shorted $200 mil on mortgage bonds?\N{\rCHT}有人敢做空2億的房貸證券？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.71,0:24:30.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just with Deutsche. Word is he hit half the town.\N{\rCHT}這還只是在德意志銀行 聽傳聞說 他掃遍了半個城市的銀行
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.01,0:24:32.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How much in total?\N{\rCHT}總共多少？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.22,0:24:33.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$1.3 billion.\N{\rCHT}一共13億
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.01,0:24:37.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What? That's pretty much all of Salon's liquidity.\N{\rCHT}說什麼？賽恩的流動資金也就這麼多啊
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.93,0:24:40.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael, this is highly distressing.\N{\rCHT}邁克爾 你這太過分了吧
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.10,0:24:44.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence, that is not all of our liquidity.\N{\rCHT}勞倫斯… 我們流動資金沒用完
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.23,0:24:45.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm not certain\N{\rCHT}我覺得
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.52,0:24:47.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that you really understand this trade.\N{\rCHT}你沒弄明白這買賣是怎麼回事
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.86,0:24:48.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a certainty.\N{\rCHT}這是必賺的錢
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.98,0:24:52.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mike, I consider myself a mentor to you.\N{\rCHT}邁克爾 我和你平常是師生關係都好說
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.15,0:24:55.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But our company is not comfortable with this investment. Am I being clear?\N{\rCHT}但是這筆投資對公司絕對不合適 我說話你聽明白了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.07,0:24:58.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence, I have full autonomy\N{\rCHT}勞倫斯 對於投資策略
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.41,0:25:01.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,when it comes to investment strategy.\N{\rCHT}我擁有完全自主權
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.41,0:25:02.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You can read our agreement.\N{\rCHT}你去看合同
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.62,0:25:05.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not throw our inception agreement in my face, Michael.\N{\rCHT}別給我扯官腔 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.04,0:25:07.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We had an underlying\N{\rCHT}那是咱倆有
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.21,0:25:09.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,understanding you wouldn't act like a goddamn crazy man.\N{\rCHT}內部共識的基礎上 現在你就像個瘋子一樣
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.88,0:25:11.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not crazy.\N{\rCHT}這不是瘋狂
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.55,0:25:13.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all very logical.\N{\rCHT}這完全是邏輯推理
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.09,0:25:15.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, now we pay up premiums on these swaps\N{\rCHT}那現在我們就每月付費
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.89,0:25:18.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,against the housing market until the mortgages fail?\N{\rCHT}坐等著房地產崩潰？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.72,0:25:20.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, we lose millions\N{\rCHT}也就是說 馬上就損失了幾百萬
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.52,0:25:23.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,until something that's never happened before happens?\N{\rCHT}除非天真塌下來？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.06,0:25:28.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct.\N{\rCHT}說的沒錯
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.60,0:26:02.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Mark Baum.\N{\rCHT}你好 馬克·鮑姆
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.93,0:26:05.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hey, Kathy, you busted me.\N{\rCHT}你好 凱茜 別怪我
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.10,0:26:07.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I had a personal thing this afternoon. - I'm not your babysitter.\N{\rCHT}- 我下午有私事 - 我不是你的保姆
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.23,0:26:09.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If FrontPoint makes money for Morgan Stanley, I'm happy.\N{\rCHT}只要你給咱們摩根士丹利賺錢 我就開心
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.94,0:26:12.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Hey, did I hear you're expecting?\N{\rCHT}好吧… 聽說你要生了？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.32,0:26:13.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're expecting to be expecting.\N{\rCHT}那個 我們是打算要小孩…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.78,0:26:15.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,LVF's are cleaning us out but we're staying positive...\N{\rCHT}雖然我不好解釋得太清楚…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.53,0:26:17.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's exciting!\N{\rCHT}那也是好事兒
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.16,0:26:24.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...lump on my ball. And I go in for a scan.\N{\rCHT}蛋蛋那裡有個腫塊 我去檢查了一下
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.37,0:26:29.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Turns out that I have a very large thing called an epididymis.\N{\rCHT}結果是叫什麼"附睾"腫了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.17,0:26:31.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is a thing that goes around the ball\N{\rCHT}這東西環繞著蛋蛋
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.79,0:26:33.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and is like a sac underneath.\N{\rCHT}好像下面兜著個口袋一樣
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.59,0:26:36.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I have an extremely pronounced epididymis. - I'm riveted...\N{\rCHT}- 我的附睾清晰可見 - 我被吸引
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.63,0:26:38.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm riveted by this. Do you have any pictures?\N{\rCHT}我被這吸引 你有照片嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.76,0:26:42.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost as large as another testicle unto itself.\N{\rCHT}腫得和睾丸一樣大
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.39,0:26:44.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So get this. Cynthia...\N{\rCHT}拿好了 辛西婭…
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.56,0:26:48.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Guys. Cynthia wants me to quit and open a B&B in Vermont.\N{\rCHT}夥計們 辛西婭想讓我辭職不幹了 讓我在佛蒙特州開個過夜旅館
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.89,0:26:52.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds great. I'd love to see Mark Baum run a bed and breakfast.\N{\rCHT}挺好的主意 我挺想看你會怎麼開旅館
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.36,0:26:54.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Like, "Here's your steel-cut oatmeal, asshole."\N{\rCHT}估計是這樣："吃你的燕麥粥吧 白癡 "
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.40,0:26:56.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark refused to kiss the ring of the people with the checkbooks,\N{\rCHT}馬克不願意討好那些能開出支票的顧客
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.07,0:27:00.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,so he had to set up his fund under Morgan Stanley's umbrella.\N{\rCHT}所以才委屈自己在摩根士丹利旗下開設基金
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.82,0:27:03.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,His small team reflected his distrust of the system.\N{\rCHT}他的團隊也反映出他對金融系統的質疑態度
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.99,0:27:05.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are sick. You're sick.\N{\rCHT}你們一群變態 變態
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.54,0:27:07.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,She says this job is making me unhappy.\N{\rCHT}她說 這工作讓我不爽
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.75,0:27:08.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're happy when you're unhappy.\N{\rCHT}可你不爽的時候反倒挺爽的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.87,0:27:10.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I am happy when I'm unhappy.\N{\rCHT}我是在不爽的時候感覺挺爽的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.46,0:27:11.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Vinnie Daniel.\N{\rCHT}文尼·丹尼爾
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.54,0:27:12.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know how to make a muffin?\N{\rCHT}你知道怎麼做松餅嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.75,0:27:14.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mark's numbers guy. - Do you even know 'now\N{\rCHT}- 文尼是馬克手下懂數位的人 - 你甚至連怎麼洗衣服
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.55,0:27:16.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- to do laundry? Make a bed? - Okay...\N{\rCHT}- 都不知道吧？鋪床呢？- 好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.09,0:27:18.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Vinnie lost his father to a violent crime when he was young.\N{\rCHT}文尼小的時候 爸爸就因為一場惡性犯罪去世了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.80,0:27:20.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Mark, he didn't talk about it.\N{\rCHT}和馬克一樣 他也從來不說起這事
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.72,0:27:21.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't talk about that.\N{\rCHT}我就是不說
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.05,0:27:24.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Cynthia's no joke. She could actually make him move to Vermont.\N{\rCHT}辛西婭這麼認真 還真有可能趕他到佛蒙特州去
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.47,0:27:26.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, she made me start wearing a seatbelt.\N{\rCHT}她都逼著我穿西服了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.22,0:27:27.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey, you want me to... - Porter Collins.\N{\rCHT}- 嘿 你想要我… - 伯特？柯林斯
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.06,0:27:30.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Former Olympic rower who went to Brown.\N{\rCHT}布朗大學的奧運會級別划船手
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.31,0:27:31.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He worked with Baum at a previous firm\N{\rCHT}從上一個公司和馬克一起過來
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.06,0:27:33.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and couldn't figure out why no one listened to Baum.\N{\rCHT}搞不懂為什麼沒人聽馬克的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.07,0:27:36.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy with all the good ideas.\N{\rCHT}他覺得馬克提出的都是好點子
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.23,0:27:38.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. I think you have the wrong FrontPoint.\N{\rCHT}抱歉 你是不是打錯電話了？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.15,0:27:40.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause there is another FrontPoint in this same building that is bonds.\N{\rCHT}這裡還有個叫前點基金的公司？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.99,0:27:43.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And Danny Moses. The optimist of the bunch.\N{\rCHT}丹尼·摩西 是這群人裡的樂天派
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.66,0:27:45.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And a hell of a trader.\N{\rCHT}他是交易鬼才
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.95,0:27:49.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is the only reason they put up with his bullshit optimism.\N{\rCHT}也這是大夥容忍他傻瓜式樂天派的唯一原因
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.16,0:27:50.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a weird call.\N{\rCHT}一個奇怪的電話
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.50,0:27:53.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You take longer with a wrong number than anybody else.\N{\rCHT}你對打錯電話的也太客氣了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.88,0:27:56.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It was this guy from Deutsche\N{\rCHT}這傢伙是德意志銀行的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.59,0:27:59.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,who was talking about shorting housing bonds.\N{\rCHT}說什麼做空房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.55,0:28:03.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then in the middle of the call I realized he had the wrong FrontPoint.\N{\rCHT}說到中間 我才聽出他找錯人了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.09,0:28:05.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then... 'Cause he wanted the one on the 8th floor.\N{\rCHT}然後他說想要找8層的那個公司
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.10,0:28:08.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to short housing bonds?\N{\rCHT}他想要做空房貸證券？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.10,0:28:09.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That happens like five times a day\N{\rCHT}每天至少5個撥錯的電話
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.23,0:28:10.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that somebody gets the wrong FrontPoint.\N{\rCHT}某人給了他錯誤的前點基金電話
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.77,0:28:12.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- We should change our name. - Wait. Wait.\N{\rCHT}- 咱們得改個名了 - 稍等
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.02,0:28:14.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to short housing bonds?\N{\rCHT}他想要做空房貸證券？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.27,0:28:17.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Who bets against housing?\N{\rCHT}賭房價跌嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.03,0:28:20.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's the ABX at? - What's ABX?\N{\rCHT}- 資產擔保證券指數到幾點了？- 這指數什麼意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.61,0:28:23.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It tracks subprime mortgage bond value. Go back to sleep.\N{\rCHT}用來跟蹤次級房貸證券的價值 回去睡你的覺
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.86,0:28:26.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The ABX is at...\N{\rCHT}指數在…
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.28,0:28:29.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it's down! It's down three points since last year.\N{\rCHT}我的天 降下來了 去年到現在降了3點
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.62,0:28:31.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird. I haven't heard a peep about that.\N{\rCHT}這不對勁 怎麼一點動靜都沒聽到過
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.96,0:28:33.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What was this guy's name?\N{\rCHT}這人叫啥？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.08,0:28:35.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jared Vennett. Vennett.\N{\rCHT}傑瑞德·威內特 威內特
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.29,0:28:37.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. These lucky sons of bitches\N{\rCHT}這是真的 這群中獎了的雜種
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.63,0:28:40.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,caught wind of one of the best trades in Wall Street history\N{\rCHT}抓住了華爾街歷史上最好的一樁交易
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.46,0:28:42.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,from a wrong number.\N{\rCHT}因為我撥錯的電話
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.13,0:28:44.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They should have paid 10% to my fuckstick assistant.\N{\rCHT}他們應該給我的錯誤電話線路抽成10%
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.47,0:28:46.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,His name was Jared Vennett. Vennett.\N{\rCHT}叫傑瑞德·威內特 威內特
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.89,0:28:48.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jared Vennett from Deutsche. Sounded very sketchy.\N{\rCHT}傑瑞德·威內特 德意志銀行 聽著就不靠譜
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.81,0:28:49.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like a douchebag.\N{\rCHT}聽他說話就讓人不爽
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.64,0:28:52.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you smell that?\N{\rCHT}你聞到了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.52,0:28:53.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you smell that?\N{\rCHT}你聞到了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.98,0:28:55.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I smell money.\N{\rCHT}我聞到錢的味道
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.02,0:28:57.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your basic mortgage...\N{\rCHT}這是你的基本房貸…
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.24,0:29:03.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, hi. How are you?\N{\rCHT}嘿 你們好啊
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.95,0:29:04.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat.\N{\rCHT}請坐
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.56,0:29:07.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Mr. Vennett from Deutsche Bank. What do we have?\N{\rCHT}來自德意志銀行的傑瑞德 我們洗耳恭聽了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.54,0:29:14.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There you go.\N{\rCHT}給
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.59,0:29:20.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how many people have you talked to about this trade?\N{\rCHT}你和多少人聊過？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.21,0:29:22.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A few. There's definitely some interest.\N{\rCHT}有幾個 有意向的還不少
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.05,0:29:24.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No! My boss would have my ass...\N{\rCHT}不 我老闆知道了非得弄死我不可
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.55,0:29:25.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- N.O.! - You crazy, Jared?\N{\rCHT}- 不 - 你瘋了吧？傑瑞
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.05,0:29:27.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Get lost. - Fuck you.\N{\rCHT}- 別廢話 - 滾蛋
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.35,0:29:31.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why you're here talking to us, a wrong number.\N{\rCHT}所以你才打錯電話給我們
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.22,0:29:32.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like there's a lot of interest.\N{\rCHT}聽著確實感興趣的人不少哇
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.73,0:29:35.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. A few people have invited us in\N{\rCHT}好吧 有的人和我聊天
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.14,0:29:37.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,just to laugh at me on this deal. Is that you?\N{\rCHT}就是看笑話尋開心 你們也不想談正事嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.61,0:29:38.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what this is?\N{\rCHT}你們也是這意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.69,0:29:39.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what this is.\N{\rCHT}我們不是這類人
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.82,0:29:41.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just how Mark is.\N{\rCHT}就馬克愛開這種玩笑
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.69,0:29:42.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let's see what you got. - I'm sorry.\N{\rCHT}- 和我們詳細說說 - 抱歉
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.07,0:29:44.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You smell that? - What is that?\N{\rCHT}- 你聞到什麼東西了嗎？- 聞到什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.86,0:29:46.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- What? - What's that smell?\N{\rCHT}- 什麼？- 這是什麼味道？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.70,0:29:48.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Your cologne? - No.\N{\rCHT}- 古龍水嗎？- 不…
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.08,0:29:53.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Opportunity. - No. Money.\N{\rCHT}- 發財的機會 - 不 錢的味道
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.87,0:29:55.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.25,0:29:56.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I smell money. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 我聞到錢味兒了- 好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.29,0:29:59.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Chris, God damn it. - Sorry.\N{\rCHT}- 克裡斯 該死的 - 抱歉
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.17,0:30:05.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your basic mortgage bond.\N{\rCHT}這就是你們房貸證券的構成
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.67,0:30:07.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right? The originals were simple.\N{\rCHT}對吧？開始很簡單
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.01,0:30:11.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They were just thousands ofAAA mortgages bundled together,\N{\rCHT}就是幾千個3A級房貸組合起來
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.76,0:30:13.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,guaranteed by the U.S. government.\N{\rCHT}政府擔保
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.60,0:30:15.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The modern ones are different.\N{\rCHT}而現代的房貸證券就不一樣了
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.52,0:30:18.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're private. And they're made up of layers of tranches.\N{\rCHT}是私營的 而且由分層份額構成意為某物的一部分
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.69,0:30:26.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The highest level, AAA, is getting paid first.\N{\rCHT}最高的3A級最先償還
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.20,0:30:27.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The lowest rated, B, is getting paid last,\N{\rCHT}最差的B級最後還
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.91,0:30:29.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,taking on defaults first.\N{\rCHT}會首先斷供
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.45,0:30:32.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, obviously, if you're buying B's, you could make more money.\N{\rCHT}顯然斷供的B級 能要回更多的錢來
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.20,0:30:33.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're a little risky.\N{\rCHT}但是有點風險
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.45,0:30:35.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes they fail.\N{\rCHT}有時候也可能償還不了
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.87,0:30:38.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Chris?\N{\rCHT}克裡斯…
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.04,0:30:44.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere along the line, these B's and BB's\N{\rCHT}某處開始 有些B級或者2B級
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.38,0:30:45.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,went from a little risky\N{\rCHT}從有點風險
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.92,0:30:48.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,to dog shit. Where's the trash?\N{\rCHT}變成狗屎貸 垃圾桶在哪
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.43,0:30:49.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's right behind you.\N{\rCHT}就在你後面
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.80,0:30:52.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking rock-bottom FICO scores.\N{\rCHT}我說的是最低的信用評分
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.89,0:30:55.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No income verification.\N{\rCHT}沒有收入核實
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.56,0:30:59.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Adjustable rates. Dog shit!\N{\rCHT}可調利率貸款 就是狗屎
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.90,0:31:03.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The default rates are already up from 1% to 4%, fellas.\N{\rCHT}違約率已經到了1至4個百分點
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.82,0:31:06.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And if they rise to 8%, and they will,\N{\rCHT}等到了8%… 也肯定會到的
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.82,0:31:09.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,a lot of these BBB's are going to zero, too.\N{\rCHT}那這些3B級的房貸也會一錢不值
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.15,0:31:10.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And that... You're too close.\N{\rCHT}這… 別離我這麼近
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.41,0:31:14.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- ...is an opportunity. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 這就是發財機會 - 好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.45,0:31:18.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that at 8% the bonds fail and we are already at 4%?\N{\rCHT}你說8%的警戒線 現在已經到4%了？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.16,0:31:19.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.\N{\rCHT}沒錯
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.25,0:31:21.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If they go to 8%, it's Armageddon?\N{\rCHT}到了8就是世界末日了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.13,0:31:22.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's right.\N{\rCHT}是的 沒錯
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.25,0:31:23.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How come nobody's talking about this?\N{\rCHT}那怎麼沒人提到過這事兒
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.09,0:31:26.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're completely sure of the math?\N{\rCHT}你計算沒問題嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.30,0:31:28.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at him. That's my quant.\N{\rCHT}好好看看他 他是我的礦工
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.97,0:31:30.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Your what?\N{\rCHT}你的啥？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.09,0:31:31.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My quantitative!\N{\rCHT}我的量化研究員
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.97,0:31:34.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My math specialist. Look at him.\N{\rCHT}我的數學專家 瞧瞧他
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.76,0:31:37.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You notice anything different about him? Look at his face.\N{\rCHT}看到有什麼與眾不同的嗎？看看他的臉
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.18,0:31:38.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty racist.\N{\rCHT}你這也太種族歧視了…
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.31,0:31:40.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at his eyes! I'll give you a hint.\N{\rCHT}看看他的眼睛 我提示你們一下…
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.90,0:31:42.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,His name's Yang!\N{\rCHT}他的名字叫做"楊"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.61,0:31:46.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He won a national math competition in China!\N{\rCHT}他得了國家數學競賽的金牌 還是中國的競賽
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.98,0:31:49.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't even speak English!\N{\rCHT}他連英語都不會說
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.57,0:31:51.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm sure of the math.\N{\rCHT}所以沒錯 我對數字有信心
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.95,0:31:56.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, my name's Jiang and I do speak English.\N{\rCHT}其實我名字叫"江" 我也會說英語
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.83,0:31:58.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jared likes to say I don't because he thinks\N{\rCHT}傑瑞喜歡這麼說
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.37,0:32:00.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,it makes me seem more authentic.\N{\rCHT}是想要讓我看起來更牛逼一些
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.29,0:32:02.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I got second in that national math competition.\N{\rCHT}我其實得了數學競賽第二名
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.42,0:32:08.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're offering us a chance to short this pile of blocks? How?\N{\rCHT}所以你讓我們做空這堆積木嗎？怎麼做空？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.38,0:32:11.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,With something called a credit default swap.\N{\rCHT}用信用違約互換來做
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.13,0:32:14.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like insurance on the bond, and if it goes bust\N{\rCHT}就像是證券的保險 不過如果證券完了
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.72,0:32:17.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,you can make 10-to-1, even 20-to-1 return.\N{\rCHT}那你能拿到10倍的賠償 甚至有可能拿到20倍
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.97,0:32:20.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's already slowly going bust!\N{\rCHT}崩潰趨勢已經開始了
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.35,0:32:22.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,10-to-1? 20-to-1? No way.\N{\rCHT}10倍 20倍 怎麼可能
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.52,0:32:24.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And no one's paying attention.\N{\rCHT}也沒人注意到
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.98,0:32:27.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No one is paying attention!\N{\rCHT}沒人親自去瞭解
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.48,0:32:30.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the banks are too busy getting paid obscene fees\N{\rCHT}因為銀行忙著賣證券
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.03,0:32:32.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,to sell these bonds.\N{\rCHT}暗地裡拿提成
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.40,0:32:35.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But wait. You are the bank. You work for the bank.\N{\rCHT}稍等 可你就是銀行的人 你為銀行工作
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.24,0:32:37.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet your margins are pretty nice and fat.\N{\rCHT}那你的提成也富的流油吧
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.37,0:32:39.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's not talk about my margins, by the way.\N{\rCHT}我的提成和這個沒關係
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.75,0:32:41.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Being nice and fat, that's a nice shirt. Do they make it for men?\N{\rCHT}這是我私事 好比我看你襯衫不錯 合不合適男的
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.17,0:32:44.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the bank?\N{\rCHT}你不替銀行說話？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.21,0:32:47.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I work for the bank. I don't think like a bank.\N{\rCHT}我給銀行打工 銀行的事跟我沒半毛關係
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.21,0:32:51.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Big bank, small bank, I like to make money. All right?\N{\rCHT}大銀行小銀行 我賺的是錢 對吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.17,0:32:53.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me put it this way. I'm standing in front of a burning house...\N{\rCHT}讓我直說 這就像我來到失火大樓前面
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.01,0:32:56.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm offering you fire insurance on it.\N{\rCHT}現場讓你們買火災保險
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.85,0:32:59.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How can these underlying bonds be as bad as you say?\N{\rCHT}怎麼可能這些證券像你說得那麼差
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.47,0:33:00.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be legal.\N{\rCHT}沒人管嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.77,0:33:02.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody knows what's in them.\N{\rCHT}沒人知道裡面裝的什麼東西
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.81,0:33:04.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody knows what's in the bonds.\N{\rCHT}沒人知道在證券裡有什麼貓膩
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.40,0:33:07.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen some that are 65% AAA-rated\N{\rCHT}我見到過65%達到3A評級的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.56,0:33:10.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that I know for a fact are filled with 95%\N{\rCHT}其實95%都是次級狗屎
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.61,0:33:13.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,subprime shit with FICOs below 550!\N{\rCHT}信用評分都低於550
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.86,0:33:14.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the fuck out of here.\N{\rCHT}你就吹吧
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.07,0:33:16.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You want me to really blow your mind?\N{\rCHT}真想被我吹暈了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.53,0:33:18.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,When the market deems a bond too risky to buy,\N{\rCHT}要是市場覺得一個證券風險太高了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.16,0:33:20.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,what do you think we do with it?\N{\rCHT}那你覺得我們怎辦？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.45,0:33:23.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Take a guess. - I don't know. You tell me.\N{\rCHT}- 你們猜吧 - 我不知道 才讓你說
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.16,0:33:27.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. You think we just warehouse it on the books? No.\N{\rCHT}好 你以為像書本上說的用倉單存貨抵押嗎？假的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.17,0:33:29.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We just repackage it with a bunch of other shit\N{\rCHT}實際上我們重新封包 混上
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.17,0:33:31.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that didn't sell and put it into a CDO.\N{\rCHT}其他賣不出去的東西 放到CDO裡面賣
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.09,0:33:34.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- A CDO? - Yes. A CDO.\N{\rCHT}- CDO？- 對 這東西叫CDO
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.93,0:33:36.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- What is that? - This is where we take a bunch of B's,\N{\rCHT}- 是什麼？- 把一些沒人買的B
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.76,0:33:38.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,BB's and BBB's that haven't sold,\N{\rCHT}2B 3B級爛貸
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.01,0:33:40.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and we put them in a pile.\N{\rCHT}打包成一堆…
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.22,0:33:44.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And when the pile gets large enough,\N{\rCHT}數量差不多了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.35,0:33:46.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the whole thing is suddenly considered diversified\N{\rCHT}就忽然叫做"分散化投資"了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.98,0:33:51.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the whores at the rating agency give it a 92%-93% AAA rating,\N{\rCHT}等著評級機構的婊子們 評個百分之92到93的3A級別
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.78,0:33:53.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,no questions asked.\N{\rCHT}其他屁都不放
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.45,0:33:57.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hold it. - What? Say that again.\N{\rCHT}- 見鬼 - 什麼 你再說一遍
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.24,0:34:00.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A collateralized debt obligation.\N{\rCHT}CDO 擔保債務憑證
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.58,0:34:02.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's important to understand because it's what allowed\N{\rCHT}理解CDO很重要 CDO才是讓房產危機…
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.16,0:34:06.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,a housing crisis to become a nationwide economic disaster.\N{\rCHT}禍害全國經濟的關鍵
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.37,0:34:09.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's world-famous chef Anthony Bourdain to explain.\N{\rCHT}讓我們的世界頂級廚師安東尼·伯爾頓解釋一下
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.13,0:34:17.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'm a chef on a Sunday afternoon setting the menu at a big restaurant.\N{\rCHT}假設我正給一個周日下午的大餐廳備菜
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.80,0:34:19.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I ordered my fish on Friday,\N{\rCHT}我週五定購的魚
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.30,0:34:22.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,which is the mortgage bond that Michael Burry shorted.\N{\rCHT}就好比邁克爾·巴里做空的房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.26,0:34:24.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But some of the fresh fish doesn't sell.\N{\rCHT}有些魚 沒賣出去
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.31,0:34:27.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why. Maybe it just came out halibut has the intelligence of a dolphin.\N{\rCHT}我也不知道原因 沒准這比目魚成精了有海豚一樣的智商
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.81,0:34:29.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what am I going to do?\N{\rCHT}那我該怎麼辦呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.61,0:34:33.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Throw all this unsold fish, which is the BBB level of the bond,\N{\rCHT}把這些3B評級的魚扔掉嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.19,0:34:35.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in the garbage and take the loss?\N{\rCHT}認虧了？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.61,0:34:37.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.\N{\rCHT}沒必要
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.65,0:34:40.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Being the crafty and morally onerous chef that I am,\N{\rCHT}我這麼心靈手巧…
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.16,0:34:42.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,whatever crappy levels of the bond I don't sell,\N{\rCHT}每種賣不掉的爛證券
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.99,0:34:44.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I throw into a seafood stew.\N{\rCHT}我都扔到海鮮湯裡去
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.00,0:34:48.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,See, it's not old fish. It's a whole new thing!\N{\rCHT}這不再是爛魚 這是新東西
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.54,0:34:52.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And the best part is they're eating 3-day-old halibut.\N{\rCHT}最妙的地方就在於 賣給顧客的名頭 是零售比目魚
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.34,0:34:54.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a CDO.\N{\rCHT}這就是CDO
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.13,0:34:56.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I just need to know, how could these possibly be collated?\N{\rCHT}怎麼可能這些東西被攢到一起
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.05,0:34:59.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow you're like Dora the Explorer\N{\rCHT}你好像《愛探險的朵拉》主人公
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.51,0:35:00.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're the first person\N{\rCHT}老是第一個
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.89,0:35:02.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- who found this thing. - Hold on. Hold on.\N{\rCHT}- 發現大新聞 - 稍等 稍等
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.30,0:35:04.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So mortgage bonds are dog shit,\N{\rCHT}你是說房貸證券是狗屎？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.26,0:35:06.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,CDOs are dog shit wrapped in cat shit.\N{\rCHT}CDO是貓屎包起來的狗屎
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.98,0:35:09.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.\N{\rCHT}對 就是這個理兒
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.90,0:35:13.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Institutions treat these CDOs like they're as solid as treasury bonds,\N{\rCHT}機構們還把CDO當成國庫券一樣的寶貝
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.48,0:35:15.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and they're going to zero.\N{\rCHT}等著它們一錢不值吧
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.94,0:35:18.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. That can't be right. There were $500 billion\N{\rCHT}不對啊 去年一年就賣了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.24,0:35:20.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in housing bonds sold last year alone.\N{\rCHT}5千億的房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.86,0:35:23.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The rating agencies, the banks, the fucking government,\N{\rCHT}信用評級機構 銀行政府也摻和在裡面？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.58,0:35:25.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,you're saying they're all asleep at the wheel?\N{\rCHT}你這就像在說他們閉著眼開車
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.66,0:35:29.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. My whole department's long on this stuff.\N{\rCHT}沒錯 我整個部門都對這種狗屎流口水
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.00,0:35:33.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They call me Chicken Little. They call me Bubble Boy.\N{\rCHT}他們反倒叫我膽小雞仔 他們叫我泡沫男孩
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.55,0:35:39.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A's, zero. B's, zero.\N{\rCHT}A級廢了 B級廢了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.26,0:35:43.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,BB's, zero. BBB's, zero.\N{\rCHT}2B級廢了 3B級 也是廢品
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.93,0:35:47.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then that happens.\N{\rCHT}接下來就是這個了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.39,0:35:49.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?\N{\rCHT}這是啥？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.94,0:35:52.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's America's housing market.\N{\rCHT}這就是美國的房產市場
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.61,0:35:56.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.73,0:35:57.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuckin' A, Jared.\N{\rCHT}說的好 傑瑞德
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.82,0:35:59.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your fucking mouth.\N{\rCHT}給我閉嘴
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.90,0:36:02.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- ...hang outwith you. - Good. Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 和你一起 - 很好 好的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.20,0:36:04.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sack up, do the deal. Let's be friends.\N{\rCHT}獲取利潤 達成成交 讓我們是朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.41,0:36:05.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We will see. Thank you.\N{\rCHT}我們會看到的 謝謝
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.70,0:36:06.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Don't bullshit me. - All right.\N{\rCHT}- 不要忽悠我 -好的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.83,0:36:07.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna say no, aren't you?\N{\rCHT}你要說不 是不是？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.04,0:36:10.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No, I'm just evaluating right now.\N{\rCHT}不 不 我只是在評估
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.58,0:36:12.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Thank you for coming in.\N{\rCHT}謝謝 謝謝你的到來
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.38,0:36:14.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Jared.\N{\rCHT}再見 傑瑞德
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.76,0:36:22.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like it.\N{\rCHT}這不對勁
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.14,0:36:24.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He's playing us.\N{\rCHT}他肯定有貓膩
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.93,0:36:27.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He's playing us. He's got too much skin in the game\N{\rCHT}他在玩我們 他陷得太深了 拉人墊背
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.85,0:36:29.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and he's dumping his position.\N{\rCHT}然後他脫身
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.48,0:36:31.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What if he's right?\N{\rCHT}要是他說的是真的呢
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.06,0:36:35.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You want him to be right. - Yes, I do.\N{\rCHT}- 你當然希望他說的是真的 - 我是希望
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.36,0:36:38.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The banks have given us 25% interest rates on credit cards.\N{\rCHT}銀行給我們信用卡的利息是25%
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.53,0:36:42.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They have screwed us on student loans that we can never get out from under.\N{\rCHT}助學貸款也坑了大家 普通人已經沒法脫身了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.15,0:36:45.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this guy walks into my office and says\N{\rCHT}然後這傢伙 走到我辦公室裡說
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.45,0:36:48.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,those same banks got greedy, they lost track of the market,\N{\rCHT}這些銀行太貪婪 已經忽視了市場真相了
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.49,0:36:50.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and I can profit off of their stupidity?\N{\rCHT}然後我還能通過他們的愚蠢賺錢
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.62,0:36:52.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck, yeah, I want him to be right!\N{\rCHT}媽的 我當然希望他是對的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.96,0:36:54.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How come you don't hate this guy?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼能不討厭他？
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.29,0:36:55.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He's everything you taught us not to trust.\N{\rCHT}你告誡我們注意的騙子特徵他身上全有
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.04,0:36:56.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't hate him.\N{\rCHT}我恨不起來
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.80,0:36:59.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He is so transparent in his self-interest that I kind of respect him.\N{\rCHT}他這麼把自己的利益擺到檯面上 我倒挺尊敬他
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.30,0:37:02.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Would I buy a car from him? No.\N{\rCHT}我會從這種人手裡買車嗎？肯定不會
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.63,0:37:04.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he right about the mortgage market?\N{\rCHT}但是他說的房貸市場情況是否屬實？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.97,0:37:07.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. - Let's find out. Let's find out.\N{\rCHT}- 不屬實 - 咱們自己去調查看看 去調查
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.76,0:37:10.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. It's two very simple questions.\N{\rCHT}我們只要回答兩個簡單問題
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.68,0:37:12.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a housing bubble?\N{\rCHT}房地產有沒有泡沫？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.27,0:37:14.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And if there is, how exposed are the banks?\N{\rCHT}如果有 銀行瞭解多少？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.94,0:37:15.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Okay.\N{\rCHT}好 好
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.06,0:37:17.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get on this quickly too.\N{\rCHT}咱們趕快行動
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.56,0:37:18.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if he's right,\N{\rCHT}如果情況屬實
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.02,0:37:22.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,every loser with a couple million bucks and a fund is gonna be jumping on this.\N{\rCHT}那有點錢的基金都會來找我們的麻煩
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.03,0:37:24.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.\N{\rCHT}現在就出發
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.00,0:37:35.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,JPMorgan Chase. JPMorgan Chase.\N{\rCHT}摩根大通 摩根大通
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.04,0:37:39.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Stop saying "JPMorgan Chase".\N{\rCHT}拜託 別再說摩根大通了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.54,0:37:40.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a good feeling about this.\N{\rCHT}我覺得咱們能交好運
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.05,0:37:42.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a meeting though, you know?\N{\rCHT}就一個會面 你知道的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.84,0:37:44.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a meeting. It's something like...\N{\rCHT}就一個會面 別抱太大期望
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.84,0:37:46.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People have meetings all the time. You know?\N{\rCHT}會面天天都有…
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.05,0:37:48.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People drink their coffee, they have a meeting.\N{\rCHT}人們喝完咖啡 就去會面…
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.76,0:37:50.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Brownfield Fund? - Yes!\N{\rCHT}- 棕地基金？- 對
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.18,0:37:52.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey. Hello. - Ted.\N{\rCHT}- 嘿 你們好 - 泰德
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.14,0:37:53.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Chris - Chris\N{\rCHT}- 我叫克裡斯 - 克裡斯
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.01,0:37:54.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm on Ted's desk. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 我叫克裡斯 泰德交易團隊的前臺 - 克裡斯 你好
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.90,0:37:57.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm Charlie, Charlie Geller. - Jamie. Jamie Shipley\N{\rCHT}- 我叫查理 查理·蓋勒 - 我叫傑米 傑米·希普利
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.44,0:37:57.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi.\N{\rCHT}嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.98,0:38:00.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're so excited to get set up on your trading platform.\N{\rCHT}我們太想在你們的交易平臺上接入了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.02,0:38:02.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool.\N{\rCHT}很好啊
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.23,0:38:04.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, have a seat a second.\N{\rCHT}先坐下聊一聊
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.78,0:38:05.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.\N{\rCHT}好的
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.86,0:38:09.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I... Ted had asked me to do some meeting prep.\N{\rCHT}我 泰德讓我 先和你們見面聊聊
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.87,0:38:13.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't find any marketing material on you guys.\N{\rCHT}可我一直找不到你們的宣傳資料
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.33,0:38:15.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We just moved here from Boulder.\N{\rCHT}我們是剛從科羅拉多州博爾德搬過來
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.25,0:38:16.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah. - Got it.\N{\rCHT}- 是的 - 知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.83,0:38:19.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Could we see some of your offering documents?\N{\rCHT}我能看看你們的招募書嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.29,0:38:21.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Brownfield is its own money.\N{\rCHT}其實 棕地基金用的是我們自己的錢
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.38,0:38:24.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's our money. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 我倆的存款 -嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.17,0:38:25.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell us how much you manage?\N{\rCHT}說說你們資金規模是多大？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.05,0:38:29.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. We're doing $30 million right now.\N{\rCHT}好啊 我們現在做到3千萬了…
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.59,0:38:33.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- But we started four years ago with $110, 000. - Wow.\N{\rCHT}- 可是我們是4年前開始的 當時只有11萬的本錢 - 厲害啊
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.72,0:38:38.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, as you can see, that's pretty phenomenal returns.\N{\rCHT}所以你看 我們的投資回報率相當厲害
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.44,0:38:41.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to get an ISDA agreement with JPMorgan so we can\N{\rCHT}我們想和摩根簽署ISDA協議
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.77,0:38:44.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,deal in long-term options.\N{\rCHT}這樣我們就能交易長線期權了
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.36,0:38:45.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's really cool. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 想法很好嘛 - 是啊
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.58,0:39:00.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That is so cool.\N{\rCHT}你們的想法很好
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.46,0:39:01.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.63,0:39:05.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But you guys are under the capital requirements for an ISDA.\N{\rCHT}不過呢 你們沒達到ISDA的資本准入門檻
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.92,0:39:06.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,By how much?\N{\rCHT}差多少？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.80,0:39:12.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,One billion four hundred seventy million, so...\N{\rCHT}差了十億四千七百萬 所以…
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.18,0:39:14.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...a lot.\N{\rCHT}還差挺多
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.97,0:39:17.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This makes us look bad, doesn't it,\N{\rCHT}這讓我們看起來挺不專業的 是嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.52,0:39:20.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that we didn't know what the capital requirements were?\N{\rCHT}我們連資金要求都不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.36,0:39:23.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not great.\N{\rCHT}影響是不太積極
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.27,0:39:25.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But\N{\rCHT}不過呢
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.65,0:39:28.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,keep up those returns and give us a call\N{\rCHT}你們保持這樣的利潤率
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.20,0:39:29.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,way down the line. You know.\N{\rCHT}以後發達了 記得再給我們打電話
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.07,0:39:31.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay?\N{\rCHT}好嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.16,0:39:32.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay. - Thanks, Chris.\N{\rCHT}- 好的 - 謝謝你 克裡斯
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.57,0:39:34.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Have a good one, guys. - Thank you, Chris.\N{\rCHT}- 祝你們好運 - 謝謝
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.96,0:39:39.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!\N{\rCHT}見鬼
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.12,0:39:42.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the fuck schedules a meeting\N{\rCHT}誰他媽會安排
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.46,0:39:44.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- at 4:50 in the afternoon? - Oh, my, God.\N{\rCHT}- 下午4點50談正事兒 - 哦 天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.67,0:39:46.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That was so painful.\N{\rCHT}真蛋疼
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.51,0:39:50.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dude, B ofA and Bear didn't even return our calls.\N{\rCHT}美國銀行和貝爾斯登沒回電話也就算了
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.22,0:39:54.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- And even fucking Wachovia blew us off, man! - I know.\N{\rCHT}- 連美聯銀行這種大眾貨也不鳥我們 - 知道了
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.30,0:39:56.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the prospectuses of all the other losers\N{\rCHT}這是其他一樣在大廳裡
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.64,0:39:58.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,who didn't make it past the lobby.\N{\rCHT}就被拍死的傢伙的招股書
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.43,0:40:00.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I can do this anymore. You know.\N{\rCHT}我真不想搞這個了 夥計
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.39,0:40:03.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm young, yet. I can still do something with my life.\N{\rCHT}我還年輕 還能幹點正事兒
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.31,0:40:05.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I miss Colorado anyway. The weed's better.\N{\rCHT}我想回科羅拉多老家 連大麻都比這邊的飄
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.36,0:40:08.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen, I need you to leave.\N{\rCHT}先生們 請離開大廳
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.49,0:40:09.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, yep, we're going. Let's go.\N{\rCHT}好 我們馬上走 咱們走
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.99,0:40:11.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this. Look at this.\N{\rCHT}看這個 看看這個
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.20,0:40:12.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy\N{\rCHT}這人
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.61,0:40:15.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,says that the housing market's a giant bubble.\N{\rCHT}說房地產市場就是一個大泡沫
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.91,0:40:20.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, so this part isn't totally accurate, you know.\N{\rCHT}這部分情節和真實情況有些出入
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.16,0:40:22.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't find Jared Vennett's housing bubble pitch\N{\rCHT}我倆不是在大廳發現了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.33,0:40:24.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in the lobby of a bank that rejected us.\N{\rCHT}傑瑞德的推銷資料
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.33,0:40:25.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is\N{\rCHT}實際情況是
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.00,0:40:27.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,a friend had told Charlie about it,\N{\rCHT}一個朋友告訴了查理這件事
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.72,0:40:30.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and I read about it Jim Grant's Interest Rate Observer.\N{\rCHT}我是從金融史學家吉姆·格蘭特的個人期刊上讀到的
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.34,0:40:31.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is crazy.\N{\rCHT}不敢相信
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.76,0:40:34.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is crazy stuff.\N{\rCHT}簡直像胡說的東西
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.34,0:40:37.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit, he's saying that there's 10-to-1 returns\N{\rCHT}這兒說房貸證券的信用違約互換
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.10,0:40:40.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,on credit default swaps for mortgage-backed securities?\N{\rCHT}是10倍的收益比
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.85,0:40:43.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And the whole housing market is about to collapse?\N{\rCHT}現在房地產市場馬上就要崩潰了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.19,0:40:48.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,For Jamie and Charlie, the housing market doomsday prediction was music to their ears.\N{\rCHT}對他倆來說 聽到這消息簡直像貓聞到了腥味一樣
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.07,0:40:58.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They had started working out of Jamie's garage\N{\rCHT}他倆在傑米家的車庫創業起家
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.12,0:41:02.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,with $110, 000 Jamie had saved taking sailboats up and down the East Coast.\N{\rCHT}資金是傑米在東海岸倒賣帆船攢下來的11萬
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.12,0:41:05.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Our investment strategy was simple.\N{\rCHT}我們的投資策略很簡單
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.00,0:41:08.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People hate to think about bad things happening,\N{\rCHT}沒人願意聽到壞消息
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.13,0:41:10.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,so they always underestimate their likelihood.\N{\rCHT}所以人們往往低估壞事發生的概率
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.55,0:41:13.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Their strategy was simple and brilliant.\N{\rCHT}簡單又高明的策略
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.59,0:41:14.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What he said.\N{\rCHT}他說的對
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.76,0:41:16.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jamie and Charlie found markets\N{\rCHT}他倆發現 市場
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.13,0:41:19.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,will sell options very cheaply on things they think will never happen.\N{\rCHT}會低價販賣認為不可能發生的事情的期權
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.85,0:41:21.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So when they were wrong, they were wrong small,\N{\rCHT}所以 一旦失利 損失會很小
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.52,0:41:23.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but when they were right, they were right big.\N{\rCHT}而一旦得利… 就能賺很多
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.32,0:41:34.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Within a few years they had turned $110, 000 into $30 million.\N{\rCHT}幾年間他們就把11萬做到了3千萬
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.15,0:41:35.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But then it was time to go to New York City.\N{\rCHT}是時候去紐約了…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.91,0:41:38.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And so far, it wasn't going very well.\N{\rCHT}不過進展並不順利
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.62,0:41:40.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So what if it does seem interesting. - No...\N{\rCHT}- 要是這個買賣可以做呢？- 不行
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.45,0:41:43.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No bank will give us our ISDA. We're dead in the water.\N{\rCHT}沒有銀行會和我們簽ISDA協議 咱們沒風掀不起浪啊…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.46,0:41:47.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,These kind of trades are totally out of the question.\N{\rCHT}這類交易完全搞不起
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.96,0:41:49.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We got to call Ben.\N{\rCHT}咱們必須打電話給本
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.80,0:41:53.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call Ben!\N{\rCHT}打給他
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.17,0:41:56.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben Rickert was a former trader in Singapore\N{\rCHT}本·裡克特是退下來的交易員 以前在摩根新加坡分行
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.34,0:41:59.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,for Chase who quit the whole game in disgust.\N{\rCHT}深深厭惡這一行就金盆洗手了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.18,0:42:01.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He happened to be Jamie's neighbor when they were in Colorado\N{\rCHT}當年在科羅拉多州 本正好是傑米的鄰居
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.60,0:42:03.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and they met walking dogs.\N{\rCHT}因為本在遛狗 兩人才認識
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.85,0:42:05.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But Ben was dark.\N{\rCHT}不過本的世界觀更陰暗
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.44,0:42:07.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't just think the whole system would fail.\N{\rCHT}不只認為金融系統會崩潰
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.56,0:42:09.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He thought the whole world was going down.\N{\rCHT}連全世界都會遲早毀滅
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.82,0:42:13.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Every one of these vegetables is fresh from my garden.\N{\rCHT}當然了 這些都是我花園裡新鮮採摘的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.40,0:42:17.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys should start your own garden.\N{\rCHT}你們應該開一個自己的花園
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.78,0:42:21.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What you got to do is get your soil off the petrochemicals.\N{\rCHT}別用石油化工的東西污染土壤
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.33,0:42:23.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I used wood ash and urine to help restore the soil.\N{\rCHT}用木屑和尿來改良土壤
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.62,0:42:25.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It creates ammonium nitrate.\N{\rCHT}增加單硝酸酯
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.29,0:42:27.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Seeds are gonna be the new currency.\N{\rCHT}以後種子會成為硬通貨
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.17,0:42:29.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And not those Franken-seeds from Monsanto.\N{\rCHT}不是孟山都公司的基因改造種子
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.25,0:42:31.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about good, healthy, organic seeds.\N{\rCHT}我說的是原生態的健康種子
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.92,0:42:33.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourself a garden.\N{\rCHT}自己種菜
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.13,0:42:34.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Learn to live off the land. - You're a fucking lunatic.\N{\rCHT}- 自給自足 - 這有點精神過敏了吧
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.67,0:42:36.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben had real experience in a big bank.\N{\rCHT}本有大銀行的實際經驗
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.97,0:42:40.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jamie and Charlie had never even been in a Manhattan bank bathroom.\N{\rCHT}傑米和查理連曼哈頓的銀行廁所都沒進過
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.76,0:42:42.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But Ben was done with the banking world.\N{\rCHT}但本明確說過金盆洗手
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.51,0:42:43.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He was very clear.\N{\rCHT}絕不再碰金融
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.87,0:42:45.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you realize that? -Alright, let's crunch some numbers,\N{\rCHT}- 這點你想到了嗎？- 咱們還是算清楚吧
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.68,0:42:47.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe we'll talk about calling Ben - I don't wanna crunch the numbers,\N{\rCHT}- 然後再打電話給本 - 我不想算來算去
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.06,0:42:49.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're always crunching numbers.\N{\rCHT}每次咱們都是算了再決定的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.19,0:42:50.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,When haven't we crunched the numbers?\N{\rCHT}什麼時候算清楚？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.31,0:42:51.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna crunch the numbers like harder...\N{\rCHT}我們要算清楚就像…
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.48,0:42:52.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I need you out of here.\N{\rCHT}你們兩個趕快離開
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.52,0:42:54.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Of course. One second. - Yes, ma'am. We're going.\N{\rCHT}- 好的 麻煩您了 - 馬上就走
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.53,0:42:59.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God. I hate this. This is a total waste of time.\N{\rCHT}天哪 真是自找麻煩 這調研絕對是浪費時間
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.03,0:43:02.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on. Would you relax?\N{\rCHT}別擔心了 想開點
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.12,0:43:06.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a housing development 45 minutes outside town.\N{\rCHT}城外45分鐘車程聽說有新房
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.33,0:43:08.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark wants us to check that out first.\N{\rCHT}我們要不就先去那裡看看
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.29,0:43:10.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I hope there are some Cuban restaurants on the way there.\N{\rCHT}希望一路上有古巴口味的餐館
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.38,0:43:13.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I heard the Cuban food is amazing in Miami.\N{\rCHT}聽說在邁阿密 古巴食品是一絕
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.09,0:43:15.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't be chipper in the face of me being miserable.\N{\rCHT}你這麼開心簡直幸災樂禍
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.88,0:43:17.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It really makes me hate you.\N{\rCHT}我恨你
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.63,0:43:20.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How is wanting to eat good food being chipper?\N{\rCHT}我想吃好的 還惹著你了
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.89,0:43:23.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?\N{\rCHT}你好？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.47,0:43:25.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?\N{\rCHT}你好？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.52,0:43:27.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What do these go for?\N{\rCHT}這些要幹嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.52,0:43:31.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$425, 000 each?\N{\rCHT}42萬5千一幢？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.08,0:43:54.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, man? What do you want?\N{\rCHT}有事嗎？你們想幹嘛
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.75,0:43:58.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello. I'm surveying mortgage owners who are over 90 days delinquent.\N{\rCHT}我們正在調查已經90天斷供房貸的房主
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.17,0:44:00.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for a Harvey Humpsey.\N{\rCHT}我找哈威·漢姆西
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.80,0:44:01.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You want my landlord's dog?\N{\rCHT}你找我房東的狗幹嘛
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.14,0:44:08.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Your landlord filled out his mortgage application using his dog's name?\N{\rCHT}你房東用狗的名字填了房貸申請表？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.22,0:44:09.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.\N{\rCHT}看來是咯
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.77,0:44:12.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, has that asshole not been paying his mortgage?\N{\rCHT}等等 這混蛋沒有再交房貸嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.35,0:44:13.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause I've been paying my rent.\N{\rCHT}我可是一直在交房租啊
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.77,0:44:15.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah, he is over 90 days delinquent.\N{\rCHT}他是有90天沒還房貸了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.07,0:44:17.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, man,\N{\rCHT}說真的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.73,0:44:19.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,am I gonna have to leave?\N{\rCHT}我是不是要搬家了？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.07,0:44:24.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause my kid just got settled in school, man.\N{\rCHT}我小孩才剛安排好在這兒上學
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.53,0:44:26.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. How are ya?\N{\rCHT}你好啊
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.37,0:44:29.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- My name's Ken. - You're Ken?\N{\rCHT}- 我叫肯 - 你是肯？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.95,0:44:31.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You should talk to your landlord about that.\N{\rCHT}你得直接問問你的房東了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.83,0:44:33.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I don't have any more information.\N{\rCHT}我這裡沒有什麼能幫到你的了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.42,0:44:34.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But you...\N{\rCHT}不過你…
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.46,0:44:37.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a great day. See ya, Ken.\N{\rCHT}祝你們好運 再見 肯
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.13,0:44:38.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's books everywhere!\N{\rCHT}到處是書
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.63,0:44:40.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Books everywhere?\N{\rCHT}是嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.97,0:44:44.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, man, is everything gonna be okay?\N{\rCHT}真的… 不會真的有事兒吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.30,0:44:47.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You should... You should call him.\N{\rCHT}你得問… 你得問房東
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.47,0:44:48.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You should give him a call.\N{\rCHT}打電話給他
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.60,0:44:50.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault, dude. I've been paying...\N{\rCHT}錯不在我身上 我可是一直在交房租
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.15,0:44:55.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello!\N{\rCHT}你好
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.15,0:45:01.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the Mary Celeste.\N{\rCHT}好像有人走得很急
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.36,0:45:04.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. All they took was the TV.\N{\rCHT}看 就搬走了電視
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.91,0:45:06.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's weird.\N{\rCHT}這不對勁
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.95,0:45:09.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't even clean out the cat litter.\N{\rCHT}連廚房檯面都沒打掃
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.84,0:45:18.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God.\N{\rCHT}老天爺
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.52,0:45:32.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like Chernobyl.\N{\rCHT}簡直像核污染的切爾諾巴里
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.52,0:45:35.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's like a hundred houses. There can't be four people living here.\N{\rCHT}這大概有100間房子 也就4個人在住
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.98,0:45:40.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, fuck that! - Shit!\N{\rCHT}- 哦 媽的 - 見鬼
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.04,0:45:58.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- He's been in there for seven hours. - Where does he go to the bathroom?\N{\rCHT}- 他在裡面呆了7個小時了 - 在洗手間？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.17,0:45:59.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he had a breakdown.\N{\rCHT}我聽說他崩潰了
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.67,0:46:01.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He's letting the fund tank.\N{\rCHT}已經破罐子破摔了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.30,0:46:04.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Burry's office.\N{\rCHT}巴里博士辦公室
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.18,0:46:06.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he actually prefers that you email him.\N{\rCHT}他還是希望你發郵件給他
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.89,0:46:08.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.\N{\rCHT}稍等
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.51,0:46:09.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Fields, Mr...\N{\rCHT}菲爾茲先生
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.64,0:46:15.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hi, Lawrence. - Holy shit!\N{\rCHT}- 你好 勞倫斯 - 天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.02,0:46:23.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We have no confidence in your ability to identify macroeconomic trends.\N{\rCHT}我們對你預測宏觀經濟趨勢的能力沒有信心
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.57,0:46:27.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You flew here to tell me that? Why?\N{\rCHT}你坐飛機來就為了說這個 為什麼？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.20,0:46:30.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone can see that there is a real estate bubble.\N{\rCHT}每個人都能看出來房地產有泡沫
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.70,0:46:32.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, no one can see a bubble.\N{\rCHT}沒人能看出有泡沫
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.62,0:46:33.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what makes it a bubble.\N{\rCHT}你的想法才是泡沫
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.91,0:46:36.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's dumb, Lawrence.\N{\rCHT}這麼說太蠢了
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.29,0:46:37.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's always markers.\N{\rCHT}總有線索可以找啊
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.63,0:46:41.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mortgage fraud has\N{\rCHT}房貸欺詐
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.17,0:46:42.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,quintupled since 2000\N{\rCHT}2000年以後翻了5倍
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.05,0:46:45.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the average take-home pay is flat,\N{\rCHT}平均收入卻沒漲
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.32,0:46:47.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but home prices are soaring.\N{\rCHT}房價暴漲
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.45,0:46:49.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the homes are debt, not assets.\N{\rCHT}意味著房子不再用來住 而是投資品
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.68,0:46:51.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So Mike Burry of San Jose, a guy who\N{\rCHT}那你這個邁克爾·巴里矽谷來的
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.89,0:46:56.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,gets his hair cut at Supercuts and doesn't wear shoes,\N{\rCHT}在連鎖理髮店理髮 不穿鞋
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.39,0:46:59.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,knows more than Alan Greenspan and Hank Paulson.\N{\rCHT}你就比格林斯潘和財政部長懂得多？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.40,0:47:00.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...\N{\rCHT}這個嘛
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.11,0:47:03.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Mike Burry, yes, he does.\N{\rCHT}我雖然沒和財政部長聊過 不過我確實更懂
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.94,0:47:06.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's cute. That's cute.\N{\rCHT}你還挺萌啊
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.82,0:47:09.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you being sarcastic with us, Mike?\N{\rCHT}你這是在諷刺自己嗎 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.28,0:47:13.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence,\N{\rCHT}勞倫斯…
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.79,0:47:16.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to be sarcastic.\N{\rCHT}我這人不懂什麼叫諷刺
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.96,0:47:19.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to be funny. I don't know how to\N{\rCHT}我也不會開玩笑 我不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.42,0:47:21.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,work people.\N{\rCHT}禮尚往來
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.96,0:47:23.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I...\N{\rCHT}我
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.21,0:47:25.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I just know how to read numbers.\N{\rCHT}可我對數據是真的懂
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.63,0:47:28.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How big is your short position right now?\N{\rCHT}你現在做空多少了？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.63,0:47:31.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just $1.3 billion.\N{\rCHT}13億
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.80,0:47:34.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- And the premiums? - Well, we pay\N{\rCHT}- 保費交多少？- 我們大概交
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.10,0:47:38.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,roughly $80 to 90 million\N{\rCHT}8千萬到9千萬
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.56,0:47:40.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,each year, which is high,\N{\rCHT}每年交 有點多
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.10,0:47:42.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was the first to do this trade.\N{\rCHT}畢竟咱們開了先例
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.27,0:47:45.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch. It will pay. I may have been early, but I'm not wrong.\N{\rCHT}等著吧 肯定能賺錢 我最先趟的道 但方向是對的
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.82,0:47:48.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same thing. It's the same thing, Mike!\N{\rCHT}你就會吹 你就會吹 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.99,0:47:53.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're managing a fund of, what, $555 million?\N{\rCHT}你管理的基金有多少 5億5千5百萬？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.66,0:47:57.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In six years, it'll all be gone.\N{\rCHT}六年內 交保費就賠光了
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.95,0:47:59.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,On one bet.\N{\rCHT}單單這一項
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.46,0:48:02.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the second quarter of '07 is when the adjustable rates kick in.\N{\rCHT}07年第二季度可調利率就發威了
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.75,0:48:04.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The defaults will skyrocket.\N{\rCHT}肯定會出現大批斷供
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.34,0:48:06.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Says you.\N{\rCHT}也就你這麼想
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.13,0:48:08.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How much is eligible for withdrawal before they do?\N{\rCHT}在合約到期前 基金裡有多少錢可以撤回？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.67,0:48:10.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, in the next two quarters.\N{\rCHT}就算半年之內吧
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.30,0:48:13.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If your investors panic.\N{\rCHT}如果你的投資人恐慌了的話
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.85,0:48:18.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$302 million?\N{\rCHT}3億零2百萬
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.85,0:48:21.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My God, Mike.\N{\rCHT}不妙啊 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.32,0:48:28.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No one will pull out. That would be suicide.\N{\rCHT}不會有人往外取錢的 那樣損人不利己
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.32,0:48:30.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I'm down 17% for the year.\N{\rCHT}今年雖然下跌了17%
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.86,0:48:33.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But if they trust me, and they trust me, because...\N{\rCHT}但相信我就行了 而且他們一直相信我
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.24,0:48:35.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No one trusts you! No one!\N{\rCHT}沒人相信你 沒人
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.95,0:48:38.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I sent several emails to my investors\N{\rCHT}我寫了幾封信給投資人了
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.49,0:48:40.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,letting them know that the...\N{\rCHT}讓他們瞭解情況
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.17,0:48:47.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...the second quarter of '07 is when our housing positions show returns and...\N{\rCHT}07年的第二季度 我們房貸投資就能盈利
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.55,0:48:49.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been very clear.\N{\rCHT}我說得很清楚了
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.59,0:48:53.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People will withdraw their money.\N{\rCHT}你就等著大家撤資吧
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.01,0:48:57.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Lawrence, that would be so stupid. I mean, the...\N{\rCHT}為啥 誰會這麼傻？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.56,0:49:01.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If the fund's capitals drop too much,\N{\rCHT}如果我們基金的資本減少過多
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.52,0:49:04.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,then the swaps contracts are voided.\N{\rCHT}那麼互換合同就會自動失效
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.69,0:49:07.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the banks get to keep all of the collateral.\N{\rCHT}然後銀行就會拿走所有錢
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.02,0:49:10.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Wait a minute. Wait. - All of it.\N{\rCHT}- 等一下 等等 - 一個子兒都不剩
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.36,0:49:12.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The contracts are voided?\N{\rCHT}合同會自動失效？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.57,0:49:14.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The contracts are voided?\N{\rCHT}合同會自動失效？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.07,0:49:16.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy shit!\N{\rCHT}狗屁的
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.20,0:49:18.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, motherfucker!\N{\rCHT}你這臭不要臉的
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.87,0:49:20.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael?\N{\rCHT}邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.75,0:49:22.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me my money back.\N{\rCHT}把我的錢還我
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.83,0:49:29.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael, do you hear me? I want my money back.\N{\rCHT}邁克爾 聽見了嗎？我要退回我的錢
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.71,0:49:34.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me my fucking money back...\N{\rCHT}你他媽的把我的錢給我
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.09,0:49:36.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...you motherfucker.\N{\rCHT}你這小兔崽子
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.43,0:49:40.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The market's in an itsy-bitsy little gully right now.\N{\rCHT}房產市場正處在一個小不丁點的低谷裡
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.68,0:49:42.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like everybody said, "Okay, that was crazy.\N{\rCHT}好像大夥說"玩得太嗨了"
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.02,0:49:44.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let's just all calm down."\N{\rCHT}"咱們稍微緩緩神"
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.73,0:49:49.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I sold that house for $350, 000 the year it was built.\N{\rCHT}那房子剛建成的時候 我35萬賣了出去
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.61,0:49:52.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Two years later, $480, 000.\N{\rCHT}兩年以後 就值48萬
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.90,0:49:56.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Then $585, 000 maybe 18 months ago.\N{\rCHT}然後58萬5 這是一年半以前的價格
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.20,0:49:58.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This couple bought it for $650, 000 last year.\N{\rCHT}這對夫妻在去年花65萬買了下來
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.24,0:50:01.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd let it go for that...\N{\rCHT}現在只能按原價賣唄
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.16,0:50:02.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, John.\N{\rCHT}嘿 約翰
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.91,0:50:03.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no.\N{\rCHT}不 不 不
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.58,0:50:05.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It will break his heart, but he'll let it go.\N{\rCHT}他肯定覺得不值 不過會放手的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.08,0:50:07.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he selling?\N{\rCHT}那他為什麼要賣房？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.92,0:50:09.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither one's working right now.\N{\rCHT}夫妻倆現在都沒工作
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.75,0:50:13.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Marlene, you'd say they're motivated, right?\N{\rCHT}馬琳 你說他們急於出手是吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.46,0:50:16.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,As motivated as one can be in this neighborhood.\N{\rCHT}和這片的人積極性差不多吧
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.55,0:50:19.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This house on the left, I would say they're probably motivated.\N{\rCHT}左邊這房子 才是真正急於出手
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.18,0:50:21.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, a lot of people seem very motivated.\N{\rCHT}我說 急於出手的也太多了點
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.22,0:50:22.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's just the gully.\N{\rCHT}房價小觸底嘛
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.60,0:50:24.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all. Just...\N{\rCHT}僅此而已 就是
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.43,0:50:25.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just nerves.\N{\rCHT}大夥神經過敏
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.94,0:50:27.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So where do we stand?\N{\rCHT}那… 我們把車停到哪兒
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.81,0:50:31.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to talk to my wife.\N{\rCHT}我得和我老婆商量一下
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.40,0:50:32.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This market won't last.\N{\rCHT}再等 過了這村就沒這店了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.78,0:50:34.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, could I talk to a mortgage broker?\N{\rCHT}其實 能給我介紹個房貸經紀人嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.65,0:50:36.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody you recommend? Anybody you like.\N{\rCHT}你推薦的 不錯的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.57,0:50:38.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes, I have someone. Absolutely.\N{\rCHT}有啊 是有個絕佳人選
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.66,0:50:39.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, bitch better like me.\N{\rCHT}這小妞肯定喜歡我啊
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.99,0:50:41.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sent her ass to Cabo.\N{\rCHT}我幫她賺錢賺翻了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.87,0:50:45.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So is Morgan Stanley recruiting us? Is that it?\N{\rCHT}連摩根士丹利都等著要我們了？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.75,0:50:48.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. No. The bank owns our hedge fund,\N{\rCHT}不是… 銀行擁有我們的對沖基金
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.79,0:50:49.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but we're not really part of it.\N{\rCHT}但我們其實不歸銀行管
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.96,0:50:52.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We invest in financial service companies\N{\rCHT}我們主要投資金融服務公司
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.50,0:50:55.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and we're trying to understand the residential mortgage business.\N{\rCHT}我們過來是想瞭解這裡房貸行業的情況
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.55,0:50:58.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How many loans do you write each month?\N{\rCHT}你每個月能辦多少筆貸款
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.59,0:51:00.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- About 60. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 大概60筆吧 - 對
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.22,0:51:01.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What was it four years ago?\N{\rCHT}4年前呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.64,0:51:03.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten...\N{\rCHT}10筆…
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.06,0:51:05.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe 15.\N{\rCHT}15筆的樣子
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.39,0:51:07.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was a bartender. Now I own a boat.\N{\rCHT}以前我是酒吧招待 現在我連船都有了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.77,0:51:08.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You own a...\N{\rCHT}你有
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.81,0:51:12.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So how many of these are adjustable-rate mortgages?\N{\rCHT}這裡面有多少是可調利率的房貸？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.15,0:51:13.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, most. - Oh, yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 嗯 絕大多數 - 哦 是的
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.90,0:51:15.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'd say about 90%.\N{\rCHT}是 我覺得有90%左右
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.94,0:51:19.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The bonuses on those skyrocketed a few years ago.\N{\rCHT}近幾年這種房貸提成飆上天了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.16,0:51:20.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Adjustable's our bread and honey.\N{\rCHT}我們全靠這個賺錢
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.53,0:51:23.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So do applicants ever get rejected?\N{\rCHT}那房貸申請有被拒的時候嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.41,0:51:28.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?\N{\rCHT}怎麼可能
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.50,0:51:31.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, if they get rejected, I suck at my job.\N{\rCHT}要是他們被拒 我就不稱職了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.67,0:51:33.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they have no money?\N{\rCHT}他們沒錢也能貸到款？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.25,0:51:36.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my firm offers NINJA loans.\N{\rCHT}我們公司有一種"忍者貸款"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.21,0:51:38.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay. - "No Income, No Job."\N{\rCHT}- 好吧 - 不需要收入和職業證明
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.01,0:51:41.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I just leave the income section blank if I want.\N{\rCHT}收入一欄空著都可以
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.30,0:51:42.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Corporate doesn't care.\N{\rCHT}公司不在乎
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.64,0:51:45.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,These people just want homes. And they go with the flow.\N{\rCHT}大夥想要房 公司順應民意唄
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.02,0:51:48.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good for you. - Your companies don't verify?\N{\rCHT}- 你當然願意 - 你們公司都不查驗的嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.85,0:51:53.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If I write a loan on Friday afternoon,\N{\rCHT}我星期五下午簽了房貸合同
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.73,0:51:56.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,a big bank will buy it by Monday lunch.\N{\rCHT}大銀行週一中午就會買走
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.28,0:51:58.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Same here.\N{\rCHT}見怪不怪 我們也一樣
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.40,0:52:03.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Could you hold on a second? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 你們能等會嗎？- 行啊
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.96,0:52:11.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it. Why are they confessing?\N{\rCHT}我搞不明白 為啥他們這麼坦白
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.71,0:52:13.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not confessing.\N{\rCHT}他們不是在坦白…
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.79,0:52:15.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're bragging.\N{\rCHT}他們這是在吹牛
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.22,0:52:28.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do people have any idea what they are buying?\N{\rCHT}貸款的人真的知道這種貸款的風險嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.18,0:52:31.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I focus on the immigrants, you know.\N{\rCHT}我一般找移民
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.52,0:52:32.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Once they find out they're getting a home,\N{\rCHT}等他們還不起房貸睡大街了…
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.02,0:52:34.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,they sign where you tell them to sign.\N{\rCHT}你讓他們簽什麼都願意
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.69,0:52:36.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask questions. Don't understand the rates.\N{\rCHT}不會問問題 不理解利率是什麼東西
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.90,0:52:38.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fucking idiots. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 都是他媽的的弱智 - 對
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.44,0:52:39.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And you target immigrants, too?\N{\rCHT}你也找移民下手嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.94,0:52:42.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, their credit actually isn't bad enough for him.\N{\rCHT}移民的信用分對他來說還太好
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.70,0:52:46.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I'm a yield guy.\N{\rCHT}我不跟錢過不去
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.87,0:52:47.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...\N{\rCHT}好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.00,0:52:52.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I make $2, 000 on a fixed-rate prime loan, right?\N{\rCHT}一筆固定利率的良性房貸 我只賺兩千 對吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.50,0:52:56.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can make $10, 000 on a subprime adjustable.\N{\rCHT}可做一筆可調利率的次級貸 我能賺一萬
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.21,0:52:59.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Trust me, I'm not driving a 7 Series without strippers.\N{\rCHT}說真的 沒有脫衣舞女郎的幫忙 我也開不上寶馬7系
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.26,0:53:02.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No one on the pole has good credit and they're all cash rich.\N{\rCHT}她們信用評分都不行 可是都超級有錢
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.63,0:53:04.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I read Warren Buffett say something like that.\N{\rCHT}我好像聽沃倫·巴菲特說過類似的話
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.47,0:53:07.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Who's Warren Buffett?\N{\rCHT}啥？沃倫·巴菲特是誰？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.26,0:53:10.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, so strippers. Like exotic dancers?\N{\rCHT}你說的脫衣舞女郎就是露肉的那種？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.06,0:53:12.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, yeah.\N{\rCHT}對 對 對
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.35,0:53:14.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Nude, you know, topless.\N{\rCHT}光屁股的 露著胸的
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.40,0:53:16.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Strippers. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 脫衣舞女郎 - 對
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.82,0:53:21.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you introduce us?\N{\rCHT}能幫我們介紹個嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.11,0:53:23.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Yes.\N{\rCHT}當然行 沒問題
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.62,0:53:28.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I always get option-pay adjustables. I'm a private contractor.\N{\rCHT}我一直選還貸方式多的可調房貸 我畢竟是自由職業者
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.62,0:53:30.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What? I can't hear you. I'm sorry.\N{\rCHT}說什麼呢？聽不清 抱歉
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.37,0:53:32.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I always get option-pay adjustables.\N{\rCHT}我一直選還貸方式多的那種可調房貸
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.29,0:53:34.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a private contractor. I need flexibility.\N{\rCHT}我自己幹 需要點靈活性
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.62,0:53:37.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And you tell the mortgage company what you do?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼跟房貸公司說你的職業
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.29,0:53:39.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I write "therapist".\N{\rCHT}我寫的是：治療師
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.38,0:53:40.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You can touch me. - Always?\N{\rCHT}- 你可以摸我 - 一直？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.46,0:53:42.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Only in V.I.P.\N{\rCHT}那只能在VIP房間
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.59,0:53:45.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, you say you always do adjustables.\N{\rCHT}不不不 誤會了 你說你一直選可調利息房貸
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.30,0:53:47.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And you have more than one loan on a property?\N{\rCHT}你一套房子不止一筆貸款嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.18,0:53:49.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody does. At least down here.\N{\rCHT}大夥都這樣 至少我們這兒這樣
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.47,0:53:50.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, what?\N{\rCHT}我沒聽明白
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.56,0:53:53.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody does. At least down here.\N{\rCHT}每個人都這樣 至少我們這兒是
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.23,0:53:55.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That way you only put down, like, 5%.\N{\rCHT}這樣首付只要5%
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.48,0:53:57.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Prices have leveled off, though, right?\N{\rCHT}可房價現在不漲了 對吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.36,0:53:59.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There's a gully.\N{\rCHT}是啊 暫時不漲
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.27,0:54:02.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind not moving anymore? I'll still pay you.\N{\rCHT}你能不能別晃來晃去的？我照樣付你錢
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.78,0:54:09.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. We're not alone.\N{\rCHT}抱歉 有人盯著
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.58,0:54:12.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, look. If home prices don't go up,\N{\rCHT}你聽我說… 如果房價不漲
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.29,0:54:14.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,you are not going to be able to refinance.\N{\rCHT}你就不能重新貸款了
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.66,0:54:17.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll be stuck paying whatever your monthly payment is\N{\rCHT}你就陷到房貸裡脫不開身 等利率優惠期過了
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.88,0:54:20.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,once it jumps up after your teaser rate expires.\N{\rCHT}月供漲到多少是多少 加上逾期的利滾利
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.00,0:54:23.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Your monthlies could go up 200%-300%.\N{\rCHT}可能漲到200%到300%
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.46,0:54:25.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,James says I can always refinance.\N{\rCHT}詹姆斯說我總可以重新貸款的
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.59,0:54:27.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's a liar.\N{\rCHT}那 他就是個騙子
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.47,0:54:30.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, in this particular case, James probably is wrong.\N{\rCHT}至少對這種情況 他很可能是錯的
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.68,0:54:33.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,200 percent? On all my loans?\N{\rCHT}200%？我所有房貸的？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.06,0:54:35.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean "all" your loans?\N{\rCHT}你"所有"房貸什麼意思？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.52,0:54:37.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're talking about two loans on one house, right?\N{\rCHT}不就是一套房兩筆貸款嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.77,0:54:40.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I have five houses.\N{\rCHT}我有5套房
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.86,0:54:42.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And a condo.\N{\rCHT}外加一套公寓房
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.69,0:54:46.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there's a bubble.\N{\rCHT}有泡沫
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.28,0:54:47.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼知道的？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.36,0:54:50.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Trust me. Call Vennett, buy $50 million in swaps on the MBS.\N{\rCHT}相信我 打電話給傑瑞德 買上5千萬房貸證券的信用違約互換
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.87,0:54:53.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we got? Garibaldi IV, BBB.\N{\rCHT}買哪個？加里波底4 3B評級
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.87,0:54:55.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, are you sure?\N{\rCHT}馬克 你確定嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.45,0:54:57.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Yeah, it's time to call bullshit.\N{\rCHT}確定 這泡沫太扯淡了
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.37,0:55:00.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Bullshit on what? - Every fucking thing.\N{\rCHT}- 哪些有泡沫？- 這兒他媽的全都是泡沫
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.23,0:55:25.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,FrontPoint! FrontPoint!\N{\rCHT}前點對沖基金 前點對沖基金
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.74,0:55:29.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this America's angriest hedge fund?\N{\rCHT}是美國最暴走的對沖基金嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.61,0:55:31.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, listen. I got one last question for you.\N{\rCHT}聽好了 我還有最後一個問題問你
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.91,0:55:34.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you fucking us?\N{\rCHT}你想怎麼蹂躪我們？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.58,0:55:38.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a nicer way to say that, Vinnie.\N{\rCHT}何必說的這麼露骨呢… 文尼
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.21,0:55:39.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious.\N{\rCHT}我沒開玩笑
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.83,0:55:42.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll buy your swaps, but only if you say how you're fucking us.\N{\rCHT}我們會買你的互換 但前提是你說清楚打算怎麼蹂躪我們
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.00,0:55:45.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not fucking you, Vinnie. I'm kissing you.\N{\rCHT}我不想蹂躪你 文尼 我想要親吻你
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.59,0:55:48.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking deep into your eyes as I make love to you, Vinnie.\N{\rCHT}看著你的雙眼 讓你爽
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.42,0:55:51.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm handing you the deal of the century on a fucking platter.\N{\rCHT}我正和盤托出本世紀最好的買賣給你
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.84,0:55:54.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I get out of it? Easy.\N{\rCHT}我能得到什麼好處？這還不簡單
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.31,0:55:56.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a $20-million-a-month negative carry.\N{\rCHT}我之前做的證券每月賠進去2千萬
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.81,0:55:58.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I got bosses trying to pull the plug\N{\rCHT}老闆早就想要了我的命
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.27,0:56:00.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,because they think I'm out of my fucking mind.\N{\rCHT}認為我神經不正常了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.77,0:56:01.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right?\N{\rCHT}明白嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.85,0:56:02.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We make this trade,\N{\rCHT}我們做成了這筆買賣
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.02,0:56:05.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,those problems aren't so big anymore.\N{\rCHT}我之前的問題都不是事兒
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.44,0:56:09.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And sure, swaps are a dark market, so I set the price.\N{\rCHT}當然了… 互換是黑市 怎麼定價
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.28,0:56:10.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever price I want.\N{\rCHT}我說了算
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.86,0:56:12.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you come for the payday,\N{\rCHT}等你收回投資的時候
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.41,0:56:14.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna rip your eyes out, I'm gonna make a fortune.\N{\rCHT}我肯定會讓你大出血 從你那裡大賺一筆
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.74,0:56:17.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But the good news is, Vinnie, you're not gonna care\N{\rCHT}但好消息是 你也不會在乎的
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.33,0:56:19.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,because you're gonna make so much fucking money.\N{\rCHT}因為你賺的錢太多 你都沒空管我
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.62,0:56:20.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I get out of it.\N{\rCHT}這就是我能得的好處
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.00,0:56:22.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to know what you get out of it?\N{\rCHT}想知道你能得到什麼嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.38,0:56:25.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You get the ice cream, the hot fudge, the banana, and the nuts.\N{\rCHT}你現在先拿到霜淇淋 熱巧克力 香蕉和堅果配料
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.96,0:56:27.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I get the sprinkles, and, yeah,\N{\rCHT}我現在能拿到裝飾糖粒
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.80,0:56:30.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,if this goes through, I get the cherry.\N{\rCHT}如果這事兒最終能成 我能吃到頂上的櫻桃
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.51,0:56:32.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But you get the sundae, Vinnie.\N{\rCHT}但你能吃到聖代冰淇淋 文尼
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.80,0:56:34.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You get the sundae.\N{\rCHT}除了櫻桃 剩下的全是你的
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.93,0:56:39.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I buy that. Thank you.\N{\rCHT}行 我信你 謝謝你解釋
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.81,0:56:41.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So what do you say?\N{\rCHT}那你拿個主意
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.06,0:56:43.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You want me to make you a market? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 想讓我幫你坐莊嗎？- 對
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.02,0:56:47.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take $50 million, Garibaldi IV, BBB.\N{\rCHT}我們買5千萬 加里波底4 3B評級
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.98,0:56:51.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sharpen your pencils. I'll get the paperwork ready.\N{\rCHT}準備好簽字筆吧 我來準備好文書
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.74,0:56:55.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck you, too.\N{\rCHT}媽的
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.20,0:56:58.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!\N{\rCHT}好
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.66,0:57:01.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.\N{\rCHT}這就對了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.79,0:57:05.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man.\N{\rCHT}哦 天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.79,0:57:09.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He has so many numbers, and I always forget\N{\rCHT}他電話號碼太多 我老忘了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.13,0:57:11.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,which one he prefers, because he's very specific.\N{\rCHT}應該打哪個電話 他明確和我說過
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.84,0:57:13.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Start with the first one.\N{\rCHT}就先選第一個吧
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.13,0:57:14.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if it's the first one.\N{\rCHT}不知道對不對
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.47,0:57:15.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just try it.\N{\rCHT}試試吧
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.85,0:57:17.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I... Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.03,0:57:37.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ben Ricker. - Hey, Ben. It's Jamie.\N{\rCHT}- 我是本·裡克特 - 本 你好 我是傑米
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.33,0:57:41.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jamie, you know you're not supposed to use this line.\N{\rCHT}傑米 我告訴過你不要打這個電話
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.66,0:57:44.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Told you.\N{\rCHT}我就知道…
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.29,0:57:48.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's try number two out of 14.\N{\rCHT}好 試試這14個號碼的第2個
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.56,0:58:01.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben Rickert.\N{\rCHT}本·裡克特
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.64,0:58:03.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, why do you do that, man? I mean...\N{\rCHT}本 你這不是自找麻煩嗎？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.73,0:58:06.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a retired trader, okay? No one is listening to your calls.\N{\rCHT}你都退休了好吧 沒人監聽你電話
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.23,0:58:07.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The NSA has a $52 billion budget and the ability\N{\rCHT}國安局有520億的預算
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.02,0:58:09.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,to monitor tens of millions of calls a second.\N{\rCHT}每秒能監聽上千萬個電話
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.48,0:58:11.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You think they're not using it?\N{\rCHT}你以為他們吃閒飯的？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.90,0:58:14.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I promise I will refrain from saying\N{\rCHT}那我保證不會在一句話裡同時說
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.82,0:58:16.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ben Rickert" and "dirty bomb" in the same sent...\N{\rCHT}你的名字和放射髒彈這詞
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.87,0:58:20.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Jesus fucking Christ. - I'm sorry, dude.\N{\rCHT}- 我的天 - 真受不了
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.16,0:58:23.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben Rickert.\N{\rCHT}本·裡克特
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.37,0:58:25.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get a chance to look at what we sent you, Ben?\N{\rCHT}你看到我們發給你的東西了嗎
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.83,0:58:28.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Charlie. I'm here, too.\N{\rCHT}我是查理 我也在旁邊
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.75,0:58:31.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Charlie. Yeah, I did. Hold on.\N{\rCHT}查理 你好 我看了 稍等
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.09,0:58:39.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ben, you still there? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 本 你還聽著嗎 - 嗯
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.18,0:58:42.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be honest, gentlemen.\N{\rCHT}我就直說吧
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.31,0:58:44.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It scared the shit out of me.\N{\rCHT}你倆把我嚇壞了
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.35,0:58:45.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's a good thing, right?\N{\rCHT}那說明這是真東西對吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.81,0:58:48.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That means this Vennett guy's not wrong.\N{\rCHT}這叫傑瑞德的傢伙沒胡說
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.31,0:58:50.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's not.\N{\rCHT}是沒有
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.11,0:58:54.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool.\N{\rCHT}太好了
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.19,0:58:55.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me more about these CDOs.\N{\rCHT}你們對CDO還瞭解什麼
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.86,0:58:59.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. Okay, so, you know, Vennett mentions the CDOs,\N{\rCHT}好的 好的 好的 傑瑞德只是提到了CDO
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.74,0:59:01.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but actually, we took a look\N{\rCHT}我倆實際看了
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.37,0:59:02.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and they're way worse than even he realizes.\N{\rCHT}情況比他想的還糟
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.12,0:59:04.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,These things don't make any sense!\N{\rCHT}資料離譜的像假的一樣
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.62,0:59:05.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't even model them.\N{\rCHT}連預測模型都用不了
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.96,0:59:08.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,These are 100 times bigger than the MBS.\N{\rCHT}打包的CDO比房貸證券規模還要大100倍
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.75,0:59:10.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And 90% AAA-rated.\N{\rCHT}然後有90%還是3A評級？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.42,0:59:12.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes! Exactly! - Over 90%.\N{\rCHT}- 是啊 - 超過90%
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.29,0:59:13.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's incredible.\N{\rCHT}真不敢相信
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.46,0:59:16.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I took a good hard look at the CDOs you want to short.\N{\rCHT}我仔細看了你打算做空的CDO
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.38,0:59:19.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're brilliant. Worthless. Total crap.\N{\rCHT}天才的想法 CDO就是包裝精美的屎
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.47,0:59:22.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jamie. Very good.\N{\rCHT}傑米 厲害厲害
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.72,0:59:26.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What can I say? I'm good at finding shit.\N{\rCHT}怎麼說呢… 我找屎還挺擅長的
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.31,0:59:29.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Ben, we shorted the BB's and the BBB's,\N{\rCHT}本 我們打算做空2B和3B級別的
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.14,0:59:31.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the risk is relatively low.\N{\rCHT}風險也相對小一些
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.31,0:59:33.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Payoff is, like, 25-to-1. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}回報率差不多是25倍
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.32,0:59:38.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, so, why are you calling me? I don't do this anymore.\N{\rCHT}那你們找我幹啥？我洗手不幹了
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.49,0:59:39.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Ben?\N{\rCHT}本 我們…
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.99,0:59:44.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We need you to help us get the ISDA.\N{\rCHT}我們需要你幫忙搞定ISDA協議
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.83,0:59:47.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If we get a hunting license, we can short this crap.\N{\rCHT}有了持槍證 我們就能開幹了
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.00,0:59:50.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And we know you hate Wall Street. We're not asking you to do the trading.\N{\rCHT}我們知道你恨華爾街 所以不會讓你去做交易
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.54,0:59:54.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're simply asking you to help us get a seat\N{\rCHT}只是 請求你… 幫助我們
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.59,0:59:57.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,at the fucking table.\N{\rCHT}能坐到"大亨"席位就行
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.84,0:59:59.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pretty ugly table, guys.\N{\rCHT}那種地方可是烏煙瘴氣的很
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.84,1:00:04.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Ben, the system fucked up in a big, big way here, okay?\N{\rCHT}本 整個系統已經出大亂子了 是不是？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.93,1:00:10.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And somehow we know before anyone else.\N{\rCHT}我們比所有人都先得到了消息
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.35,1:00:13.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know? This is a once-in-a-lifetime deal.\N{\rCHT}知道嗎 這是絕對是千載難逢的機會
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.86,1:00:16.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking.\N{\rCHT}我在考慮
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.95,1:00:23.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I'll call Deutsche Bank.\N{\rCHT}好 我打電話給德意志銀行
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.95,1:00:26.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Ben. Thank you.\N{\rCHT}太感謝你了 本
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.29,1:00:29.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And Bear. What about Bear? They have some reprehensible product.\N{\rCHT}還有貝爾斯登公司 那裡也有些把柄可以抓
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.21,1:00:32.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Bear will trade with anybody.\N{\rCHT}好 貝爾肯定來者不拒
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.67,1:01:23.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I'll see if I can push it through.\N{\rCHT}好了 我看看能不能把材料遞上去
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.51,1:01:25.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Noah. And thank Jared for us.\N{\rCHT}謝謝 諾亞 幫我們謝謝傑瑞德
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.30,1:01:29.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Couldn't we go inside? - Yeah, me, too.\N{\rCHT}- 我們不能進去？- 對的 我也是
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.98,1:02:16.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi. It's Mark. I need to talk to Vinnie right now.\N{\rCHT}是我 馬克 現在就把電話轉給文尼
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.40,1:02:19.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just asking you to explain to us\N{\rCHT}我們就是想讓你們解釋清楚
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.98,1:02:23.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,just how it is that you are fucking us, because what we are seeing...\N{\rCHT}我們看到的和你說的完全不同
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.66,1:02:27.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Morgan Stanley building, fast.\N{\rCHT}快去摩根士丹利大廈
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.95,1:02:31.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we hooked up to the same computer screen?\N{\rCHT}我們螢幕上顯示的東西難道不一樣嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.49,1:02:33.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make any sense.\N{\rCHT}這簡直是胡說八道
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.00,1:02:37.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Vinnie, you there?\N{\rCHT}文尼 能聽見吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.96,1:02:39.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Mark, you there? - Yeah, did you hear?\N{\rCHT}- 馬克 我能聽見 - 你聽說了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.00,1:02:41.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mortgage defaults have gone through the roof.\N{\rCHT}房貸斷供已經破記錄了
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.84,1:02:43.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is anybody jumping off of buildings yet?\N{\rCHT}你那裡房頂有人跳樓嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.38,1:02:45.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they? Subprime mortgage bond prices are up.\N{\rCHT}為什麼要跳？次級貸證券可是在上漲
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.67,1:02:46.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\N{\rCHT}怎麼可能？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.80,1:02:50.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Vennett wants $1.9 million more in collateral by close.\N{\rCHT}傑瑞德讓我們今天再投入190萬的抵押
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.18,1:02:51.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Vennett's asking us to post collateral.\N{\rCHT}傑瑞德讓我們追加抵押
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.56,1:02:52.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is going on?\N{\rCHT}怎麼會這樣？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.06,1:02:55.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know, but Deutsche's on the phone demanding payment.\N{\rCHT}不知道 但德意志銀行電話一直在催
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.10,1:02:56.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Call Vennett. Call that little shit.\N{\rCHT}把傑瑞德給我叫過來 這小畜生
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.02,1:02:58.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Call Vennett. Tell him to get his ass down here.\N{\rCHT}給傑瑞德打電話 讓他快點滾過來
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.06,1:03:00.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So subprime loans go bad,\N{\rCHT}次級房貸斷供越來越多
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.94,1:03:04.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but subprime bonds, which are made up of subprime loans, are more valuable?\N{\rCHT}但是它們組成的房貸證券卻更值錢了？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.23,1:03:06.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. They want another $1.9 million by market close.\N{\rCHT}我也奇怪 他們要今天必須交齊1千9百萬
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.82,1:03:08.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the ratings agencies? Moody's, S&P...\N{\rCHT}信用評級機構呢？穆迪公司？標準普爾？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.03,1:03:11.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Are they downgrading the CDOs and mortgage bonds?\N{\rCHT}他們調低了CDO或房貸證券的評級嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.53,1:03:12.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the ratings agencies at?\N{\rCHT}現在評級什麼樣？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.70,1:03:15.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- They're the fucking same. - No, they're all still AAA.\N{\rCHT}- 還是原封不動 - 沒變 還都是3A評級
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.87,1:03:18.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell? Are you fucking kidding me?\N{\rCHT}見鬼了 他媽的在逗我？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.46,1:03:20.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Those fuckers! Those motherfuckers!\N{\rCHT}這幫混蛋 不要臉的
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.63,1:03:23.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They go public, and all they care about is their bottom line and their shit.\N{\rCHT}他們對外評級以後就鑽到錢眼裡去了
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.67,1:03:25.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mark, that's not all.\N{\rCHT}嘿 馬克 還有事…
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.51,1:03:26.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The Morgan Stanley risk guys are here.\N{\rCHT}摩根士丹利風險部的過來了
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.88,1:03:28.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They called in Kathy Tao.\N{\rCHT}他們找了你老闆
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.34,1:03:30.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're trying to convince her to make us sell our swaps.\N{\rCHT}想說服她賣掉我們的互換
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.55,1:03:32.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, tying up six years of insurance payments\N{\rCHT}他們覺得這些保費肯定是被套牢的買賣
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.89,1:03:35.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in hopes of a housing Armageddon is not prudent in vesting.+\N{\rCHT}等著房地產崩潰是不明智的投資
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.88,1:03:37.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What did Kathy say?\N{\rCHT}老闆怎麼說？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.43,1:03:40.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing yet. She keeps asking if this is one of your crusades.\N{\rCHT}沒表態 她一直問這是不是你的核心投資
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.23,1:03:42.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I want you to walk back in there\N{\rCHT}明白了 你走過去
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.23,1:03:46.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and very calmly, very politely, tell the risk assessors to fuck off.\N{\rCHT}語氣平靜 非常禮貌的 讓這些風險評估師都他媽滾蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.78,1:03:48.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then meet me over at Standard & Poor's.\N{\rCHT}然後過來和我在標準普爾碰頭
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.53,1:03:50.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna talk to Georgia.\N{\rCHT}我們要找喬治亞聊聊
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.11,1:03:51.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Okay.\N{\rCHT}知道了 好的
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.24,1:03:53.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Get that fuck Jared Vennett in this office.\N{\rCHT}把傑瑞德那混蛋叫過來
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.24,1:03:55.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bash his fucking head in.\N{\rCHT}看我不把他腦漿打出來
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.29,1:04:01.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen?\N{\rCHT}各位
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.71,1:04:04.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I spoke with Mark Baum. He says to fuck off.\N{\rCHT}我剛和馬克·鮑姆談過了 他的原話：都他媽滾蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.56,1:04:20.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see a damn thing.\N{\rCHT}我眼睛不好使啊
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.56,1:04:24.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My eye doctor's always busy.\N{\rCHT}我選的眼科醫生總是特別忙
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.86,1:04:26.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I end up taking any appointment they'll give me,\N{\rCHT}只要能預約上我就得去
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.73,1:04:29.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and then the whole morning gets shot to hell!\N{\rCHT}今天上午就這麼廢了
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.24,1:04:31.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So...\N{\rCHT}那麼…
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.24,1:04:33.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All righty,\N{\rCHT}好咧
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.12,1:04:36.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,FrontPoint Partners,\N{\rCHT}前點基金的朋友們
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.16,1:04:39.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,how can Standard & Poor's help you?\N{\rCHT}標準普爾有什麼能幫到你們的嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.62,1:04:40.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we don't understand why\N{\rCHT}我們想弄明白 為什麼
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.96,1:04:43.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the ratings agencies haven't downgraded subprime bonds\N{\rCHT}評級機構 不下調次級貸證券的評級
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.67,1:04:46.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,since the underlying loans are clearly deteriorating.\N{\rCHT}證券包含的房貸 很明顯情況在惡化
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.80,1:04:49.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the delinquency rates do have people worried,\N{\rCHT}斷供率是讓人們擔心了
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.30,1:04:51.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but they're actually within our models.\N{\rCHT}不過數字波動還在我們的合理模型之內
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.17,1:04:53.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- So. .. - Says you.\N{\rCHT}- 那… - 你先說
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.30,1:04:59.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...you're convinced the underlying mortgages in these bonds are solid loans.\N{\rCHT}你確信這些證券裡的房貸是可靠的？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.35,1:05:01.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That is our opinion yeah. - Oh crack the tape!\N{\rCHT}- 這是我們的觀點 - 打開天窗說亮話
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.55,1:05:03.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you looked at the loan-level data?\N{\rCHT}你看過底層房貸的資料嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.61,1:05:04.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- What do you think we do here all day? - I mean, they're giving\N{\rCHT}- 你認為我們工作是什麼？- 現在只要
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.73,1:05:06.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- these loans to anybody with a credit score and a pulse. - Excuse me, sir.\N{\rCHT}- 有信用分 就肯定能拿到房貸 - 打斷一下
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.92,1:05:09.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think we do here all day?\N{\rCHT}你認為我們工作是什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.32,1:05:10.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not sure. That's why we're here.\N{\rCHT}我不明白 要不我們也不會過來
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.44,1:05:11.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what I don't understand...\N{\rCHT}我不明白
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.65,1:05:13.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We check, recheck, recheck again.\N{\rCHT}我們再三反覆核對過了
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.49,1:05:14.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If these mortgage bonds are so stable...\N{\rCHT}如果這些房貸證券這麼穩定可靠
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.87,1:05:16.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps you could check your friend.\N{\rCHT}你先檢查一下你同事吧
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.66,1:05:18.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...have you ever refused to rate...\N{\rCHT}你有沒有拒絕…
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.74,1:05:20.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, that's delusional.\N{\rCHT}做你的夢吧
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.16,1:05:21.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We stand behind them.\N{\rCHT}我們有理由這麼評級
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.37,1:05:22.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Georgia, have you ever refused to rate\N{\rCHT}你有沒有給過這裡任何一個證券
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.04,1:05:26.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,any of these bonds upper tranches AAA?\N{\rCHT}評級低於3A級別？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.42,1:05:28.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we see the paperwork on those deals?\N{\rCHT}我們能看看對應的材料嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.09,1:05:30.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I am under no obligation to share that information\N{\rCHT}我沒有義務給你們看內部資訊
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.17,1:05:31.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,with you, whoever you might be.\N{\rCHT}不管你是誰
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.34,1:05:33.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just answer the question, Georgia.\N{\rCHT}你就回答我的簡單問題 喬治
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.18,1:05:35.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you name one time in the past year\N{\rCHT}給我們個去年低於3A評級的名字
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.22,1:05:36.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,where you checked the tape\N{\rCHT}你去看了實際資料
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.64,1:05:40.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and you didn't give the banks the AAA percentage they wanted?\N{\rCHT}最後也沒有給銀行想要的3A評級
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.10,1:05:44.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't give them the ratings,\N{\rCHT}如果我們不這麼評
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.35,1:05:46.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll go to Moody's, right down the block.\N{\rCHT}人家就去隔壁的穆迪評級了
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.19,1:05:50.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't work with them, they will go to our competitors.\N{\rCHT}我們不配合 那我們的對頭就會搶走客戶的錢
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.19,1:05:54.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Not our fault. Simply the way the world works.\N{\rCHT}這地方就這麼運轉 我們有什麼辦法
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.70,1:06:01.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Holy shit. - Yes, now you see.\N{\rCHT}- 我靠 - 明白了吧
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.25,1:06:04.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I never said that.\N{\rCHT}我什麼都沒說過
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.37,1:06:06.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're selling ratings for fees.\N{\rCHT}你們就是賣信用評級的賺錢機構
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.88,1:06:07.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A ratings shop.\N{\rCHT}信用商店
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.92,1:06:10.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You can afford to make less. Make less.\N{\rCHT}你們不賺這麼多錢也能維持運行啊
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.84,1:06:12.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody said that.\N{\rCHT}沒人這麼要求我
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.80,1:06:14.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And it is not my decision. I have a boss.\N{\rCHT}這不是我能做主的 我有老闆管著
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.05,1:06:17.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Are you kidding me? - No, I am not "kidding you".\N{\rCHT}- 你在逗我？- 我沒空跟你開玩笑
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.31,1:06:21.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the angle you're taking?\N{\rCHT}這就是你的立場？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.60,1:06:25.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, now, anyone who has a boss can't be held responsible\N{\rCHT}這意思是 只要有老闆的人 都不用為
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.23,1:06:26.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,for doing shitty and illegal things.\N{\rCHT}任何圖財害命的勾當負責了
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.73,1:06:28.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you, four?\N{\rCHT}你當自己四歲小孩嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.40,1:06:32.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, lam not four, Mr. Baum. I am not, no.\N{\rCHT}我不是四歲孩子 鮑姆先生 不是不負責
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.78,1:06:36.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I wonder what your incentives might be.\N{\rCHT}我倒奇怪 你們來找我的動機是什麼
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.28,1:06:40.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it maybe in your best interest to have the ratings change? Is it, perhaps?\N{\rCHT}是不是評級變了 對你們有好處啊？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.70,1:06:44.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How many credit default swaps do you own?\N{\rCHT}信用違約互換你們買了多少？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.29,1:06:49.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make me wrong.\N{\rCHT}立場和對錯是兩回事
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.25,1:06:50.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No.\N{\rCHT}錯
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.46,1:06:52.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It just makes you a hypocrite.\N{\rCHT}你倆還裝什麼好人
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.21,1:07:35.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck!\N{\rCHT}媽的
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.30,1:07:36.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mortgage delinquencies went up\N{\rCHT}房貸斷供
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.51,1:07:38.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the CDOs got more valuable. Unbelievable.\N{\rCHT}房貸證券卻更值錢了 真見鬼了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.63,1:07:40.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Unbelievable. - We know. It's completely backwards.\N{\rCHT}- 難以置信 - 是啊 走勢太反常了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.97,1:07:42.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I just called an old friend at Bear.\N{\rCHT}我給貝爾斯登公司的朋友打電話
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.64,1:07:44.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't even know what a CDO is.\N{\rCHT}他連CDO是啥都不知道
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.39,1:07:48.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I just had to wire Bear and Deutsche $70, 000.\N{\rCHT}是啊 我剛給貝爾和德意志匯過去7萬塊錢
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.81,1:07:51.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like two plus two equals\N{\rCHT}這感覺 就好像現在二加二等於…
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.65,1:07:52.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,fish.\N{\rCHT}屎
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.83,1:07:53.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's rigged.\N{\rCHT}有黑幕
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.97,1:07:55.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We bought into a rigged game.\N{\rCHT}我們被帶到溝裡面了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.65,1:07:57.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna lose everything.\N{\rCHT}要是錢賠光了
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.53,1:07:59.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna have to move back in with my mom.\N{\rCHT}我就得回去家裡和老媽在一起
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.53,1:08:01.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't do that.\N{\rCHT}我可不想
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.99,1:08:04.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Well, I got a colonic appointment.\N{\rCHT}好了 我等會還有事兒忙
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.24,1:08:05.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. Hold on, Ben.\N{\rCHT}等一下 別掛電話 本
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.99,1:08:07.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, look.\N{\rCHT}本 聽我說
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.41,1:08:12.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Either the banks are cluelessand they don't know how to value these CDOs,\N{\rCHT}有可能銀行完全不懂CDO是什麼東西 或者
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.25,1:08:17.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,or they're such crooks that the CDOs are worth shit\N{\rCHT}或者他們想用沙子把屎蓋起來
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.42,1:08:19.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and they're hiding it.\N{\rCHT}藏著掖著
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.34,1:08:22.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we should buy more swaps.\N{\rCHT}我覺得我們應該再買更多
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.35,1:08:24.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\N{\rCHT}你說啥？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.47,1:08:26.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Suck it up and pay up, fellas. We made a deal.\N{\rCHT}別廢話 合同上白紙黑字寫得清楚
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.56,1:08:28.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! No!\N{\rCHT}不行 不行
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.68,1:08:30.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fucking kidding me?\N{\rCHT}你小子玩我們嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.19,1:08:32.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious? You think this is a game?\N{\rCHT}還有臉過來 還想著來玩這個遊戲？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.60,1:08:35.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- No.No.No.No.No. - Yeah. Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 不 不 不 - 行 行
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.82,1:08:43.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No! No!\N{\rCHT}不行不行不行
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.62,1:08:45.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, seriously, a colonic once a year.\N{\rCHT}建議你每年灌一次腸來排排毒
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.37,1:08:46.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ass!\N{\rCHT}混蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.45,1:08:49.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And you got a matching little butler boy, you buttfuck!\N{\rCHT}你就是個跑腿的 他媽的
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.13,1:08:54.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Are you done? - I think so, yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 都發洩完了？- 完了…
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.04,1:08:57.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,God! I pulled a muscle in my back from yelling.\N{\rCHT}剛才大聲罵 我都閃腰了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.38,1:09:03.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mortgage defaults have done nothing but go up.\N{\rCHT}房貸斷供率一直在漲
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.05,1:09:07.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet you quote us a higher price on the bonds.\N{\rCHT}你給我們房貸證券的報價還更高了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.10,1:09:10.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Please explain that to me. There's no way that makes sense.\N{\rCHT}你給我解釋清楚 這顯然不科學啊
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.31,1:09:13.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you're marking these swaps appropriately.\N{\rCHT}你的量化方法絕對有問題
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.98,1:09:15.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Why shouldn't we back out of this trade right now?\N{\rCHT}有什麼理由讓我們繼續幹？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.40,1:09:19.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I say when we made this deal\N{\rCHT}我說沒說過 咱們談成買賣的時候
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.93,1:09:21.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that the ratings agencies, the SEC\N{\rCHT}評級機構 美國證券交易委員會
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.90,1:09:24.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the big banks were clueless? Didn't I say that?\N{\rCHT}大銀行們全都不懂？說沒說過？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.49,1:09:25.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes. - Didn't I say it?\N{\rCHT}- 說過沒有？- 有說過的
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.87,1:09:27.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you did. You did.\N{\rCHT}有說過的
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.83,1:09:29.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.\N{\rCHT}閉嘴
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.37,1:09:30.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now their foot's on fire,\N{\rCHT}他們腳都開始著火了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.59,1:09:32.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,they think their steak is done, and you're surprised?\N{\rCHT}心裡卻想著 牛排應該烤熟了 你還覺得奇怪？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.41,1:09:35.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not stupidity. That's fraud.\N{\rCHT}這不是愚蠢 這是詐騙
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.29,1:09:37.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me the difference between stupid and illegal,\N{\rCHT}你跟我說清楚愚蠢和違法的區別
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.09,1:09:39.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'll have my wife's brother arrested.\N{\rCHT}我就去把我小舅子抓起來
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.96,1:09:41.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That was funny.\N{\rCHT}挺好笑的
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.09,1:09:45.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you just don't realize how clueless the system really is.\N{\rCHT}你們還是沒弄明白整個系統有多蠢
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.84,1:09:48.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there's some shady shit going down,\N{\rCHT}我承認 是有一些見不得人的勾當
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.26,1:09:51.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but trust me, it's fueled by stupidity!\N{\rCHT}但相信我 這是愚蠢驅使的
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.81,1:09:54.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at yourselves.\N{\rCHT}看看你們這些人
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.94,1:09:58.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, you pass yourself off as cynical people\N{\rCHT}都覺得自己是敢於懷疑的人
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.48,1:10:00.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but you still have some faith in the system, don't you?\N{\rCHT}可你們還對這幫青天大老爺抱有希望？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.94,1:10:02.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't.\N{\rCHT}我是不抱
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.32,1:10:05.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, except for Vinnie. And who gives a shit?\N{\rCHT}文尼是明白人 誰在乎？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.28,1:10:07.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- No way! - Look...\N{\rCHT}- 不行 - 聽我說
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.12,1:10:10.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Either we're right or we're wrong in a giant, giant way.\N{\rCHT}要麼我們對 要麼我們錯得離譜
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.37,1:10:13.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we're wrong, then we got to find someone to help us get out of this trade.\N{\rCHT}如果真錯了 得找高人給我們點醒才行
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.04,1:10:16.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not feeling remotely confident that we're right.\N{\rCHT}我現在是一點都不覺得我們占理
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.88,1:10:20.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And if we're wrong, who's gonna tell us?\N{\rCHT}萬一咱們錯了 誰來告訴我們？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.38,1:10:23.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Who understands this stuff? It makes no sense!\N{\rCHT}有誰懂？沒人懂
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.26,1:10:28.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we need to go to Vegas.\N{\rCHT}我們應該去拉斯維加斯
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.14,1:10:30.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's in Vegas? - Vegas?\N{\rCHT}- 那兒有什麼？- 去哪兒幹啥
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.39,1:10:32.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell's in Las Vegas?\N{\rCHT}拉斯維加斯又能有什麼東西？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.35,1:10:36.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The American Securitization Forum is there next week.\N{\rCHT}下周那裡召開美國證券化論壇年會
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.65,1:10:39.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Every bond and CDO salesman, subprime lender\N{\rCHT}每個證券 CDO 次級貸
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.15,1:10:41.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and swap trader is gonna be there.\N{\rCHT}倒賣交換的交易員都會去
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.32,1:10:44.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, your bet is against dumb money.\N{\rCHT}我這麼說 你掙的是他們手裡的錢
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.15,1:10:46.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time you find out just how dumb that money really is.\N{\rCHT}是時候去看看人傻錢多是怎麼回事了
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.07,1:10:48.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,God, I hate Vegas.\N{\rCHT}我真不喜歡拉斯維加斯
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.32,1:10:49.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear the food has gotten really good in Vegas.\N{\rCHT}聽說吃的東西特別好
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.82,1:10:51.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They have a Nobu now.\N{\rCHT}那裡也有松久壽司店了
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.41,1:10:52.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you fucking stop it?\N{\rCHT}你能不惦記著吃嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.37,1:11:42.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Any sense? - And if a bond is "rich" it is...\N{\rCHT}- 什麼意思？- 證券"貴"的意思是…
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.38,1:11:45.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I don't know, loaded with assets? -"Rich" just means overpriced.\N{\rCHT}- 我不知道 資產說明什麼 - 只說明證券定價過高
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.55,1:11:47.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't sleep on planes, so I did my homework.\N{\rCHT}飛機上睡不著我就自己準備了一下
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.59,1:11:50.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's focus. What's our goal?\N{\rCHT}咱們集中精神 我們是為了什麼來的？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.09,1:11:52.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,To figure out if this is a deal of a lifetime\N{\rCHT}搞清楚這買賣是千載難逢的機會
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.51,1:11:54.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,or if everyone here knows something we don't\N{\rCHT}還是別人比我們懂得都多
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.39,1:11:56.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and we're gonna get royally screwed.\N{\rCHT}咱們回頭會虧大發了
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.31,1:11:59.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Remember that when you meet with the guys from Bear.\N{\rCHT}和貝爾公司的人接觸的時候 注意你們的目的
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.23,1:12:00.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I set you up with a face-to-face.\N{\rCHT}我給你們安排見面機會
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.06,1:12:02.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Awesome. - Where is that?\N{\rCHT}- 好的 - 地方在哪？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.44,1:12:06.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy shit. Five years ago, Securitization was a loser convention.\N{\rCHT}我的天 5年前這年會還是窮鬼聚會
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.86,1:12:08.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,100, maybe 200 people would show.\N{\rCHT}也就有100到200人出席
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.07,1:12:11.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$500 billion a year later, you get this.\N{\rCHT}產業每年五千億的發展之後 就變成這樣了
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.32,1:12:12.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot of smug-looking people in here, huh?\N{\rCHT}這裡自帶裝逼表情的人還真多
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.03,1:12:16.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like someone hit a pifiata filled with white people who suck at golf.\N{\rCHT}好像暴發戶白人都跑來了
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.58,1:12:18.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, who are all these clowns?\N{\rCHT}都從哪兒冒出來的？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.16,1:12:19.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. I think it looks fun.\N{\rCHT}別抱怨了 肯定很好玩
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.62,1:12:23.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly. Vennett says these are the people we're betting against.\N{\rCHT}查理 傑瑞德說咱們賺的是這些人的錢
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.17,1:12:25.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah, here we go. Here we go. - There he is.\N{\rCHT}- 咱們過去 - 他在那裡
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.13,1:12:26.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Chris, on my left. Chris, on my left.\N{\rCHT}克裡斯 到我左邊去 別擋道
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.34,1:12:28.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Gentlemen.\N{\rCHT}大家好
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.55,1:12:32.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,When do we get a chance to face time with some of these lovely folks?\N{\rCHT}什麼時候能見到你說的那些愛心天使
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.22,1:12:33.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Chris, give him the keycards.\N{\rCHT}克裡斯 把門卡發給他
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.76,1:12:34.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you even know which keycards you're giving out?\N{\rCHT}你還沒搞清楚你要發的哪張門卡
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.06,1:12:36.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're just giving them out? - Thank you.\N{\rCHT}- 就把門卡都發他們了？- 謝謝
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.14,1:12:38.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, how was your travel? How are you? Uneventful?\N{\rCHT}先生們路上還順利嗎？沒什麼事兒
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.93,1:12:40.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Uneventful. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 沒事 - 好吧
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.23,1:12:41.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been here for six hours. I've already been to the gym,\N{\rCHT}我來了6小時了 我已經鍛煉完
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.02,1:12:43.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I had two poached eggs\N{\rCHT}吃了兩個荷包蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.44,1:12:45.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and I played blackjack with Harry Dean Stanton.\N{\rCHT}還和演員哈利·戴恩·斯坦通一起打牌
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.15,1:12:46.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your diary.\N{\rCHT}你記日記還真清楚
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.07,1:12:48.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Face time. I'd like some face time.\N{\rCHT}我想找人見面聊
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.78,1:12:50.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just remember. We're here to gather information.\N{\rCHT}提醒你們記住 我們是來收集資訊的
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.32,1:12:51.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gathering information, okay?\N{\rCHT}我們是收集資訊 知道不？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.82,1:12:54.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not advertising our short position. All right?\N{\rCHT}不要打草驚蛇 好嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.28,1:12:55.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want to spook everybody. Can you do that?\N{\rCHT}別嚇到大夥兒 行不行？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.99,1:12:57.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you got a big mouth, you like to run it.\N{\rCHT}你說話太直 還老是不停嘴
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.62,1:12:59.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you just keep it shut for a few days?\N{\rCHT}這幾天能不能收斂一點？
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.54,1:13:00.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧 好吧
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.66,1:13:02.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, don't worry. We'll play nice.\N{\rCHT}別擔心 我們會好好套話的
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.62,1:13:03.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen.\N{\rCHT}女士們先生們
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.00,1:13:06.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Business is good.\N{\rCHT}商業形勢大好
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.29,1:13:07.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Profits are strong\N{\rCHT}利潤也很高
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.80,1:13:10.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the mortgage continues to be the bedrock\N{\rCHT}房貸還堅持著經濟的
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.80,1:13:13.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,on which this economy is built.\N{\rCHT}中流砥柱作用
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.81,1:13:19.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And, yes, we had to take some losses\N{\rCHT}對 去年我們
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.47,1:13:22.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in our subprime department last year, but those losses\N{\rCHT}在次級貸市場有些損失 不過這些損失
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.85,1:13:25.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,will be contained at only 5%.\N{\rCHT}預計也就最多5%
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.65,1:13:27.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, in our residential sector...\N{\rCHT}接下來說 我們住宅業務板塊的表現
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.86,1:13:29.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, it's not a Q and A.\N{\rCHT}馬克 這不是提問環節
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.15,1:13:30.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...our rollout of those variable rate packages\N{\rCHT}我們推出的可調利率房貸
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.90,1:13:32.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,were gobbled up by the consumers!\N{\rCHT}被一搶而空
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.65,1:13:34.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a question, please.\N{\rCHT}我有個問題
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.66,1:13:39.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, the Q and A is after my statements.\N{\rCHT}先生 本來提問環節是在我陳述之後
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.83,1:13:42.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know what? You seem anxious. How can I help you?\N{\rCHT}但看你這麼著急 需要我回答什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.33,1:13:44.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thank you. How are you? - Fine, thank you.\N{\rCHT}- 現在就問吧 你好啊 - 你好 謝謝
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.33,1:13:47.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you say that it is a possibility\N{\rCHT}你覺得… 有沒有這個可能性
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.54,1:13:52.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,or a probability that subprime losses stop at 5%?\N{\rCHT}或者說必然性次級貸的損失最多升到5%封頂？
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.38,1:13:53.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.55,1:13:58.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I would say it is a very strong probability, indeed.\N{\rCHT}我覺得這簡直是必然的 是的
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.85,1:14:01.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So back to the residential sector.\N{\rCHT}再回到住宅部分
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.52,1:14:03.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,When we rolled out the new variable rates package...\N{\rCHT}我們推出可調利率…
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.69,1:14:05.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.\N{\rCHT}我還沒問完
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.69,1:14:08.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.\N{\rCHT}這位先生
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.86,1:14:12.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Zero! Zero!\N{\rCHT}零 零
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.36,1:14:15.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a 0% chance\N{\rCHT}可能性為零
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.20,1:14:18.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that your subprime losses will stop at 5%.\N{\rCHT}次級貸止損到5%的可能性為
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.08,1:14:20.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Zero.\N{\rCHT}零
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.24,1:14:21.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.\N{\rCHT}抱歉
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.87,1:14:22.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to take this.\N{\rCHT}我得接這個電話了
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.92,1:14:24.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He must be from Bank of America.\N{\rCHT}你一定來自眼紅我們的美國銀行吧
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.98,1:14:29.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not doing anything right now.\N{\rCHT}我現在什麼都沒幹
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.42,1:14:30.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,As I was saying, our residential department...\N{\rCHT}我正說到住宅部分
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.05,1:14:32.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How are the kids?\N{\rCHT}孩子們都還好嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.34,1:14:34.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...consumers reacted to our packages...\N{\rCHT}客戶對我們的房貸產品反響…
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.80,1:14:36.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark Baum really did that.\N{\rCHT}馬克真的這麼做了
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.55,1:14:37.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,When we were in Vegas, he did that.\N{\rCHT}他來拉斯維加斯真敢這麼做
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.89,1:14:40.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that, he took the call.\N{\rCHT}敢這麼說 還接電話走人了
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.51,1:14:42.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you see what I had to deal with?\N{\rCHT}明白我有多費心了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.90,1:14:58.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the Beretta... Meh.\N{\rCHT}伯萊塔手槍 呃
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.11,1:15:00.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But this Uzi is fucking awesome!\N{\rCHT}這烏茲微沖真是爽啊
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.41,1:15:02.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I need this CDO machine to run for another two years.\N{\rCHT}只要讓CDO再轉上兩年
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.08,1:15:06.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I'm rich as fuck and I got my house in Aspen.\N{\rCHT}我就能富的流油 在滑雪勝地買房了
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.41,1:15:11.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But do you have any concerns about the performance of the underlying securitizations?\N{\rCHT}你對證券化的資產表現不擔心嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.38,1:15:13.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy to see that delinquencies\N{\rCHT}違約的消息一直有
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.25,1:15:16.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and default rates are on the rise right now.\N{\rCHT}斷供率又在增長了
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.22,1:15:18.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you please stop being such a buzzkill, dude?\N{\rCHT}你倆怎麼老潑冷水 有意思嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.76,1:15:21.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't bring you out here to talk about work, bro.\N{\rCHT}帶你們來放鬆 不是再來聊工作的 老兄
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.39,1:15:22.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you bring us out here?\N{\rCHT}你為什麼帶我們過來
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.93,1:15:26.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we need to be able to expense the ammo to a client.\N{\rCHT}因為我們必須讓客戶給彈藥買單
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.23,1:15:29.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go shoot some terrorists. Watch how it's done, boys!\N{\rCHT}來繼續射擊恐怖分子吧 你們看著點
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.44,1:15:32.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- These guys are morons. - Fucking tool.\N{\rCHT}- 這是一群白癡 - 他媽的什麼東西
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.77,1:15:33.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,These guys are morons.\N{\rCHT}真是個棒槌
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.94,1:15:37.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fuck, yes! Boom! - Yeah, man!\N{\rCHT}- 真他媽爽 炸啊 - 爽啊
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.49,1:15:39.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to be buying up every swap we can get our hands on here.\N{\rCHT}我們所有餘錢都應該買互換
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.95,1:15:42.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hold on, okay? Hold on.\N{\rCHT}先別急 別急
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.33,1:15:44.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother's ex-girlfriend works for the SEC.\N{\rCHT}我哥哥的前女友在證券交易委員會工作
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.74,1:15:46.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,She just told me she's in town, okay?\N{\rCHT}她說她也在城裡 我去聊聊
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.66,1:15:48.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if we're missing something, maybe she can tell me.\N{\rCHT}如果有些內幕消息我們不知道
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.92,1:15:50.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, give me some insight.\N{\rCHT}她是最有可能透露給我們的人
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.63,1:15:52.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In the meantime, you go to the main floor\N{\rCHT}你這邊先去一樓
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.46,1:15:54.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and price some swaps.\N{\rCHT}再買點互換
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.63,1:15:58.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, actually, we're about to invest in housing bonds, and...\N{\rCHT}有個事兒 我們想要投資房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.72,1:16:01.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering if the SEC is worried about them at all.\N{\rCHT}我想問問證券交易委員會的態度
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.47,1:16:04.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're not allowed to tell me specifics, but just generally.\N{\rCHT}我知道你不能透露具體內容 但你可以說說大概態度
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.31,1:16:06.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't investigate mortgage bonds.\N{\rCHT}我們不去調查房產證券
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.60,1:16:09.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth is, since we got our budget cut, we don't investigate much.\N{\rCHT}實際上 我們預算減了以後 就不怎麼調查了
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.98,1:16:14.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Then why are you here? I thought... - I'm not here for the SEC.\N{\rCHT}- 那你開會不是來調查的嗎？- 我又不是以證交會員工身份過來的
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.02,1:16:16.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here on my own dime.\N{\rCHT}我自己花錢來的
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.65,1:16:20.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm floating my resume to some big banks.\N{\rCHT}正給各大銀行投簡歷呢
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.95,1:16:22.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How's your brother, by the way?\N{\rCHT}你哥還好嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.62,1:16:24.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you floating your resume to big banks?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼能把簡歷遞給大銀行呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.58,1:16:27.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you're supposed to be the ones, you know, policing the big banks.\N{\rCHT}你不是應該監管大銀行嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.50,1:16:28.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Grow up, Jamie.\N{\rCHT}你幾歲了 傑米
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.00,1:16:32.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be some kind of law against working for a financial institution\N{\rCHT}肯定有法律規定你們不能…
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.83,1:16:36.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,right after you've been working in financial regulation, right?\N{\rCHT}馬上從監管跳到被監管的地方
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.13,1:16:38.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No.\N{\rCHT}沒有沒有啊
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.72,1:16:41.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Dougie!\N{\rCHT}嘿 道奇
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.68,1:16:45.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Come over here. What are you doing at Caesars?\N{\rCHT}快過來 你怎麼也來凱撒宮了
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.72,1:16:47.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He's at Goldman.\N{\rCHT}他在高盛工作
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.85,1:16:48.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,See you.\N{\rCHT}回頭見
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.98,1:16:54.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We can do BBB-level swaps at 500 basis points. Maybe.\N{\rCHT}我們應該能做5%的3B評分互換
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.11,1:16:57.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pricing the swaps like the bond is gonna collapse\N{\rCHT}你們互換價格這麼高 好像證券要跌破價一樣
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.98,1:17:00.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,even though the bond value's going up? Really?\N{\rCHT}雖然現在證券價格還在上升？你確定嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.90,1:17:01.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sign of the times.\N{\rCHT}這是變革的年代
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.07,1:17:03.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is going on?\N{\rCHT}搞不懂究竟是怎麼回事啊
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.96,1:18:05.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Lewis, can you come in early tomorrow, please?\N{\rCHT}路易斯 你能明天早點兒過來嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.84,1:18:08.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to unload the AIG and Countrywide\N{\rCHT}我得減持美國國際集團 國家銀行
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.22,1:18:09.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and Freddie Mac positions\N{\rCHT}聯邦住房抵押貸款公司
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.76,1:18:12.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,so that we can afford the premiums on the...\N{\rCHT}這樣才能填上資金缺口
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.52,1:18:16.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...core mortgage shorts on the swaps.\N{\rCHT}核心做空的保費還差一些
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.90,1:18:18.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem, Dr. Burry.\N{\rCHT}沒問題 巴里博士
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.44,1:18:21.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Burry?\N{\rCHT}巴里博士
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.20,1:18:26.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If the investors withdraw,\N{\rCHT}要是投資者撤資
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.32,1:18:29.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,what's going to happen here? Are we done?\N{\rCHT}咱們接下來會怎麼樣？我們就完了？
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.20,1:18:31.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I don't know.\N{\rCHT}說實話 我也不知道
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.79,1:18:41.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The bonds aren't going down.\N{\rCHT}證券一直不下跌
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.30,1:18:44.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They won't move. It's possible\N{\rCHT}一動不動 很有可能
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.38,1:18:49.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that we are in a completely fraudulent system.\N{\rCHT}整個金融系統都在欺詐
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.39,1:18:54.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Or... You're wrong.\N{\rCHT}或者 是你 錯了
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.81,1:18:59.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.\N{\rCHT}是有可能
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.65,1:19:04.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible I'm wrong. I just don't know how.\N{\rCHT}有這個可能 可我找不出我錯在哪裡
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.37,1:19:13.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess when someone's wrong, they never...\N{\rCHT}我估計別人犯了錯 也不知道
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.91,1:19:16.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They never know how.\N{\rCHT}錯在哪裡吧
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.46,1:19:22.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- See you in the morning. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 早上見吧 - 好
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.46,1:19:26.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Bear upped their prices.\N{\rCHT}貝爾也把價格提高了
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.05,1:19:29.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And they keep calling us Brownhole.\N{\rCHT}管我們棕地基金叫屎洞基金
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.64,1:19:31.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't have the money or the reputation.\N{\rCHT}你們沒錢沒名聲 他們瞧不起也正常
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.35,1:19:32.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take it personally.\N{\rCHT}別往心裡去
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.81,1:19:34.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I have the strip club in me tonight.\N{\rCHT}估計今晚我沒心情去看脫衣舞了
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.18,1:19:37.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just gonna get some ginger ale and watch some pay-per-view.\N{\rCHT}喝點酒去 晚上看些付費A片
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.94,1:19:40.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll book us some flights out for the morning.\N{\rCHT}訂好明早的機票就行了
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.73,1:19:44.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A deal. We need a deal, right? A deal.\N{\rCHT}交易… 我們需要做成一筆交易
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.44,1:19:46.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We need a deal we can afford.\N{\rCHT}我們得做一個能承受的
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.36,1:19:48.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We need a deal that they're not gonna refuse.\N{\rCHT}並且對方肯定不會拒絕的
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.74,1:19:52.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So... What can we do? We can...\N{\rCHT}那 我們怎麼辦呢…
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.37,1:19:56.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The AA tranches. What if we bet against the AA tranches?\N{\rCHT}2A評級的怎麼樣？我們壓注2A評級的證券
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.37,1:19:57.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's not gonna take that bet?\N{\rCHT}誰會拒絕這種賭注？
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.41,1:20:01.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We know they say they're 95% AAA-rated,\N{\rCHT}他們說95%都是3A級別的
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.42,1:20:03.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but in reality they're more like 25%.\N{\rCHT}其實頂多才有25%
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.50,1:20:05.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them are 0%!\N{\rCHT}剩下的都是垃圾證券
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.01,1:20:08.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We also know that if the bottom tranches fail at over 8%,\N{\rCHT}我們也知道如果最差評級的證券 有超過8%作廢
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.72,1:20:09.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the upper tranches are affected.\N{\rCHT}就會導致最上面的證券
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.97,1:20:11.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They go to zero.\N{\rCHT}也跟著雪崩
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.43,1:20:14.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet you right now that those AA's are actually like B's.\N{\rCHT}所以這些2A級別 頂多就是B級
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.85,1:20:17.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I rarely ever say these words, but I think Charlie's right.\N{\rCHT}我很少這麼說 不過這回查理是對的
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.27,1:20:19.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Ben.\N{\rCHT}你看 本
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.60,1:20:23.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The payoff\N{\rCHT}回報率…
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.52,1:20:24.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,is 200 to 1.\N{\rCHT}是200比1
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.02,1:20:27.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're all taking the ratings at face value.\N{\rCHT}但他們是根據現在評級來定價
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.19,1:20:30.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So they're charging pennies on the dollar a bet against the AA's.\N{\rCHT}所以低風險2A的保費很低
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.20,1:20:35.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I start thinking you guys are clowns...\N{\rCHT}我剛開始覺得你倆是笨蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.12,1:20:37.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No one on the planet's betting against AA's.\N{\rCHT}地球人都不會去做空2A級別
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.70,1:20:40.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The banks will think we're either high or having a stroke.\N{\rCHT}銀行會認為我們嗑藥了 或者中風了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.71,1:20:43.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll take every dime we have to offer.\N{\rCHT}他們會大方接受我們的所有提議
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.63,1:20:46.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Kinda brilliant.\N{\rCHT}絕妙的主意
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.76,1:20:50.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what we did that no one else thought of.\N{\rCHT}這個點子 只有我們想到了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.93,1:20:53.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even Baum or Burry thought to short the AA's.\N{\rCHT}連馬克和邁克爾都沒有做空2A
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.93,1:20:55.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But we did.\N{\rCHT}但我們做了
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.39,1:20:56.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Little Brownhole Capital.\N{\rCHT}我們這個小不點屎洞基金
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.27,1:21:02.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're interested in shorting some of the AA tranche of CDOs.\N{\rCHT}我們想做空一些2A級的CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.27,1:21:04.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, guys, what's the angle?\N{\rCHT}直說吧 你倆在打什麼主意？
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.15,1:21:06.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, got no angle. We're new to this. We're just excited.\N{\rCHT}我們沒其他意思 新手嘛 很想拿這個試手
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.57,1:21:10.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to do $15 million in swaps on the AA tranche.\N{\rCHT}我們想買1千5百萬互換 做空2A級
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.74,1:21:11.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand.\N{\rCHT}我是搞不懂你們
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.90,1:21:14.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You can buy as much AA tranche as you want.\N{\rCHT}你倆願意買多少就買多少
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.74,1:21:18.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$40 million against the AA.\N{\rCHT}那就4千萬做空2A吧
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.95,1:21:21.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, I will sell you as much as you want.\N{\rCHT}哥們 你願意買多少我都賣給你
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.46,1:21:23.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You understand perfectly, Bob. You want the deal?\N{\rCHT}我知道我在買啥 你想賣嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.84,1:21:27.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's cool. That's all right with me.\N{\rCHT}好啊 我沒問題
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.05,1:21:31.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleasure.\N{\rCHT}他走了
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.47,1:21:41.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do that. Stop. Stop.\N{\rCHT}別這樣 快停下來
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.10,1:21:43.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Stop that. - Charlie.\N{\rCHT}- 別鬧了 - 查理
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.02,1:21:45.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! Stop.\N{\rCHT}停下來 你倆
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.90,1:21:48.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\N{\rCHT}怎麼了
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.40,1:21:51.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what you just did?\N{\rCHT}知道你們剛剛做了什麼事嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.19,1:21:53.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. We just made the deal of our lifetimes!\N{\rCHT}我倆做成了一輩子一遇的買賣啊
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.95,1:21:55.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We should celebrate.\N{\rCHT}應該慶祝
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.20,1:21:57.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You just bet against the American economy.\N{\rCHT}你倆在賭未來美國經濟崩潰
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.20,1:21:58.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck, yeah, we did!\N{\rCHT}是啊 沒錯
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.78,1:22:00.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fuck, yeah! - Which means...\N{\rCHT}- 這意味著 - 太棒了
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.83,1:22:03.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means if we're right...\N{\rCHT}這意味著 如果我們賭對了
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.54,1:22:07.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're right, people lose homes. People lose jobs.\N{\rCHT}如果我們是對的 人們會無家可歸 大批人會失業
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.00,1:22:11.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People lose retirement savings. People lose pensions.\N{\rCHT}大家沒了退休存款 養老錢都沒了
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.30,1:22:12.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what I hate about fucking banking?\N{\rCHT}我最討厭這行的就是這一點
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.55,1:22:14.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It reduces people to numbers. Here's a number.\N{\rCHT}把人化為數位 告訴你個數位
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.18,1:22:17.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Every 1% unemployment goes up, 40, 000 people die. Did you know that?\N{\rCHT}失業率上升1% 死亡人數會增加4萬人 明白嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.09,1:22:18.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. - Did you know that?\N{\rCHT}- 不 - 知不知道？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.68,1:22:20.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't know that.\N{\rCHT}不 我們不瞭解
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.72,1:22:23.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We were just excited.\N{\rCHT}我們就是有點興奮
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.81,1:22:27.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just don't fucking dance.\N{\rCHT}還跳舞就太過分了
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.48,1:22:30.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- All right. - Where are you going?\N{\rCHT}- 好吧 - 你要去哪
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.70,1:22:36.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, I just got really scared.\N{\rCHT}我心裡有點發毛了
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.41,1:22:40.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, great show today.\N{\rCHT}今天表現挺好嘛
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.41,1:22:41.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You were terrific. - Thank you.\N{\rCHT}- 簡直好極了- 謝謝
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.95,1:22:43.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Your big mouth was a revelation.\N{\rCHT}你嘴不嚴實還真是我出乎意料
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.66,1:22:45.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate that.\N{\rCHT}理解萬歲
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.50,1:22:47.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You worried you and your swaps are getting played?\N{\rCHT}你們擔心有人暗箱操作？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.33,1:22:50.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this is an opportunity for you to meet who you're betting against.\N{\rCHT}現在這個機會 讓你們去看看對手是誰
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.54,1:22:52.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to get too righteous and listen a little.\N{\rCHT}別覺得自己正義 就不聽不進他的話
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.42,1:22:53.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, fine. Who is this guy?\N{\rCHT}好吧 這人是誰？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.92,1:22:55.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A real solid-gold asshole.\N{\rCHT}24K級的混蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.76,1:22:58.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm a CDO manager. - A "CDO manager"?\N{\rCHT}- 我是CDO經理 - 還有這個職位？
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.09,1:22:59.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, at Harding Advisors.\N{\rCHT}對啊 在哈丁顧問公司就有
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.10,1:23:03.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't realize that there was anything to manage with CDOs.\N{\rCHT}我從沒想過CDO還有什麼要管的
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.94,1:23:08.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We select the securities that go into the CDO portfolio\N{\rCHT}我們篩選進入CDO投資組合的證券
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.56,1:23:09.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and monitor the assets.\N{\rCHT}監控背後的資產情況
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.02,1:23:11.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I do most of Merrill Lynch's CDOs.\N{\rCHT}我主要做美林證券的CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.90,1:23:14.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you represent the investors or Merrill Lynch?\N{\rCHT}你是代表投資人還是美林？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.94,1:23:17.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- The investors. - You do.\N{\rCHT}- 投資人啊 - 你啊
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.20,1:23:18.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah. - But...\N{\rCHT}- 是的 - 可是…
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.74,1:23:20.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Merrill Lynch isn't gonna send you any customers\N{\rCHT}美林不可能白白送客戶給你
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.70,1:23:24.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,unless you put Merrill Lynch's bonds in your CDO.\N{\rCHT}除非你把美林也包含進CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.37,1:23:28.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Good question. Let's just say Merrill and I have...\N{\rCHT}問得好 你可以假設 美林和我
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.71,1:23:30.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a good relationship.\N{\rCHT}我們關係不錯
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.92,1:23:33.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a good relationship with Merrill Lynch.\N{\rCHT}你和美林證券關係不錯？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.21,1:23:34.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been doing business together for a long time.\N{\rCHT}我們一起做買賣
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.96,1:23:37.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And so the CDOs that you create\N{\rCHT}所以你選出的這些CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.55,1:23:41.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,are of the highest quality and the highest value.\N{\rCHT}都是最高品質的最有價值的
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.55,1:23:43.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Absolutely. Yep. - Absolutely.\N{\rCHT}- 那是當然 - 那是當然…
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.56,1:23:47.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you at all concerned about the rising default rates?\N{\rCHT}你不擔心正在上升的斷供率嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.06,1:23:52.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume no risk for these products myself, Mark.\N{\rCHT}我個人不覺得CDO有風險
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.90,1:23:56.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.65,1:24:00.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So let me get this straight. The bank calls you up.\N{\rCHT}那我直說吧 銀行聯繫你
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.41,1:24:02.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They give you the bonds they want to sell.\N{\rCHT}讓你幫忙賣他們的證券
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.03,1:24:04.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They give you clients,\N{\rCHT}再送給你客戶
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.45,1:24:06.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,they give you money to run your business.\N{\rCHT}給你錢讓你運行公司
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.91,1:24:08.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Give you fat fees for doing so.\N{\rCHT}提成也少不了你的
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.71,1:24:10.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But you represent the investors?\N{\rCHT}你居然還代表投資者？
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.25,1:24:14.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Is that right? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 你是這個邏輯嗎？- 是啊
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.55,1:24:16.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But we're not in the Merrill Lynch building.\N{\rCHT}但我不在美林大廈裡工作
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.09,1:24:17.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay. Where are you? - We're in New Jersey.\N{\rCHT}- 那你在哪 - 我在新澤西
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.68,1:24:19.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're 20 minutes away.\N{\rCHT}開車20分鐘就到了
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.28,1:24:21.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, five if you use a helicopter.\N{\rCHT}5分鐘就行了 如果你坐直升飛機
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.72,1:24:26.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's funny, huh? - That's hilarious.\N{\rCHT}- 挺好玩吧 - 真是好玩
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.35,1:24:30.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, boy.\N{\rCHT}不好
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.77,1:24:32.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Your boss is about to explode.\N{\rCHT}你老闆要發作了
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.06,1:24:34.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's too curious to explode.\N{\rCHT}他太想搞明白了 發作不了
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.77,1:24:36.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Say that again.\N{\rCHT}等等 你再解釋一下
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.32,1:24:38.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,CDO "A" has parts of CDO\N{\rCHT}兩個CDO A包含著B的一部分
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.53,1:24:40.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And CDO "B" has parts of CDO\N{\rCHT}然後B也包含A一部分
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.53,1:24:42.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But then they both get put inside CDO\N{\rCHT}然後AB被放到C裡面
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.87,1:24:44.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that one's called CDO squared.\N{\rCHT}對 這就是CDO平方
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.70,1:24:46.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A CDO Of a CDO.\N{\rCHT}CDO的CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.20,1:24:48.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right?\N{\rCHT}明白？
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.37,1:24:50.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's CDOs made up of the opposite side\N{\rCHT}CDO還能包含你
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.41,1:24:51.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,of the bet you made with your swaps.\N{\rCHT}互換押注剩下的部分
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.21,1:24:54.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We call them synthetic CDOs.\N{\rCHT}我們叫它 合成CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.63,1:24:56.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say? -Synthetic CDOs.\N{\rCHT}你說啥？合成CDO？
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.88,1:25:00.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That is fucking crazy. -It's not. It's awesome.\N{\rCHT}- 真是亂套了 - 沒有亂 這很賺錢
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.80,1:25:05.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,His face is starting to boil. He looks like the bad guy from Dune.\N{\rCHT}他臉都氣紅了 像槍戰遊戲裡的壞蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.39,1:25:11.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's say\N{\rCHT}那我們假設
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.81,1:25:15.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,you have a pool of $50 million in subprime loans.\N{\rCHT}你有5千萬美元的次級貸
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.48,1:25:18.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How much money could be out there betting on it,\N{\rCHT}那賭在上面的錢 能有多少？
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.15,1:25:20.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in your synthetic CDOs and swaps\N{\rCHT}在你的合成CDO和互換裡
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.03,1:25:22.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,right now, tonight?\N{\rCHT}就按今晚的行情？
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.70,1:25:25.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, $50 million...\N{\rCHT}5千萬的次級貸…
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.33,1:25:28.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- A billion dollars. - What?\N{\rCHT}- 10億美元吧 - 啥？
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.50,1:25:31.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If the mortgage bonds that Michael Burry discovered\N{\rCHT}如果邁克爾最早發現的房貸證券
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.50,1:25:32.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,were the match...\N{\rCHT}是火柴的話
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.25,1:25:38.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How much bigger is the market for insuring mortgage bonds than actual mortgages?\N{\rCHT}房貸市場衍生出的證券規模有多大
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.38,1:25:40.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,About 20 times.\N{\rCHT}大概20倍吧
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.71,1:25:42.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If the mortgage bonds were the match\N{\rCHT}如果房貸證券是火柴
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.88,1:25:45.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and the CDOs were the kerosene-soaked rags,\N{\rCHT}那CDO就是煤油弄濕的破布
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.68,1:25:47.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,then the synthetic CDO was the atomic bomb\N{\rCHT}而合成CDO 就是原子彈
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.81,1:25:50.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,with the drunk President holding his finger over the button.\N{\rCHT}啟動按鈕被一個酒鬼總統把持著
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.85,1:25:53.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It was at that moment in that dumb restaurant\N{\rCHT}這個時刻 在這破餐館
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.19,1:25:56.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,with that stupid look on his face that Mark Baum realized\N{\rCHT}馬克表情像傻了一樣 他頭一次意識到
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.44,1:25:58.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that the whole world economy might collapse.\N{\rCHT}整個世界經濟可能要崩潰了
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.49,1:26:04.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I know what you're thinking.\N{\rCHT}我知道你們在想什麼
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.49,1:26:06.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"What the fuck is a synthetic CDO?"\N{\rCHT}合成CDO又是什麼鬼
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.20,1:26:12.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, here's Dr. Richard Thaler, father of behavioral economics\N{\rCHT}好 讓行為經濟學之父塞勒博士
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.91,1:26:15.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and Selena Gomez to explain.\N{\rCHT}和塞琳娜解釋一下
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.88,1:26:19.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. So here's how a synthetic CDO works.\N{\rCHT}合成CDO是這麼回事
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.13,1:26:22.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say I bet $10 million on a blackjack hand.\N{\rCHT}就說我賭1千萬在21點牌局的這手上
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.09,1:26:24.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$10 million because this hand is meant to represent\N{\rCHT}1千萬 大概就是一個
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.97,1:26:27.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,a single mortgage bond.\N{\rCHT}房貸證券的規模
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.18,1:26:33.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Selena has a pretty good hand here, showing 18.\N{\rCHT}好的 塞琳娜這手牌不錯
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.73,1:26:34.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dealer showing seven.\N{\rCHT}兩張明牌18點 莊家7點
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.81,1:26:36.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a really good hand for Selena.\N{\rCHT}塞琳娜拿到了一手好牌
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.94,1:26:38.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Good odds. In fact, her chances of winning\N{\rCHT}贏面大 實際這手牌贏的概率
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.44,1:26:40.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,this hand are 87%.\N{\rCHT}是87%
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.90,1:26:44.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, my odds are good. I'm on a winning streak.\N{\rCHT}就是說我很可能贏了現在我勢頭正旺
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.36,1:26:47.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody in this place wants to get in on the action.\N{\rCHT}大夥也想要趁勢賺錢
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.11,1:26:48.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How could I lose, right?\N{\rCHT}我怎麼會輸呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.57,1:26:50.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, this is a classic error.\N{\rCHT}這是個經典的思維缺陷
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.16,1:26:53.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In basketball it's called the Hot Hand Fallacy.\N{\rCHT}籃球裡面叫"熱手謬誤"
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.20,1:26:55.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A player makes a bunch of shots in a row.\N{\rCHT}一個人連續投籃進了
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.83,1:26:58.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People are sure they're gonna make the next one.\N{\rCHT}大夥會覺得下一次也會進
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.21,1:27:00.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People think that whatever's happening now\N{\rCHT}人們認為 發生過的事情
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.25,1:27:03.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,is gonna continue to happen into the future.\N{\rCHT}在以後也會繼續出現
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.09,1:27:06.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,During the real estate boom, markets were going up and up\N{\rCHT}在房地產泡沫時期房價一直在漲啊漲
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.51,1:27:08.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and people thought they would never go down.\N{\rCHT}人們會覺得房價不可能跌下來
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.26,1:27:10.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So people who are watching and think that I won't lose\N{\rCHT}旁觀的人心想 賭邊注的話
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.89,1:27:12.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,will make a side bet.\N{\rCHT}也不會輸
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.43,1:27:14.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, this is the first synthetic CDO.\N{\rCHT}這就是第一個合成CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.77,1:27:16.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I love Selena Gomez.\N{\rCHT}我喜歡塞琳娜
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.44,1:27:17.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you $50 million she wins.\N{\rCHT}我和你賭1千5百萬 賭她贏
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.02,1:27:20.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll give you 3-to-1 odds.\N{\rCHT}賠率設3：1
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.19,1:27:24.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,3-to-1 odds? Okay, I'll take that bet.\N{\rCHT}3：1？好 我和你賭
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.04,1:27:27.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, somebody else is gonna want to make a bet\N{\rCHT}現在 旁邊還有人對他倆的賭局
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.46,1:27:29.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,on the outcome of their bet.\N{\rCHT}再對賭
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.19,1:27:30.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bet you 50 million she wins.\N{\rCHT}五千萬賭她贏
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.03,1:27:32.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That will lead to synthetic CDO number two.\N{\rCHT}形成了第二個合成CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.08,1:27:36.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I bet you $200 million that lady in the glasses\N{\rCHT}我和你賭2億 賭那個戴眼鏡的女士
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.41,1:27:37.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,wins that bet.\N{\rCHT}贏
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.08,1:27:41.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,She probably will win. So I want a great payoff.\N{\rCHT}她是贏面很大所以我很可能大賺一筆
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.34,1:27:43.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- How about 20-to-1? - Deal.\N{\rCHT}- 我就來賠率20：1吧 - 成交
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.00,1:27:48.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And this will go on and on with more and more synthetic CDOs.\N{\rCHT}這樣的過程循環往復 合成CDO越來越多
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.38,1:27:52.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And we can transform an original $10 million investment\N{\rCHT}原始的1千萬投資
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.60,1:27:54.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,into billions of dollars.\N{\rCHT}滾雪球成為了幾十億的賭注
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.43,1:27:56.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You Okay?\N{\rCHT}你沒事吧
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.19,1:27:59.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No.\N{\rCHT}不舒服
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.56,1:28:02.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I actually feel pretty sick.\N{\rCHT}我感覺很噁心
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.61,1:28:09.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm going to leave.\N{\rCHT}我得先走了
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.12,1:28:13.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'm a parasite, don't you, Mr. Baum?\N{\rCHT}馬克 你心裡認為我就是寄生蟲是吧
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.08,1:28:18.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But, apparently, society values me very much.\N{\rCHT}可社會待見我這樣的人非常待見
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.04,1:28:20.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, let's do this.\N{\rCHT}不信的話 咱們算算
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.84,1:28:25.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you how much I'm worth.\N{\rCHT}我先告訴你我現在身價多少
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.38,1:28:27.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You tell me how much you're worth.\N{\rCHT}你再告訴我你身價多少
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.09,1:28:34.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,God, you are an incredibly big piece of shit.\N{\rCHT}你還真是個渾身銅臭味的混蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.94,1:28:41.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Short everything that guy has touched.\N{\rCHT}買空他做的所有CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.90,1:28:43.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I want half a billion more in swaps.\N{\rCHT}再投入5個億
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.06,1:28:46.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure about that? The collateral calls could bankrupt you.\N{\rCHT}你確定嗎？萬一不行你就破產了
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.40,1:28:48.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah. Yeah. - Where are you going?\N{\rCHT}- 我確定 - 你要去哪兒
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.44,1:28:51.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I am going to try to find moral redemption\N{\rCHT}我得去輪盤賭那裡恢復一下
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.57,1:28:53.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,at the roulette table.\N{\rCHT}粉碎的三觀
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.60,1:29:58.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, hey!\N{\rCHT}嘿 嘿 嘿
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.06,1:30:04.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Things are worse than I thought.\N{\rCHT}情況比我設想的還要糟
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.65,1:30:08.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I honestly think the economy might collapse.\N{\rCHT}這次我真覺得經濟要崩潰了
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.98,1:30:13.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But you've been saying that the system's broken for years, Mark. So...\N{\rCHT}你這麼說都說了幾年了 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.74,1:30:15.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so shocked?\N{\rCHT}這次是怎麼了
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.16,1:30:21.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more twisted than I could have imagined.\N{\rCHT}我再挖空心思 也想不到裡面這麼黑
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.66,1:30:23.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You love to be the virtuous one.\N{\rCHT}你總是對自己有很高的道德要求
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.00,1:30:25.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a banker. I'm a part of it.\N{\rCHT}我做這行 在這個染缸裡
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.67,1:30:27.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You always have, Mark. Like you're untainted.\N{\rCHT}你總是這樣 馬克 不想沾染髒東西
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.04,1:30:31.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It changed me. It changed me into a person\N{\rCHT}我也被改變了 我變成了
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.09,1:30:33.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,who is not able to reach out to someone...\N{\rCHT}再也不能和別人交心的人
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.01,1:30:35.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He was in pain. My brother was in real pain.\N{\rCHT}我兄弟當時很痛苦 真的很痛苦
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.51,1:30:38.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no perfect way to help.\N{\rCHT}沒有十全十美的辦法來幫他
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.85,1:30:44.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's sad. It's scary.\N{\rCHT}難受就說出來
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.44,1:30:47.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So stop trying to fix the world.\N{\rCHT}停下來別想著拯救世界了
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.69,1:30:48.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me...\N{\rCHT}他對說我
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.86,1:30:50.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not a saint.\N{\rCHT}你不是聖人
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.27,1:30:52.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Saints don't live on Park Avenue.\N{\rCHT}聖人不會住在公園大道的富人區裡
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.23,1:30:53.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...that he was having bad thoughts.\N{\rCHT}那時他就有不好的想法
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.94,1:30:56.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just feel the feelings like the rest of us.\N{\rCHT}你得去接受自己的喜怒哀樂 像我們普通人一樣
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.07,1:31:01.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My first response was to offer him some money.\N{\rCHT}我當初怎麼幫他的… 第一反應是給他錢
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.58,1:31:04.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I offered him fucking money!\N{\rCHT}我他媽的只會給錢
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.75,1:31:12.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,His face was so smashed.\N{\rCHT}他最後臉都摔爛了
Dialogue: 0,1:31:31.44,1:31:32.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.\N{\rCHT}沒事了
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.47,1:32:40.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Michael?\N{\rCHT}邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.88,1:32:42.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Michael? - Yes. Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 邁克爾？- 我在
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.30,1:32:44.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Is everything okay? - Yes, honey.\N{\rCHT}- 你沒事吧？- 沒事 親愛的
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.47,1:32:46.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You sure? - Yeah, baby.\N{\rCHT}- 真的？- 寶貝放心吧
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.39,1:32:49.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.\N{\rCHT}沒事了
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.65,1:33:00.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,To all investors.\N{\rCHT}至所有的投資人
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.40,1:33:01.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,As you may know,\N{\rCHT}你們也知道
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.49,1:33:06.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,our agreement allows me to take extraordinary measures\N{\rCHT}我們的協議允許我 在市場運行脫軌的時候
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.54,1:33:09.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,when markets aren't functioning properly.\N{\rCHT}採取極端的措施
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.54,1:33:13.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I currently have reason to believe the mortgage bond market\N{\rCHT}我現在有理由相信 房貸證券市場
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.92,1:33:15.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,is fraudulent.\N{\rCHT}是個騙局
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.84,1:33:22.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, in order to protect investors from this fraudulent market,\N{\rCHT}為了保護各位的投資不受扭曲市場的影響
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.68,1:33:25.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided to restrict investors' withdrawals\N{\rCHT}我決定禁止投資者撤資
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.01,1:33:27.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,until further notice.\N{\rCHT}後續情況請等待通知
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.02,1:33:31.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sincerely, Dr. Michael J. Burry.\N{\rCHT}真誠的 邁克爾·巴里博士
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.34,1:34:40.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I never would have guessed my life\N{\rCHT}我從未想過我的生活
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.88,1:34:43.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,could change as much as it has since I moved to L.A.\N{\rCHT}會改變這麼多 自從我搬到洛杉磯
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.51,1:34:45.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just, like, that easy to, like, not see you.\N{\rCHT}不只是不見你
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.97,1:34:49.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He lashed out at rumors he used performance enhancing drugs.\N{\rCHT}他猛烈抨擊他使用違禁藥物的傳聞
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.26,1:34:50.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This record is not tainted.\N{\rCHT}這個記錄不存在污點
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.76,1:34:51.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God, dude.\N{\rCHT}天哪 夥計
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.02,1:34:53.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you please stop changing the channels?\N{\rCHT}你能不能 別老是換頻道了
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.81,1:34:55.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're driving me crazy. - All right.\N{\rCHT}- 要把我逼瘋了 - 好吧
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.52,1:34:57.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fine. - Just put the business news on.\N{\rCHT}- 好的 - 就放商業新聞好了
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.06,1:35:00.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- ...and the S&P picked up three points. - Jesus!\N{\rCHT}- 標準普爾指數提升3點 - 天啊
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.77,1:35:02.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mortgage meltdown continued today.\N{\rCHT}房貸市場崩潰還在繼續
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.61,1:35:05.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Subprime mortgage lender New Century Financial,\N{\rCHT}曾經是領軍企業 發放次級貸的
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.45,1:35:08.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,once the industry leader, by the way, filed for bankruptcy.\N{\rCHT}新世紀金融公司申請破產
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.16,1:35:10.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- The company immediately... - Whoa, whoa, whoa.\N{\rCHT}- 該公司馬上… - 哇 哇
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.70,1:35:11.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Good time for my voice to go...\N{\rCHT}我清一下嗓子
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.95,1:35:14.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fired 3, 200 workers.\N{\rCHT}裁員了3200人
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.29,1:35:16.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The manufacturing index also fell in the month of March...\N{\rCHT}與三月相比 製造業指數仍在下滑
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.71,1:35:17.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's starting.\N{\rCHT}開始了…
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.87,1:35:19.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...a warning that economic growth could slow.\N{\rCHT}有專家提醒 經濟增長可能會放緩
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.54,1:35:22.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The Institute of Supply Management also reported a rise in prices...\N{\rCHT}相關機構聲稱 次級貸資產價格仍在上漲
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.63,1:35:24.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna call my mom.\N{\rCHT}我必須打電話給我媽了
Dialogue: 0,1:35:26.51,1:35:29.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The principal source of the slowdown in economic growth...\N{\rCHT}經濟放緩的主要原因
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.47,1:35:33.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Time and time and time again, I have gone to bat for you, Mark!\N{\rCHT}每次我都幫你擋著 馬克
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.85,1:35:35.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We've known each other for seven years...\N{\rCHT}我們認識都17年了
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.23,1:35:37.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,She's got some lungs on her. I'm impressed.\N{\rCHT}她嗓門這麼大 真是厲害
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.73,1:35:40.56,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help but enjoy it.\N{\rCHT}看她生氣我還挺高興
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.48,1:35:43.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no fucking way. There's no fucking way\N{\rCHT}絕對不可能 絕對不可能
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.19,1:35:44.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that the big banks are that stupid.\N{\rCHT}大銀行哪有這麼蠢
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.65,1:35:47.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Kathy!\N{\rCHT}再見 凱茜
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.16,1:35:53.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?\N{\rCHT}怎麼說
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.37,1:35:58.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Kathy thinks that it would be a good idea if we sold our shorts.\N{\rCHT}凱茜說 我們應該賣掉做空的互換
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.08,1:35:59.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What else is new?\N{\rCHT}老話重提
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.17,1:36:01.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And she said that Morgan Stanley will buy them.\N{\rCHT}她說摩根士丹利會買下來
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.13,1:36:02.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy shit!\N{\rCHT}天啊
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.84,1:36:04.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?\N{\rCHT}你怎麼說
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.17,1:36:05.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I told her we're not selling shit.\N{\rCHT}我告訴她 我們啥都不賣
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.01,1:36:15.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If you need the files for 2005...\N{\rCHT}如果你需要2005年資料的話…
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.02,1:36:19.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Fields' suit is very specific to files from the past year.\N{\rCHT}菲爾德先生的訴訟 只需要去年到現在的資料
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.77,1:36:22.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Then get out. Say hi to Lawrence for me.\N{\rCHT}那出去吧 代我向勞倫斯問好
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.61,1:36:23.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Will do.\N{\rCHT}好的
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.82,1:36:28.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't call me back for a week?\N{\rCHT}你一個禮拜都不能回我電話？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.57,1:36:30.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I am so sorry, Mike.\N{\rCHT}我很抱歉 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.78,1:36:33.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Goldman had a systems failure. I lost a ton of messages.\N{\rCHT}高盛的系統崩潰 我把很多消息都丟了
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.03,1:36:36.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, B of A said they had a power outage,\N{\rCHT}美國銀行說他們停電了
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.20,1:36:39.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and Morgan Stanley said their server crashed.\N{\rCHT}摩根士丹利說伺服器崩潰了
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.50,1:36:40.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird.\N{\rCHT}這麼湊巧
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.71,1:36:43.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I would call it improbable.\N{\rCHT}我覺得不太可能
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.34,1:36:46.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So where do you have our position marked?\N{\rCHT}那你記錄我們的資金量是多少
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.71,1:36:49.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's the same, Mike.\N{\rCHT}和以前一樣 邁克爾
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.55,1:36:51.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Can you explain that to me, please,\N{\rCHT}什麼？你能給我解釋一下嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.51,1:36:54.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,because how can the value of an insurance contract\N{\rCHT}被保的東西都毀滅了還不能用保險
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.89,1:36:59.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,not be affected by the demise of the very thing it insures?\N{\rCHT}那一個保險合同還叫什麼保險合同？
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.18,1:37:01.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're independent markets. They're not always correlated.\N{\rCHT}他們是獨立的市場 兩者並不總是相關
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.06,1:37:03.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it sounds odd,\N{\rCHT}我知道聽起來奇怪
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.15,1:37:05.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but these are very complicated products.\N{\rCHT}但是它們都是十分複雜的金融產品
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.44,1:37:08.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They are correlated.\N{\rCHT}它們本來就是相關的
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.40,1:37:10.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gonna lose their houses, they're gonna lose theirjobs,\N{\rCHT}人們會沒了房子 丟了工作
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.49,1:37:11.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,they're gonna lose their...\N{\rCHT}養老金…
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.37,1:37:16.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you listen to me?\N{\rCHT}你好好聽我說
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.41,1:37:19.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is like the end of capitalism.\N{\rCHT}這次… 就像資本主義終結一樣嚴重
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.16,1:37:22.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is like the Dark Ages all over again.\N{\rCHT}再次回到黑暗時代
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.54,1:37:24.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to talk to Dad.\N{\rCHT}我不想和我爸說話
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.75,1:37:27.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I love you, too. Save your money.\N{\rCHT}我也愛你 把你們的錢保護好
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.00,1:37:32.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,She says I need to be on Xanax and double my dose of Zoloft.\N{\rCHT}她說我得去開治抑鬱的藥 抗焦慮的藥要加倍
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.18,1:37:34.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Bear Stearns to price our shorts.\N{\rCHT}我問貝爾斯登買我們做空的報價
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.22,1:37:35.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They tell me the CDOs still haven't moved.\N{\rCHT}他們說CDO價格還是沒變
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.89,1:37:37.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fucking insane!\N{\rCHT}這幫人真是喪心病狂了
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.76,1:37:39.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You realize that? These people are crooks\N{\rCHT}這幫合夥騙子
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.35,1:37:41.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and they should be in prison.\N{\rCHT}應該進監獄
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.56,1:37:42.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the TABX.\N{\rCHT}看看資產擔保證券指數
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.77,1:37:44.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see that the CDOs are worth zero!\N{\rCHT}CDO的價值已經是零了
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.69,1:37:46.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So you know what they're doing, huh? You know what they're doing, right?\N{\rCHT}你知道他們想幹啥嗎 你知道他們想幹啥嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.98,1:37:48.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They're unloading them.\N{\rCHT}他們之所以不買
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.73,1:37:52.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're selling their dog shit CDOs, then they go to another bank\N{\rCHT}是因為要賣出去自己的狗屎CDO 然後才能去另一家銀行
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.11,1:37:54.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and short the shit they just fucking sold!\N{\rCHT}做空自己的狗屎 再吃進去
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.32,1:37:55.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the press, man!\N{\rCHT}天哪 咱們可以去找媒體了
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.99,1:37:59.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a massive story. Who wouldn't publish it?\N{\rCHT}這絕對是轟動新聞 誰會不願意登
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.25,1:38:01.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Robert Redford!\N{\rCHT}羅伯特？雷德福那樣的
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.00,1:38:03.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you don't understand!\N{\rCHT}再做空自己買下的
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.54,1:38:05.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it, guys. I got it.\N{\rCHT}我明白了 我明白了
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.84,1:38:08.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to do?\N{\rCHT}我又能做什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.50,1:38:10.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want me to write a piece called "We're All Fucked"?\N{\rCHT}難道寫一篇報導 題目就叫"我們都完蛋了"
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.30,1:38:12.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! That's a perfect title!\N{\rCHT}好啊 完美的題目
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.26,1:38:16.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Casey, right now every bank in town is unloading these shit bonds\N{\rCHT}現在所有的銀行都在轉手這些垃圾證券
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.60,1:38:18.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,onto unsuspecting customers.\N{\rCHT}讓那些不瞭解內情的人買單
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.39,1:38:21.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And they won't devalue them until they get them off their books.\N{\rCHT}他們在賣出去之前是不會主動降價的
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.47,1:38:26.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This level of criminality is unprecedented, even on fucking Wall Street.\N{\rCHT}這種犯罪程度在華爾街也是史無前例
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.40,1:38:30.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jamie... And this is me being honest here, okay?\N{\rCHT}傑米 我就打開天窗說亮話吧
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.53,1:38:33.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It took me years to build my relationships on Wall Street.\N{\rCHT}我在華爾街建立關係網花了好幾年
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.15,1:38:37.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No bank or ratings agency is going to confirm a story like this\N{\rCHT}沒有銀行或者評級機構 會傻到主動承認你倆所說的
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.41,1:38:39.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,just because it comes from two guys in a...\N{\rCHT}你倆的基金開在車庫
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.04,1:38:43.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, garage band hedge fund that thinks it's the apocalypse.\N{\rCHT}吵吵著世界末日就要來了 誰信
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.12,1:38:48.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were for real, Casey. You know, I'll have to say I really did.\N{\rCHT}我還以為你是良心記者 真的 我一直都這麼想
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.04,1:38:50.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?\N{\rCHT}真的？
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.30,1:38:52.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Jamie, you try being for real with a three-year-old\N{\rCHT}傑米 你和我講良心 我現在小孩3歲
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.46,1:38:54.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and a wife getting her master's degree.\N{\rCHT}老婆也要交學費讀碩士
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.55,1:38:57.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna burn my reputation on your wild hunch.\N{\rCHT}我不會因為你們瞎猜就把自己的名譽賠進去
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.39,1:39:02.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming, guys.\N{\rCHT}麻煩你倆跑一趟了
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.52,1:39:03.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Totally fucking awesome to see you.\N{\rCHT}見到你們真他媽開心
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.77,1:39:07.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Casey. I've always hated you, because you were a prick in college\N{\rCHT}我們也是 之前我就對你不爽 在大學裡面你就這臭屁樣兒
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.98,1:39:10.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and you are a prick today!\N{\rCHT}到現在了還是沒改
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.77,1:39:13.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Charlie. Still living with your mom?\N{\rCHT}謝謝評價 那你還在和你媽一起住嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.82,1:39:15.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Charlie, come on!\N{\rCHT}查理 咱們走
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.36,1:39:17.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark Baum again. Call me.\N{\rCHT}我是馬克·鮑姆 給我回電話
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.86,1:39:19.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Subprime bonds fell off a cliff.\N{\rCHT}次級貸證券大跳水
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.57,1:39:21.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor has it the default numbers are huge.\N{\rCHT}傳聞有大批房貸斷供
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.62,1:39:24.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Who got the remittance data early? I bet it's Goldman.\N{\rCHT}誰先拿到匯款數據了？估計是高盛
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.50,1:39:25.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, fuck you very much.\N{\rCHT}真是幫倒忙
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.91,1:39:28.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jared, it's chaos down here. Where are we?\N{\rCHT}傑瑞德 我這兒一團亂麻 咱們情況怎麼樣
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.17,1:39:32.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"And Caesar wept, for there were no more worlds to conquer."\N{\rCHT}"他哭泣了 再也沒能讓我征服的地方了" 亞歷山大大帝名言
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.96,1:39:35.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Shane?\N{\rCHT}夏恩…
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.59,1:39:36.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Shane?\N{\rCHT}夏恩
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.43,1:39:41.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, nobody's buying CDO or mortgage bonds anymore\N{\rCHT}情況是沒人買CDO和房貸證券了
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.22,1:39:42.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and everybody wants swaps.\N{\rCHT}人人都要買互換
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.85,1:39:45.18,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Swaps are now the most popular product on the street.\N{\rCHT}這是華爾街現在最搶手的東西
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.27,1:39:47.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's good for us. - Yes and no.\N{\rCHT}- 對我們是好消息吧 - 是也不是
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.19,1:39:48.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from somebody who heard from somebody...\N{\rCHT}我聽別人說… 對方也從別處聽說…
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.69,1:39:51.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Alex, no. Sorry.\N{\rCHT}不行 亞曆克斯 這裡我占了
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.57,1:39:58.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bennie Cleager over at Morgan is taking on some heavy losses in the bond department.\N{\rCHT}我聽說摩根的本尼在證券部門損失慘重
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.41,1:40:01.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Your ship might be taking on water.\N{\rCHT}你所在的大船可能漏水了
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.62,1:40:03.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It might be time to get our Iifejacket and get out.\N{\rCHT}趕緊穿上救生衣跳船吧
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.77,1:40:04.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy shit!\N{\rCHT}我的天
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.70,1:40:06.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jacked.\N{\rCHT}他媽的
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.75,1:40:09.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jacked! I'm jacked to the tits!\N{\rCHT}他媽的 我就是要這樣
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.87,1:40:10.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.\N{\rCHT}很好
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.00,1:40:13.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you feel it? - No.\N{\rCHT}- 能體會到痛苦又興奮的感覺嗎 - 我可不想
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.26,1:40:20.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you hear, Tommy?\N{\rCHT}你聽到什麼了泰德
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.89,1:40:23.89,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's happening...\N{\rCHT}開始了
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.97,1:40:25.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody wants our swaps.\N{\rCHT}大夥都要買我們的互換
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.02,1:40:28.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Kathy's office is looking for you.\N{\rCHT}凱茜讓你去她辦公室
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.35,1:40:30.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're singing a different tune now, aren't they?\N{\rCHT}黑臉的又變白臉了
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.11,1:40:33.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good.\N{\rCHT}情況不妙啊
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.45,1:40:39.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe later. Not now.\N{\rCHT}以後再說吧
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.90,1:40:42.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a joke. Never.\N{\rCHT}我沒開玩笑
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.79,1:40:46.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Listening.\N{\rCHT}我聽著呢
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.29,1:40:48.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Dr. Burry? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 巴里博士？- 是我
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.96,1:40:50.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Deeb Winston, Goldman Sachs.\N{\rCHT}我是高盛的迪伯？溫斯頓
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.46,1:40:51.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, I've been reviewing your position.\N{\rCHT}我看了一下你的價位
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.04,1:40:54.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to discuss your marks and make sure they're fair.\N{\rCHT}想要和你討論估值的情況 盡可能的公平
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.38,1:41:00.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think you mean that you've secured a net short position yourselves.\N{\rCHT}我想 你的意思是你已經做空了自己的倉位
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.22,1:41:02.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're free to mark my swaps accurately for once\N{\rCHT}這樣你總算能認真評估我的互換了
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.14,1:41:05.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,because it's now in your interest to do so.\N{\rCHT}現在對你們也有利
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.97,1:41:10.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what you want me to say.\N{\rCHT}我… 我不知道你要我怎麼說
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.23,1:41:11.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that...\N{\rCHT}我想…
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.23,1:41:15.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that you've already said it.\N{\rCHT}你該說的都說了
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.16,1:41:25.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You tell Jeff at Goldman that I'm not transferring funds.\N{\rCHT}你告訴高盛的傑夫 我絕對不會轉移基金
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.37,1:41:26.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bullshit!\N{\rCHT}太扯淡了
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.17,1:41:35.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we'll talk later.\N{\rCHT}回頭再說
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.42,1:41:37.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝…
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.34,1:41:42.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for coming so quickly, Mark.\N{\rCHT}謝謝你這麼快就過來了
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.30,1:41:43.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.\N{\rCHT}嗯
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.93,1:41:46.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you've been hearing rumblings about some losses Morgan has suffered.\N{\rCHT}我知道你聽說了摩根有一些損失
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.85,1:41:48.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Congratulations. - On what?\N{\rCHT}- 恭喜你 - 恭喜什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.18,1:41:52.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.\N{\rCHT}謝謝
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.77,1:41:54.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Having fun?\N{\rCHT}感覺挺好的吧
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.15,1:41:56.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.\N{\rCHT}還行
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.69,1:41:59.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Tons.\N{\rCHT}是感覺不錯
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.53,1:42:01.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted you to know that...\N{\rCHT}我想告訴你
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.45,1:42:04.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That, yes, Morgan has suffered some losses,\N{\rCHT}摩根是遭受了一些損失
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.20,1:42:07.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but our liquidity is strong and there's no cause for concern.\N{\rCHT}但我們的流動資產還是很穩健 不需要再擔心什麼了
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.20,1:42:11.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Would Bennie Cleager be concerned?\N{\rCHT}那需要擔心本尼嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.37,1:42:15.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Because word on the street is that he took some pretty heavy losses.\N{\rCHT}聽人說他損失慘重
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.96,1:42:18.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Kathy, come on. We know each other.\N{\rCHT}凱茜 別遮掩了 咱們都認識多少年了…
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.84,1:42:21.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?\N{\rCHT}發生了什麼事情
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.46,1:42:22.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How bad is this?\N{\rCHT}情況有多嚴重
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.13,1:42:24.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.09,1:42:28.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, Bennie Cleager in Morgan's bond department\N{\rCHT}在兩年以前 摩根證券部門的克裡格
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.22,1:42:31.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,also started shorting subprime housing, $2 billion in BBBs.\N{\rCHT}也開始做空次級貸 20億做空3B級
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.85,1:42:33.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bennie is smarter than I thought.\N{\rCHT}本尼比我想的還要聰明啊
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.18,1:42:34.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's not smart at all.\N{\rCHT}不 他一點也不聰明
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.69,1:42:37.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The premiums on the swap ate into his desk's profit.\N{\rCHT}交的保費搭進去了其他利潤
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.15,1:42:39.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,To cover his BBB shorts,\N{\rCHT}為了保住3B的做空
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.19,1:42:41.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,he sold a lot ofA and AA swaps as protection.\N{\rCHT}他賣了很多的A和2A的交換做保護
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.78,1:42:42.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot.\N{\rCHT}很多
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.49,1:42:46.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He believed that there was no way that they could be affected.\N{\rCHT}他覺得 不可能A級的也會受影響
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.24,1:42:50.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me Morgan Stanley doesn't hold the contracts on these swaps.\N{\rCHT}你該不會說是摩根士丹利賣給我們交換的吧
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.91,1:42:55.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy shit.\N{\rCHT}我的天
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.08,1:42:59.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All this time I've been trying to figure out who I'm betting against,\N{\rCHT}我一直都在找我們的對家是誰
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.75,1:43:01.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's Morgan Stanley.\N{\rCHT}沒想到是我們的母公司
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.55,1:43:03.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is me.\N{\rCHT}遭殃的是自己的公司
Dialogue: 0,1:43:05.59,1:43:07.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your exposure? $3 billion?\N{\rCHT}風險敞口有多少？30億？
Dialogue: 0,1:43:08.85,1:43:10.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't tell me it's more than four.\N{\rCHT}不可能超過40億吧？
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.85,1:43:12.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't answer that. I can't answer that.\N{\rCHT}我不能回答你這問題
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.56,1:43:15.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you can answer that, because I walk in here\N{\rCHT}你可以說… 我過來的時候
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.81,1:43:18.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and people are crying in your hallway.\N{\rCHT}看到走廊上的人都在哭
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.27,1:43:20.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Kathy,\N{\rCHT}凱茜
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.94,1:43:22.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,you bring me in to tell me everything's fine,\N{\rCHT}你跟我說什麼事兒都好
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.07,1:43:24.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and everything's not fine.\N{\rCHT}可什麼事兒現在都不好
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.94,1:43:26.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What, what is happening?\N{\rCHT}究竟現在是怎麼了
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.03,1:43:31.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The long exposure is...\N{\rCHT}做多的敞口有…
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.12,1:43:34.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$150 billion.\N{\rCHT}150億
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.59,1:43:41.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus!\N{\rCHT}我的老天爺
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.79,1:43:44.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He kept saying defaults over 8% were impossible.\N{\rCHT}你總是說斷供率不可能超過8%的
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.26,1:43:45.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God.\N{\rCHT}我的天
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.34,1:43:46.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That there would be a million homeless!\N{\rCHT}那樣會有1百萬人無家可歸
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.01,1:43:50.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but we have nothing to do with Morgan Stanley.\N{\rCHT}摩根和我們沒有關係
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.18,1:43:54.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...\N{\rCHT}嗯
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.64,1:43:56.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the bankruptcy court.\N{\rCHT}那你上破產法庭這麼說去
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.73,1:43:59.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Morgan fails, all our accounts go on their balance sheet.\N{\rCHT}摩根破產 我們所有的錢都會轉到 他們的資產負債表上
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.48,1:44:02.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just crazy.\N{\rCHT}這也太瘋狂了
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.32,1:44:03.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Morgan makes the sucker's bet\N{\rCHT}摩根輸了爛賭注
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.73,1:44:06.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and we pay their fucking gambling debt?\N{\rCHT}卻讓我們來還帳？
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.57,1:44:09.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Short the bank stocks. Then we wait.\N{\rCHT}做空摩根的股票 然後我們等
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.99,1:44:14.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Or we sell our swaps when the market opens.\N{\rCHT}或者等市場一開始交易 就賣了我們的互換
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.75,1:44:19.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We get our bonuses, our investors get their profits, we get...\N{\rCHT}我們拿到獎金 我們的投資人拿到收益
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.87,1:44:22.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What, 30 cents on the dollar? It's not bad.\N{\rCHT}咱們能拿到一塊錢裡的三毛錢 至少能保命
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.67,1:44:24.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're three times that.\N{\rCHT}我們比這值3倍
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.25,1:44:25.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Not if there's no market left to sell them in.\N{\rCHT}要是買家市場都沒了 就爛到手裡了
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.05,1:44:27.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it. We're not giving out any lifeboats.\N{\rCHT}不行 我不能把救生船送給這些人
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.05,1:44:30.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,If Morgan goes under, we end up with nothing.\N{\rCHT}馬克 如果摩根垮了 到頭來我們什麼都沒有了
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.51,1:44:31.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Vinnie.\N{\rCHT}文尼
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.26,1:44:36.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus, come on. I say when we sell.\N{\rCHT}別爭了 我說賣 咱們再賣
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.56,1:44:45.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I get that this is personal for you, but we have a fiduciary responsibility.\N{\rCHT}我知道你跟華爾街有私人恩怨 但是我們對投資人也要負責
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.40,1:44:46.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No, we don't.\N{\rCHT}我們不需要負責
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.19,1:44:49.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody's acting responsible.\N{\rCHT}我們負責？這裡誰給別人負責？
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.53,1:44:52.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck responsibility. Are you kidding me?\N{\rCHT}操他媽的責任 跟我談負責
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.78,1:44:54.87,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The assholes at the big banks will take...\N{\rCHT}大銀行的那些混蛋們
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.95,1:44:55.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You boys want any appetizers?\N{\rCHT}你們點菜嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.08,1:44:57.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're talking, please!\N{\rCHT}我們在說正經事… 別打擾
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.58,1:45:00.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Excuse us. - Sorry.\N{\rCHT}- 請原諒 - 抱歉了
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.21,1:45:05.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We are going to wait, and we are going to wait,\N{\rCHT}我們要等著 耐心等著
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.13,1:45:10.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and we are going to wait until they feel the pain, until they start to bleed.\N{\rCHT}等到他們知道疼了 開始流血了才行
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.88,1:45:13.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That is what I want. - But what about our clients\N{\rCHT}- 這才是我想要的結果 - 那我們的客戶怎麼辦
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.09,1:45:14.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,who've entrusted us with their savings...\N{\rCHT}我們在拿他們的錢冒風險
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.47,1:45:15.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I say when we sell.\N{\rCHT}我說賣 我們再出手
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.72,1:45:16.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't about you.\N{\rCHT}這不是你公報私仇的時候
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.85,1:45:19.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- This isn't about you and your Upper East Side mahogany soapbox. - Hey! Hey!\N{\rCHT}- 這不是有關你和你的富人區 -嘿 嘿
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.39,1:45:20.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I say when we sell!\N{\rCHT}我說賣 再出手
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.31,1:45:24.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever you say, Mark.\N{\rCHT}好吧 那聽你的
Dialogue: 0,1:45:30.78,1:45:32.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Dude, did you hear the news?\N{\rCHT}夥計你看新聞了嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.41,1:45:38.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. So, not only do two mortgage hedge funds backed by Bear Stearns go belly up,\N{\rCHT}好的 那 不僅是兩個貝爾投資的房貸對沖基金爆倉了
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.70,1:45:41.83,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but now there's a class-action lawsuit against Bear.\N{\rCHT}而且現在貝爾還被集體訴訟
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.91,1:45:43.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy shit!\N{\rCHT}壞了
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.17,1:45:45.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! Push! Push!\N{\rCHT}跟我做 用力 用力
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.75,1:45:47.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what? Bear could really collapse here.\N{\rCHT}那怎麼了？貝爾會破產嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.25,1:45:49.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- This is a risk we really shouldn't take. - Then what?\N{\rCHT}- 我們不能冒這個險 - 那又怎樣
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.13,1:45:51.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We bought 80% of our swaps at Bear.\N{\rCHT}我們有80%的互換 是從貝爾那裡買的
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.22,1:45:52.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We 'd lose everything.\N{\rCHT}我們可能陪個精光
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.88,1:45:54.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey, sir? - One second!\N{\rCHT}- 先生 - 馬上就好
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.43,1:45:55.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my opinion.\N{\rCHT}這是我的看法
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.47,1:45:57.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We bought these fucking things. We have no clue how to sell them.\N{\rCHT}我們買了這東西 卻不知道怎麼賣
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.01,1:45:59.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I know. We have to get Ben to do it.\N{\rCHT}是啊 所以我們得找本幫忙
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.52,1:46:01.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been trying to call him and he won't get back to me.\N{\rCHT}我一直給他打電話 他也不回
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.60,1:46:03.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He's on vacation with his wife's family.\N{\rCHT}現在他和老婆一家人在度假
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.94,1:46:05.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They're in England.\N{\rCHT}在英國
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.06,1:46:07.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\N{\rCHT}什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.78,1:46:16.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hello, Ben. - Hey. Guys'?\N{\rCHT}- 你好 本 - 你們好
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.45,1:46:18.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we're here. Can you hear us?\N{\rCHT}我們在 你能聽清嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.12,1:46:19.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Guys? - Yeah, we got you.\N{\rCHT}- 夥計們 我聽的清楚
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.79,1:46:22.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I hardly got cell phone or Wi-Fi service.\N{\rCHT}我這裡電話和無線網路信號都不好
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.75,1:46:26.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm trying to sell $200 million worth of securities.\N{\rCHT}居然要這樣賣掉2億的證券
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.67,1:46:29.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In a pub. It smells like sheep.\N{\rCHT}就在這酒吧 聞著綿羊味兒
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.30,1:46:30.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do this.\N{\rCHT}你能行的
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.42,1:46:31.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to pressure you, Ben\N{\rCHT}我不想給你壓力
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.63,1:46:34.22,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you don't pull this off, we lose everything.\N{\rCHT}但你搞不定的話 我們就全賠光了
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.47,1:46:37.76,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Let's see what Credit Suisse's appetite is.\N{\rCHT}看看瑞士瑞信銀行的胃口如何
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.93,1:46:44.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Brownfield Fund.\N{\rCHT}我是棕地基金
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.19,1:46:46.10,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to unload my credit default swaps.\N{\rCHT}我想要拋售我的信用違約互換
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.44,1:46:47.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. What you got?\N{\rCHT}好的 你們有多少
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.15,1:46:49.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty AA tranches of A.B.S. CDOs.\N{\rCHT}大概有20個2A級別的CDO
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.44,1:46:52.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,A.B.S.? Are these... These are pretty bad?\N{\rCHT}好吧… 這些現在行情不太好
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.99,1:46:54.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely. They're complete shit.\N{\rCHT}是啊 全是垃圾
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.28,1:46:56.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your notional value?\N{\rCHT}你的…
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.86,1:46:59.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Face value is 205 million. Dollars.\N{\rCHT}面值是2億50萬 美元
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.83,1:47:02.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we could, we could go to forty.\N{\rCHT}那我們能… 以40收購
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.50,1:47:03.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. We want at least 100 million.\N{\rCHT}不行 至少要1億
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.87,1:47:07.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,100 million? Who are you, a drug dealer or a banker?\N{\rCHT}1個億？你是毒品販子 還是搞銀行的？
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.67,1:47:10.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause if you're a banker, you can fuck right off!\N{\rCHT}你要是銀行家 就立馬給我滾蛋
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.25,1:47:11.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if we can make a market.\N{\rCHT}我不知道能不能坐莊
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.50,1:47:12.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just give me your best price?\N{\rCHT}直接說你的最好報價
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.71,1:47:15.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Chuck 100 million in for me, mate.\N{\rCHT}哎呦 1個億還嫌不夠
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.34,1:47:16.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we're far apart.\N{\rCHT}我覺得我們期望差太多
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.09,1:47:19.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, if you don't want the deal, you can just hang up.\N{\rCHT}你要是不想買 就直接掛斷
Dialogue: 0,1:47:21.97,1:47:23.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought.\N{\rCHT}跟我料想的一樣
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.31,1:47:26.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- 90 million. -70.\N{\rCHT}- 9千萬 - 7千萬
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.65,1:47:29.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,85.\N{\rCHT}8千5百萬
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.36,1:47:31.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,-78. -84.\N{\rCHT}- 7千8百萬 - 8千4百萬
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.53,1:47:34.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,-78. -84.\N{\rCHT}- 7千8百萬 - 8千4百萬
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.36,1:47:37.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Dr. Burry.\N{\rCHT}我是巴里博士
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.24,1:47:41.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the collapse of the financial sector is imminent.\N{\rCHT}看來金融危機馬上來了
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.08,1:47:44.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start to sell my position.\N{\rCHT}我以現在的倉位出手
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.41,1:47:46.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's $1.3 billion.\N{\rCHT}13億
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.75,1:47:48.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I'll hold.\N{\rCHT}當然 我可以等著
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.40,1:48:14.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I was right.\N{\rCHT}最終我還是對的
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.74,1:48:18.24,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I took a rash of shit for two years, but\N{\rCHT}我被人噴了兩年…
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.65,1:48:20.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I was right.\N{\rCHT}但是我是對的
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.91,1:48:22.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And everyone was wrong.\N{\rCHT}所有人都錯了
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.58,1:48:26.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And, yeah, I got a bonus check for it. Sue me.\N{\rCHT}我還拿到了獎金支票 來告我啊
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.41,1:48:28.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know?\N{\rCHT}隨便了
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.92,1:48:32.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot of money. I get it. I can feel you judging me.\N{\rCHT}這錢是不少 我能感到你們心裡有看法
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.63,1:48:33.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's palpable.\N{\rCHT}很明顯嘛
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.63,1:48:38.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But, hey, I never said I was the hero of this story.\N{\rCHT}可是呢 我從沒說過我是這個故事裡的英雄人物
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.26,1:48:41.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ben. How are we looking?\N{\rCHT}你好啊 情況怎麼樣？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.01,1:48:44.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Eight...on...\N{\rCHT}八 萬
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.10,1:48:46.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry?\N{\rCHT}什麼？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:46.81,1:48:48.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Eighty million.\N{\rCHT}是8千萬 8千萬成交了
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.14,1:48:50.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,$80 million, $80 million, that's good, right?\N{\rCHT}8千萬 8千萬 這挺好的是吧
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.85,1:48:51.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Eighty is great. - Is that good?\N{\rCHT}- 8千萬很好 - 很好嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.02,1:48:53.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Eighty is great, Ben. - Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 是的 本 - 對
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.27,1:48:55.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. Thank you so much.\N{\rCHT}謝謝你 非常感謝
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.94,1:48:57.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of it went to UBS.\N{\rCHT}錢都匯到瑞士聯合銀行了
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.94,1:48:59.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You're very lucky. The largest bank\N{\rCHT}你們運氣相當不錯
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.78,1:49:02.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,in France froze customer's money market accounts today.\N{\rCHT}今天法國把國內最大的貨幣市場帳戶凍結了
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.91,1:49:04.45,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This thing's hitting Europe.\N{\rCHT}風暴已經傳到歐洲了
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.53,1:49:06.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Greece and Iceland are finished.\N{\rCHT}希臘和愛爾蘭已經完了
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.45,1:49:07.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Spain is teetering.\N{\rCHT}西班牙正在遭殃
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.87,1:49:09.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious? Fuck.\N{\rCHT}真的假的？這麼嚴重
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.87,1:49:11.71,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Ben, call us when you get home.\N{\rCHT}本 等你回家給我們打電話
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.79,1:49:13.58,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But, hey, before you go,\N{\rCHT}不過放電話之前請等一下
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.67,1:49:15.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just wondering...\N{\rCHT}我一直想問…
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.30,1:49:20.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do this with us?\N{\rCHT}你為什麼要和我們做這件事
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.30,1:49:23.30,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have to.\N{\rCHT}你並不需要…
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.64,1:49:27.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. But, why?\N{\rCHT}當然我們很感謝你 但 為什麼
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.22,1:49:31.14,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys said you wanted to get rich. Now you're rich.\N{\rCHT}你們說想要發財 現在你們有錢了
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.65,1:49:41.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,As the housing markets and banks continued to hemorrhage,\N{\rCHT}房產和銀行還在持續出血
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.28,1:49:43.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,only one of the big shorts refused to sell.\N{\rCHT}只有一家大單做空的還拒絕出售
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.78,1:49:44.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark Baum.\N{\rCHT}馬克·鮑姆的空頭
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.37,1:49:50.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was beyond perfect when he was asked to speak\N{\rCHT}這簡直比咱們導演的還要好
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.50,1:49:52.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,at a conference opposite Bruce Miller,\N{\rCHT}他在會議上和布魯斯·米勒同台討論
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.42,1:49:54.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,the famous bullish investor.\N{\rCHT}著名的樂觀投資人
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.25,1:49:57.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,After he and Mark had their debate, Alan Greenspan,\N{\rCHT}他和馬克辯論以後 格林斯潘
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.55,1:50:01.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,one of the architects of the whole crisis was scheduled to speak.\N{\rCHT}整個金融危機的總設計師 還要繼續講話
Dialogue: 0,1:50:01.26,1:50:03.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone in Mark's office showed up, he even invited friends.\N{\rCHT}馬克辦公室的人都來了 把朋友也邀請過來了
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.34,1:50:08.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This was the Ali vs. Foreman of the financial world.\N{\rCHT}這就像金融界的阿裡和福爾曼的拳擊世紀對決
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.02,1:50:11.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The realist versus the fools.\N{\rCHT}現實主義者對戰傻瓜
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.48,1:50:12.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And if it seems almost too perfect,\N{\rCHT}在我們以為事情不可能更完美的時候
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.06,1:50:15.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,trust me, this happened.\N{\rCHT}相信我 這事兒發生了
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.53,1:50:23.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, everyone. Please give a generous welcome to\N{\rCHT}請讓我們熱烈歡迎
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.70,1:50:27.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Bruce Miller and Mark Baum.\N{\rCHT}布魯斯·米勒和馬克·鮑姆
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.47,1:50:45.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Strap yourself in.\N{\rCHT}系好安全帶看戲了
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.22,1:50:49.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So as some of you may know, Bear Steams\N{\rCHT}你們有些人可能知道 貝爾斯登
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.47,1:50:52.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,has just received a loan from JP Morgan.\N{\rCHT}剛剛接受了一筆摩根的貸款
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.14,1:50:54.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, we're gonna have to wait and see how the markets react,\N{\rCHT}當然我們等些時間才能看到市場的回饋
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.06,1:50:58.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,but that should lay to rest any concerns about the bank's health.\N{\rCHT}但這事本身就能打消對貝爾銀行的擔心了
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.86,1:51:03.57,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I take it you have no plans to sell your $200 million in Bear stock?\N{\rCHT}我理解 所以你本人不會出售你的2億股票了
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.90,1:51:05.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No. As a matter of fact, when we're done here,\N{\rCHT}當然不 實際上等我們聊完
Dialogue: 0,1:51:05.61,1:51:07.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll probably go out and buy some more.\N{\rCHT}我還要再買進更多
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.91,1:51:12.41,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,For the opposing view, Mr. Baum.\N{\rCHT}而對立觀點… 馬克·鮑姆
Dialogue: 0,1:51:14.83,1:51:16.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I got to stand for this.\N{\rCHT}我得站起來說
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.67,1:51:21.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, hi.\N{\rCHT}好的 大家好
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.67,1:51:24.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My firm's thesis is pretty simple.\N{\rCHT}我們公司投資理念很簡單
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.42,1:51:27.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Wall Street took a good idea, Lewis Ranieri's mortgage bond,\N{\rCHT}華爾街把最初路易斯房貸證券的好點子
Dialogue: 0,1:51:28.09,1:51:32.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and turned it into an atomic bomb of fraud and stupidity\N{\rCHT}變成了一個欺詐和愚蠢做成的原子彈
Dialogue: 0,1:51:32.93,1:51:35.60,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that's on its way to decimating the world economy.\N{\rCHT}現在原子彈馬上就要毀滅全球經濟了
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.69,1:51:38.23,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you really feel?\N{\rCHT}你說的還挺像那麼回事似的
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.35,1:51:40.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you still have a sense of humor.\N{\rCHT}我沒想到你現在還能笑的出來
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.36,1:51:42.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't if I were you.\N{\rCHT}我要是你的話可不這麼樂觀
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.78,1:51:46.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, anyone who knows me knows that\N{\rCHT}認識我的人都知道
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.90,1:51:49.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no problem telling someone they're wrong.\N{\rCHT}我是對別人的錯誤直言不諱的
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.45,1:51:51.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bear Stearns is denying rumors of liquidity problems.\N{\rCHT}貝爾斯登否認存在流動資金問題的謠言
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.78,1:51:55.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- But for the first time.. in my life.. - Holy fuck, it's 39 now!\N{\rCHT}- 但這一輩子 我是頭一次… - 天啊 股價39
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.28,1:51:57.16,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not so enjoyable\N{\rCHT}真心笑不出來
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.08,1:52:00.63,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We live in an era of fraud in America.\N{\rCHT}現在的美國充斥著欺詐
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.71,1:52:03.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Notjust in banking, but in government,\N{\rCHT}不僅是銀行 連政府也參與其中
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.55,1:52:06.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,education, religion, food,\N{\rCHT}教育 宗教 食品
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.59,1:52:08.26,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,even baseball.\N{\rCHT}連棒球都作假
Dialogue: 0,1:52:08.76,1:52:11.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What bothers me isn't that\N{\rCHT}真正讓我擔心的
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.97,1:52:15.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,fraud is not nice or that fraud is mean.\N{\rCHT}並不是說欺詐不道德 也不是說欺詐很邪惡
Dialogue: 0,1:52:16.10,1:52:17.98,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that for 15, 000 years\N{\rCHT}而是說 在過去一萬五千年的歷史中
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.81,1:52:20.35,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,fraud and short-sighted thinking\N{\rCHT}欺詐和短視
Dialogue: 0,1:52:20.44,1:52:22.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,have never, ever worked.\N{\rCHT}就從來沒有成功過
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.94,1:52:25.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not once. - Jesus, Bear at 37...\N{\rCHT}- 一次都沒有 - 已經降到37了
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.90,1:52:26.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We're at thirty-seven\N{\rCHT}已經降到37了
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.28,1:52:30.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's plummeting again, It's fucking plummeting, man.\N{\rCHT}又要下跌 他媽的是暴跌
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.82,1:52:33.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,When the hell did we forget all that?\N{\rCHT}我們難道都忘記教訓了嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.29,1:52:39.79,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we were better than this. I really did.\N{\rCHT}我還以為我們有希望 真的這麼以為過
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.12,1:52:42.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And the fact that we're not\N{\rCHT}還有雖然我們不夠明智
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.29,1:52:45.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't make me feel all right and superior.\N{\rCHT}但是我也不覺得自己多麼正義 多麼驕傲
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.09,1:52:47.59,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me feel... Sad.\N{\rCHT}我只是為大家感到… 深深的悲哀
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.01,1:52:50.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I fucking hit "refresh" it's dropping, man.\N{\rCHT}- 我每次刷新 股價都在掉 - 垮掉算了
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.01,1:52:53.68,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And as fun as it is to watch\N{\rCHT}看笑話的心情…
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.97,1:52:56.27,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,pompous, dumb Wall Streeters be wildly wrong,\N{\rCHT}看這些自大愚蠢的華爾街人士大錯特錯
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.35,1:52:58.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and you are wrong, sir,\N{\rCHT}您也一樣 大錯特錯
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.48,1:53:02.48,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I just know, that at the end of the day\N{\rCHT}我只知道 最後…
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.15,1:53:08.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,average people are going to be the ones that are gonna have to pay for all this.\N{\rCHT}將是普通百姓來承受這些痛苦
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.82,1:53:10.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Because they always, always do.\N{\rCHT}興亡總是百姓遭殃
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.03,1:53:12.03,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 32.\N{\rCHT}真是32點
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.16,1:53:13.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fucking tanked, man.\N{\rCHT}這是跌破的節奏
Dialogue: 0,1:53:13.66,1:53:15.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my two cents. Thank you.\N{\rCHT}這是我的拙見 謝謝大家
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.99,1:53:18.33,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me drop a deuce at Deutsche.\N{\rCHT}我得去德意志銀行去看熱鬧
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.50,1:53:20.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Does our bull have a response?\N{\rCHT}我們的樂觀派有什麼回應嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.50,1:53:25.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Only that, in the entire history of Wall Street,\N{\rCHT}在華爾街的整個歷史上
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.13,1:53:29.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,no investment bank has ever failed unless caught in criminal activities.\N{\rCHT}從沒有投資銀行失敗 除非因為犯罪被牽連
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.01,1:53:33.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, yes, I stand by my Bear Stearns optimism.\N{\rCHT}我的回應是堅持 我認為貝爾前景光明
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.84,1:53:35.85,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Miller, I'm sorry. Quick question.\N{\rCHT}米勒先生 打擾了 一個小問題
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.35,1:53:38.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,From the time you guys started talking,\N{\rCHT}剛才你們正在談話的時候
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.18,1:53:41.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Bear Stearns stock has fallen more than 38%.\N{\rCHT}貝爾的股票已經跌落了38%
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.14,1:53:42.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you still buy more?\N{\rCHT}你還要再買入嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.73,1:53:46.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure, of course I'd buy more. Why not?\N{\rCHT}當然我當然要買入 為什麼不買
Dialogue: 0,1:53:47.32,1:53:48.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Boom.\N{\rCHT}當場打臉
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.57,1:53:52.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ!\N{\rCHT}天哪
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.37,1:53:57.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,That concludes the first part of our presentation.\N{\rCHT}我們第一部分的討論就結束了
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.54,1:54:03.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Up next, we have the legendary former chairman of the Fed,\N{\rCHT}下面我們有請 傳奇的前美聯儲主席
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.25,1:54:05.04,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Alan Greenspan.\N{\rCHT}格林斯潘
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.13,1:54:06.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Folks?\N{\rCHT}大夥
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.77,1:54:25.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...employees of Lehman Brothers today,\N{\rCHT}雷曼兄弟的員工…
Dialogue: 0,1:54:26.06,1:54:29.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,as the Wall Street giant's stock went to zero.\N{\rCHT}華爾街的大公司股票跌到零
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.73,1:54:31.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The collapse of the venerable New York bank\N{\rCHT}紐約銀行的形象毀於一旦
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.69,1:54:35.36,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,follows a tumultuous few months of market volatility\N{\rCHT}之後將是幾個月的市場動盪
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.45,1:54:38.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and fear in the world economy.\N{\rCHT}我們擔心世界經濟…
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.41,1:54:40.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I got to see inside.\N{\rCHT}我得去裡面看看
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.91,1:54:42.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,How?\N{\rCHT}怎麼進去？
Dialogue: 0,1:54:42.96,1:54:43.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.\N{\rCHT}來吧
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.79,1:54:47.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I left my phone in the office. I threw my pass out already.\N{\rCHT}我電話忘到辦公室了 門卡也扔了
Dialogue: 0,1:54:47.96,1:54:49.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if I take your pass?\N{\rCHT}能用你的嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.46,1:54:52.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't give a shit anymore. You can do what you want.\N{\rCHT}愛用就用 我才不管
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.93,1:55:01.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Go directly to your transportation.\N{\rCHT}直接上班車
Dialogue: 0,1:55:01.72,1:55:03.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not talk to the press.\N{\rCHT}別對媒體說話
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.60,1:55:06.94,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,After 18 years, I just leave? That's just fucking great!\N{\rCHT}18年了 我就落了這麼個結果 還趕我走
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.15,1:55:10.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to whoever the hell I want!\N{\rCHT}我願意怎麼幹就怎麼幹
Dialogue: 0,1:55:10.11,1:55:12.44,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not talk to the press.\N{\rCHT}別對媒體說話
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.78,1:55:14.74,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Go directly to your transportation.\N{\rCHT}直接上班車
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.82,1:55:15.91,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not talk to...\N{\rCHT}別對…
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.49,1:55:19.66,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look, you wanna get a bite tonight?\N{\rCHT}晚上想一起吃個飯嗎？
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.67,1:55:23.61,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's this new Cuban place just opened on the Lower East Side.\N{\rCHT}下東城那邊開了古巴餐館
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.64,1:55:24.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's supposed to be good.\N{\rCHT}可以去…
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.62,1:55:26.29,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- Really? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 是嗎 - 是啊
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.79,1:55:28.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I?\N{\rCHT}咱們倆
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.33,1:55:29.92,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, or other people.\N{\rCHT}也帶上大夥吧
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.00,1:55:31.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,- That sounds nice. I would like that. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}好主意 我很想去
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.84,1:55:33.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally.\N{\rCHT}總算打電話了
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.51,1:55:34.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, hey.\N{\rCHT}馬克
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.13,1:55:36.43,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bloodbath up here.\N{\rCHT}這裡已經血流成河了
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.51,1:55:38.01,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Morgan stock has lost half its value.\N{\rCHT}摩根股票貶值一半
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.09,1:55:40.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's down to 23.10. It's in freefall.\N{\rCHT}跌倒23.10
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.47,1:55:43.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Clients want to talk to you about pulling their money.\N{\rCHT}這是跌破的趨勢 我想和你談談脫身的事
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.68,1:55:47.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's now or never, Mark. We got to sell.\N{\rCHT}現在不把錢撤出來就沒機會了 馬克 我們要出手了
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.48,1:55:51.65,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark.\N{\rCHT}馬克
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.03,1:55:54.19,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, you hear me?\N{\rCHT}馬克 你聽到了嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:55:54.53,1:55:55.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mailbox one.\N{\rCHT}語音信箱1
Dialogue: 0,1:55:56.15,1:55:58.86,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You have 15 messages.\N{\rCHT}您有15條留言
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.32,1:56:01.95,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mike, I can't seem to get ahold of you.\N{\rCHT}邁克爾 我聯繫不上你
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.03,1:56:04.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you please call me at your earliest convenience.\N{\rCHT}你能方便的時候儘快回電話嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:56:05.83,1:56:08.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Jack. You're buying stocks?\N{\rCHT}我是傑夫 你現在還要買股票？
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.87,1:56:11.84,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The market's at an all-time low. This is crazy!\N{\rCHT}現在是股市最低點 你太離譜了
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.09,1:56:14.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I met my wife on Match.com.\N{\rCHT}我和我妻子是在網上認識的
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.84,1:56:16.17,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,My profile said,\N{\rCHT}我的交友資料說
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.38,1:56:18.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am a medical student with only one eye,\N{\rCHT}我是個醫學院學生只有一隻眼能用
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.80,1:56:20.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"an awkward social manner,\N{\rCHT}不懂社交
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.80,1:56:24.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"and $145, 000 in student loans."\N{\rCHT}助學貸款還有14.5萬要還
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.06,1:56:26.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,She wrote back,\N{\rCHT}她的回信是
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.81,1:56:28.39,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,"You're just what I've been looking for."\N{\rCHT}我找的就是你這樣的
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.35,1:56:31.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,She meant honest.\N{\rCHT}她的意思是我很坦誠
Dialogue: 0,1:56:31.23,1:56:32.90,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So let me be honest.\N{\rCHT}那我也對你們開誠佈公
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.07,1:56:37.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The housing crisis represents the greatest financial opportunity of...\N{\rCHT}房地產危機是金融史上最大的機會
Dialogue: 0,1:56:37.40,1:56:40.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Making money is not like I thought it would be.\N{\rCHT}但賺錢並不像我想像的那樣簡單
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.53,1:56:45.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This business kills the part of life that is essential.\N{\rCHT}做交易… 殺死了生命中對我最重要的那部分
Dialogue: 0,1:56:45.20,1:56:48.25,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The part that has nothing to do with business.\N{\rCHT}這部分和做交易無關
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.54,1:56:52.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,For the past two years, my insides\N{\rCHT}在過去兩年 我內心感覺到
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.71,1:56:56.09,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,have felt like they're eating themselves.\N{\rCHT}黑暗的東西在自我吞噬
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.26,1:56:58.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,All the people I respected\N{\rCHT}我曾經尊敬過的人
Dialogue: 0,1:56:59.05,1:57:01.55,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,won't talk to me anymore\N{\rCHT}現在再也不理我了
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.80,1:57:03.64,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,except through lawyers.\N{\rCHT}除了通過律師來找我
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.39,1:57:08.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,People\N{\rCHT}人們…
Dialogue: 0,1:57:09.56,1:57:12.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,want an authority to tell them how to value things...\N{\rCHT}總希望有權威來告訴他們如何來選擇價值
Dialogue: 0,1:57:12.23,1:57:17.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,...but they choose this authority not based on facts or results.\N{\rCHT}但他們選擇權威 並不是基於事實情況 或者成就
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.15,1:57:23.82,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They choose it because it seems authoritative and familiar.\N{\rCHT}他們這樣選 只是因為這些人看起來很權威
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.91,1:57:26.37,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And I am not\N{\rCHT}說出了他們想聽的話
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.45,1:57:29.50,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and never have been "familiar".\N{\rCHT}可是 我從未盲從過大眾
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.46,1:57:32.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So...\N{\rCHT}所以…
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.33,1:57:36.46,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I've come to the sullen realization\N{\rCHT}我得到了嚴肅的結論
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.55,1:57:39.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that I must close down the fund.\N{\rCHT}我必須關閉基金
Dialogue: 0,1:57:39.42,1:57:42.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Sincerely, Michael J. Burry, M.D.\N{\rCHT}真誠的 邁克爾·巴里博士
Dialogue: 0,1:58:42.24,1:58:44.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't how I pictured it.\N{\rCHT}這和我想像的不一樣
Dialogue: 0,1:58:46.32,1:58:47.49,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think we'd find?\N{\rCHT}你以為是什麼樣的
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.57,1:58:48.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.\N{\rCHT}反正不是這樣
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.49,1:58:52.00,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Grownups.\N{\rCHT}人人都做個成年人
Dialogue: 0,1:58:55.92,1:58:57.42,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, you there?\N{\rCHT}馬克 你聽著嗎
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.09,1:59:01.34,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark?\N{\rCHT}馬克
Dialogue: 0,1:59:01.59,1:59:04.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Paulson and Bernanke just left the White House.\N{\rCHT}財政部長和美聯儲主席剛剛離開白宮
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.85,1:59:12.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,There's going to be a bailout.\N{\rCHT}可能政府要出手了
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.60,1:59:17.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they had to. Right?\N{\rCHT}不出手不行啊 是吧
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.35,1:59:18.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Paper markets would've collapsed.\N{\rCHT}我們用擔保兌付房貸
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.61,1:59:19.77,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They knew.\N{\rCHT}這些人早就知道
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.02,1:59:21.53,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Cash would've stopped coming out of ATMs.\N{\rCHT}ATM機回頭會取不出錢來的
Dialogue: 0,1:59:21.61,1:59:23.15,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They had to backstop this.\N{\rCHT}他們必須阻止這種情況發生
Dialogue: 0,1:59:23.44,1:59:25.78,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They knew the taxpayers would bail them out.\N{\rCHT}這些銀行家知道政府會用納稅人的錢保他們
Dialogue: 0,1:59:25.86,1:59:28.28,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They weren't being stupid. They just didn't care.\N{\rCHT}他們不是愚蠢 他們只是不在乎
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.45,1:59:30.62,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. 'Cause they're fucking crooks.\N{\rCHT}是啊 他媽的一幫騙子
Dialogue: 0,1:59:32.54,1:59:35.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But at least we're going to see some of them go to jail.\N{\rCHT}但是走著瞧吧 肯定會有人進監獄的
Dialogue: 0,1:59:36.29,1:59:39.54,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Right? I mean, they're gonna have to break up the banks.\N{\rCHT}是吧？大銀行會被拆分
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.63,1:59:41.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, the party's over.\N{\rCHT}不可能再為所欲為
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.05,1:59:44.72,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. I don't know, Vinnie.\N{\rCHT}我不知道 我不知道 文尼
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.47,1:59:48.97,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling\N{\rCHT}我總覺得
Dialogue: 0,1:59:49.05,1:59:50.93,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,that in a few years people are gonna be doing\N{\rCHT}幾年之內人們還是會和
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.01,1:59:54.02,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,what they always do when the economy tanks.\N{\rCHT}以前經濟危機一樣
Dialogue: 0,1:59:54.47,1:59:57.69,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They will be blaming immigrants and poor people.\N{\rCHT}責怪移民和窮人拖累了他們
Dialogue: 0,1:59:57.98,1:59:59.31,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mark was wrong.\N{\rCHT}但是馬克錯了
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.44,2:00:02.40,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,In the years that followed, hundreds of bankers\N{\rCHT}接下來的幾年 幾百個銀行
Dialogue: 0,2:00:02.48,2:00:05.11,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and rating agencies executives went to jail.\N{\rCHT}和評級高管進了監獄
Dialogue: 0,2:00:05.28,2:00:07.32,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The SEC was completely overhauled.\N{\rCHT}證券交易委員會被政府徹查
Dialogue: 0,2:00:07.49,2:00:10.20,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And Congress had no choice but to break up the big banks\N{\rCHT}議會也迫於壓力不得不拆分大銀行
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.62,2:00:13.08,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and regulate the mortgage and derivatives industries.\N{\rCHT}進一步規範房貸和金融衍生品市場
Dialogue: 0,2:00:17.87,2:00:19.21,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.\N{\rCHT}上面開玩笑啦
Dialogue: 0,2:00:19.46,2:00:21.67,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The banks took the money the American people gave them\N{\rCHT}銀行把人們投資的錢拿走
Dialogue: 0,2:00:21.75,2:00:24.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and used it to pay themselves huge bonuses\N{\rCHT}用來給他們自己開巨額獎金
Dialogue: 0,2:00:24.13,2:00:26.38,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,and lobby Congress to kill big reform.\N{\rCHT}然後賄賂議會 來駁回激進的改革
Dialogue: 0,2:00:26.55,2:00:28.80,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And then they blamed immigrants and poor people.\N{\rCHT}然後再把鍋甩到移民和窮鬼身上
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.88,2:00:31.05,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And this time, even teachers.\N{\rCHT}這次 連教師也跟著被指責
Dialogue: 0,2:00:32.43,2:00:35.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And when all was said and done, only one single banker went to jail.\N{\rCHT}這些都說完做完以後 只有一個銀行家被關了監獄
Dialogue: 0,2:00:36.39,2:00:37.52,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,This poor schmuck.\N{\rCHT}這個倒楣蛋
Dialogue: 0,2:00:37.60,2:00:40.06,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Kareem Serageldin from Credit Suisse.\N{\rCHT}瑞士瑞信銀行的卡裡姆
Dialogue: 0,2:00:40.40,2:00:42.73,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,He hid a few billion in mortgage bond losses,\N{\rCHT}他在房貸證券中損失了幾十億
Dialogue: 0,2:00:42.81,2:00:46.07,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,something most of the big banks did on a good day during the crisis.\N{\rCHT}但對金融危機的大銀行來說 這些損失都是平常事兒
Dialogue: 0,2:00:47.69,2:00:49.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,Mark, can we sell now?\N{\rCHT}馬克 我們能出手了嗎
Dialogue: 0,2:00:51.37,2:00:53.99,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,The fund will make almost $1 billion.\N{\rCHT}現在基金能回收10億
Dialogue: 0,2:00:54.08,2:00:55.70,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll clear $200 mil, Mark.\N{\rCHT}你能清算出2億來
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.87,2:00:59.12,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, once we sell,\N{\rCHT}可是… 如果我們出手
Dialogue: 0,2:00:59.87,2:01:01.75,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll be just like the rest of them.\N{\rCHT}最終和他們又有什麼不一樣
Dialogue: 0,2:01:01.83,2:01:02.96,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that.\N{\rCHT}你知道我的意思
Dialogue: 0,2:01:03.29,2:01:04.88,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we're not. We're not the bad guys here.\N{\rCHT}不一樣 我們不是壞人
Dialogue: 0,2:01:04.96,2:01:08.47,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't defraud the American people and prey on their dreams\N{\rCHT}我們沒有利用美國人 想要有個
Dialogue: 0,2:01:08.55,2:01:10.13,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,of owning a home. All right?\N{\rCHT}房子的夢想來詐騙
Dialogue: 0,2:01:10.22,2:01:11.51,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,They did.\N{\rCHT}像他們那樣
Dialogue: 0,2:01:12.51,2:01:14.81,ENG,,0000,0000,0000,,And now we get to kick them in the teeth.\N{\rCHT}現在出手能打得他們找牙
